Cools the <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link> piped through it, but outputs <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link> in its immediate vicinity.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.AIRFILTER.EFFE: Uses <link=\"SAND\">Sand</link> to filter <link=\"CONTAMINATEDOXYGEN\">Polluted Oxygen</link> from the air, reducing <link=\"DISEASE\">Disease</link> spread.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ALGAEHABITAT.E: Consumes <link=\"ALGAE\">Algae</link> to produce <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link> and remove some <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link>.\n\nGains a 10% efficiency boost in direct <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.APOTHECARY.DES: Some medications help prevent diseases, while others aim to alleviate existing illness.

Analyses and extracts <link=\"UNOBTANIUM\">Neutronium</link> from artifacts of interest.
This artifact has a {chance} to drop a Vacillator Recharge when analyzed at the <link=\"ARTIFACTANALYSISSTATION\">Artifact Analysis Station</link>

Allows Duplicants to store any artifacts they uncover during space missions.

Artifacts become available to the colony upon the rocket's return. 

Must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ASTRONAUTTRAIN: Duplicants must complete astronaut training in order to pilot space rockets.
Trains Duplicants to become <link=\"ROCKETPILOTING1\">Astronaut</link>.\n\nDuplicants must possess the <link=\"ROCKETPILOTING1\">Astronaut</link> trait to receive training.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.AUTOMINER.DESC: A robo-miner's range can be viewed at any time by selecting the building.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.AUTOMINER.NAME: <link=\"AUTOMINER\">Robo-Miner</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.BATTERY.DESC: Batteries allow power from generators to be stored for later.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.BATTERY.EFFECT: Stores <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> from generators, then provides that power to buildings.\n\nLoses charge over time.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.BATTERY.NAME: <link=\"BATTERY\">Battery</link>
Larger batteries hold more power and keep systems running longer before recharging.
Stores <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> from generators, then provides that power to buildings.\n\nSlightly loses charge over time.
Charging a battery module before takeoff makes it easier to power buildings during flight.

Stores the excess <link="POWER">Power</link> generated by a Rocket Engine or <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>.

Loses charge over time. 

Must be built via Rocket Platform.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.BATTERYSMART.A: Sends a Green Signal when battery is less than {0}% charged, until it is {1}% (High Threshold) charged

Smart batteries send a Green Signal when they require charging.

Sends a Red Signal when the battery is more than High Threshold charged, until Low Threshold is reached again
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.BEACHCHAIR.DES: Soak up some relaxing sun rays.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.BEACHCHAIR.EFF: Duplicants can relax by lounging in <link=\"LIGHT\">Sunlight</link>.\n\nIncreases Duplicant <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.

Duplicants will gain {amount} {attrib} if this building is in light dimmer than {lux}.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.BED.DESC: Duplicants without a bed will develop sore backs from sleeping on the floor.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.BED.FACADES.SC: For the Duplicant who dreams of scientific discoveries.

Like a weekend away, except... not.
Wrapped in shiny gold stars, to help sleepy Duplicants feel accomplished.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.BED.NAME: <link=\"BED\">Cot</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.BEEHIVE.DESC:
A moderately <link="RADIATION">Radioactive</link> nest made by <link="BEE">Beetas</link>.

Will not function if ground below has been destroyed.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.BEEHIVE.EFFECT: The cozy home of a Beeta.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.BEEHIVE.NAME: <link=\"BEEHIVE\">Beeta Hive</link>

Once the engine has been built, more rocket modules can be added.
More powerful rocket engines can propel heavier burdens.

<link=\"ARTWIDEA\">The Twins</link>
Every story has its origin.
<link=\"ARTWIDEB\">Ground Zero</link>

<link=\"ARTWIDEE\">Behold, A Fork</link>

<link=\"ARTWIDEF\">The Astronomer at Home</link>

<link=\"ARTWIDEG\">Iconic Iteration</link>

<link=\"ARTWIDEH\">La Belle Meep</link>

<link=\"ARTWIDEI\">Glorious Vole</link>

<link=\"ARTWIDEJ\">The Swell Swell</link>

<link=\"ARTWIDEK\">Flight of the Slicksters</link>

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.CO2ENGINE.EFFE:
Uses pressurized <link="CARBONDIOXIDE">Carbon Dioxide</link> to propel rockets for short range space exploration.

Carbon Dioxide Engines are relatively fast engine for their size but with limited height restrictions.

Engine must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.CRYOTANK.DEFRO: A new pal is just an icebreaker away
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.CRYOTANK.DESC: The tank appears impossibly old, but smells crisp and brand new.\n\nA silhouette just barely visible through the frost of the glass.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.CRYOTANK.NAME: <link=\"CRYOTANK\">Cryotank 3000</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DATAMINER.DESC: Data banks can also be used to program robo-pilot rocket modules.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DATAMINER.EFFE: Mass-produces <link=\"DATABANK\">Data Banks</link> that can be processed into <link=\"RESEARCHDLC1\">Data Analysis Research</link> points.\n\nDuplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DATAMINER.NAME: <link=\"DATAMINER\">Data Miner</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DECONTAMINATIO: Don't forget to decontaminate behind your ears.
Uses <link=\"WATER\">Water</link> to remove <link=\"DISEASE\">Germs</link> and <link=\"RADIATION\">Radiation</link>.\n\nDecontaminates both Duplicants and their <link=\"EQUIPMENT\">Clothing</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DEEPFRYER.DESC: Everything tastes better when it's deep-fried.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DEEPFRYER.EFFE: Uses <link=\"TALLOW\">Tallow</link> to cook a wide variety of improved <link=\"FOOD\">Foods</link>.\n\nDuplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DEEPFRYER.NAME: <link=\"DEEPFRYER\">Deep Fryer</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DEEPFRYER.STAT: This building must be in a Kitchen before it can be used
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DESALINATOR.DE: Salt can be refined into table salt for a mealtime morale boost.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DEVGENERATOR.E: Generates testing power for late nights.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DEVHEATER.EFFE: Generates on-demand heat for testing toastiness.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DEVLIGHTGENERA: Brightens up a dev's darkest hours.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DEVPUMPSOLID.D: Piping a pump's output to a building's intake will send solids to that building.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DININGTABLE.DE: Duplicants prefer to dine at a table, rather than eat off the floor.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DININGTABLE.EF: Gives one Duplicant a place to eat.\n\nDuplicants will automatically eat at their assigned table when hungry.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DIRECTIONALWOR: Channels move more volume than pumps and require no power, but need sufficient pressure to function.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DISTILLATIONCO: Separates any <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Contaminated Water</link> piped through it into <link=\"STEAM\">Steam</link> and <link=\"TOXICSAND\">Polluted Dirt</link>.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DLC2POITECHUNL: A functional research decrypter with one transmission remaining.\n\nIt was designed to support colony survival.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DLC4POITECHUNL: A functional research decrypter with one transmission remaining.\n\nIt was designed to support colony survival.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DOOR.CONTROL_S: Duplicants open and close this door as needed
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.DOOR.DESC: Door controls can be used to prevent Duplicants from entering restricted areas.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.EGGINCUBATOR.D: Incubators can maintain the ideal internal conditions for several species of critter egg.

Converts empty <link=\"ELECTROBANK\">Eco Power Banks</link> into fully charged units ready for reuse.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ELECTROLYZER.E: Converts <link=\"WATER\">Water</link> into <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link> and <link=\"HYDROGEN\">Hydrogen Gas</link>.\n\nBecomes idle when the area reaches maximum pressure capacity.

A colorful reservoir keeps gases neatly organized.
<link=\"GASRESERVOIR\">Greenpea Gas Reservoir</link>
Safe gas storage doesn't have to be dull.
<link=\"GASRESERVOIR\">Party Dot Gas Reservoir</link>
It sports the cheeriest of paint jobs. What a gas!
<link=\"GASRESERVOIR\">Mod Dot Gas Reservoir</link>
A colorful reservoir keeps gases neatly organized.
<link=\"GASRESERVOIR\">Faint Purple Gas Reservoir</link>
A colorful reservoir keeps gases neatly organized.
<link=\"GASRESERVOIR\">Puce Pink Gas Reservoir</link>
A colorful reservoir keeps gases neatly organized.
<link=\"GASRESERVOIR\">Ick Yellow Gas Reservoir</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GASVALVE.DESC: Valves control the amount of gas that moves through pipes, preventing waste.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GASVALVE.NAME: <link=\"GASVALVE\">Gas Valve</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GASVENT.DESC: Vents are an exit point for gases from ventilation systems.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GASVENT.NAME: <link=\"GASVENT\">Gas Vent</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GASVENTHIGHPRE: High pressure vents can expel gas into more highly pressurized environments.
Releases <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link> from <link=\"GASPIPING\">Gas Pipes</link> into high pressure locations.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GENERATOR.DESC: Burning coal produces more energy than manual power, but emits heat and exhaust.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GENERATOR.NAME: <link=\"GENERATOR\">Coal Generator</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GENERICFABRICA: Omniprinters are incapable of printing organic matter.
Converts <link=\"RAWMINERAL\">Raw Mineral</link> into unique materials and objects.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GENESHUFFLER.D: A massive synthetic brain, suspended in saline solution.\n\nThere is a chair attached to the device with room for one person.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GENETICANALYSI: Would a mutated rose still smell as sweet?
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GEOTHERMALCONT: What comes out depends very much on the initial temperature of what goes in.
Uses <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link> from the planet's core to dramatically increase the temperature of <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> inputs.\n\nMaterials will be emitted at connected Geo Vents.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GEOTHERMALVENT: Blocked geo vents can be cleared by pumping in <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">liquids</link> that are hot enough to melt <link=\"LEAD\">Lead</link>.
Geo vents must finish their current emission before accepting new materials.
Emits high-<link=\"HEAT\">temperature</link> materials received from the Geothermal Heat Pump.
Sends a Green Signal when geo vent has materials to emit
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GEOTUNER.DESC: The targeted geyser receives stored amplification data when it is erupting.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GEOTUNER.EFFEC: Increases the <link=\"HEAT\">Temperature</link> and output of an analyzed <link=\"GEYSERS\">Geyser</link>.\n\nMultiple Geotuners can be directed at a single <link=\"GEYSERS\">Geyser</link> anywhere on an asteroid.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GEOTUNER.LOGIC: Sends a Green Signal when geyser is erupting
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GEOTUNER.NAME: <link=\"GEOTUNER\">Geotuner</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GLASSFORGE.DES: Glass can be used to construct window tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GLASSFORGE.EFF:
Produces <link="MOLTENGLASS">Molten Glass</link> from raw <link="SAND">Sand</link>.

Outputs <link="HEAT">High Temperature</link> <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link>.

Duplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GLASSTILE.DESC: Window tiles provide a barrier against liquid and gas and are completely transparent.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GLASSTILE.EFFE: Used to build the walls and floors of rooms.\n\nAllows <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link> and <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link> to pass through.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GLASSTILE.NAME: <link=\"GLASSTILE\">Window Tile</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GOURMETCOOKING: Luxury meals increase Duplicants' morale and prevent them from becoming stressed.
Cooks a wide variety of quality <link=\"FOOD\">Foods</link>.\n\nDuplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GRAVE.DESC: Burying dead Duplicants reduces health hazards and stress on the colony.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GRAVE.EFFECT: Provides a final resting place for deceased Duplicants.\n\nLiving Duplicants will automatically place an unburied corpse inside.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GRAVE.NAME: <link=\"GRAVE\">Tasteful Memorial</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GRAVITASBATHRO: A private toilet for senior scientists.\n\nIt was the site of many great scientific breakthroughs.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GRAVITASCONTAI: A clothing storage unit.\n\nIt contains ultra-soft sleepwear.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GRAVITASCREATU: An experimental DNA manipulator.\n\nAnalyzes <link=\"CREATURES\">Critters</link> to transform base morphs into random variants of their species.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GRAVITASDOOR.E: An office door to an office that no longer exists.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GRAVITASLABLIG: An overhead light therapy lamp designed to soothe the minds.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GRAVITASPEDEST: Perception can be drastically changed by a bit of thoughtful presentation.
Displays a single object, doubling its <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link> value.\n\nObjects with negative Decor will gain some positive Decor when displayed.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GUNKEMPTIER.DE: Bionic Duplicants are much more relaxed after a visit to the gunk extractor.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.GUNKEMPTIER.EF: Cleanses stale <link=\"LIQUIDGUNK\">Gunk</link> build-up from Duplicants' bionic parts.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HABITATMODULEM: Allows Duplicants to survive space travel... Hopefully.

Functions as a Command Module.

Holds up to 10 Duplicant travellers.

One Command Module may be installed per rocket. 

Must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HABITATMODULES: One lucky Duplicant gets the best view from the whole rocket.

Functions as a Command Module and a Nosecone.

Holds one Duplicant traveller.

One Command Module may be installed per rocket.

Must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>. 

Must be built at the top of a rocket.
Hand sanitizers kill germs more effectively than wash basins.
Removes most <link=\"DISEASE\">Germs</link> from Duplicants.\n\nGerm-covered Duplicants use Hand Sanitizers when passing by in the selected direction.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HEADQUARTERS.D: New Duplicants come out here, but thank goodness, they never go back in.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HEADQUARTERS.E: An exceptionally advanced bioprinter of unknown origin.\n\nIt periodically produces new Duplicants or care packages containing resources.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HEADQUARTERSCO: A clone of the cloning machine? What a novel thought.\n\nAlas, it won't work.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HEATCOMPRESSOR: Heats or cools <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> to match ambient <link=\"HEAT\">Air Temperature</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HEPBATTERY.DES: Particles packed up and ready to go.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HEPBATTERY.EFF: Stores Radbolts in a high-energy state, ready for transport. Requires a Green Signal to release radbolts from storage when the Radbolt threshold is reached. Radbolts in storage will rapidly decay while this building is disabled.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HEPBATTERY.LOG: Sends a Green Signal when its Radbolt Storage is full
Allows Radbolts to pass through walls.

Receives <link=\"RADIATION\">Radbolts</link> from <link=\"HIGHENERGYPARTICLESPAWNER\">Radbolt Generators</link> and directs them through walls. All other materials and elements will be blocked from passage.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HEPENGINE.DESC: Radbolt-fueled rockets support few modules, but travel exceptionally far.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HEPENGINE.EFFE:
Injects <link="RADIATION">Radbolts</link> into a reaction chamber to propel rockets for long-range space exploration.

Radbolt Engines are faster than <link="HYDROGENENGINE">Hydrogen Engines</link> but with a more restrictive height allowance.

Engine must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>. 

Once the engine has been built, more rocket modules can be added.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HEPENGINE.LOGI: Sends a Green Signal when its Radbolt Storage is full
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HEPENGINE.NAME: <link=\"HEPENGINE\">Radbolt Engine</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HIGHENERGYPART: We were all out of mirrors.
Receives and redirects Radbolts from <link=\"HIGHENERGYPARTICLESPAWNER\">Radbolt Generators</link>.
Radbolts are necessary for producing Materials Science research.

Attracts nearby <link="RADIATION">Radiation</link> to generate Radbolts.

Emits generated Radbolts in the direction of your choosing when the set Radbolt threshold is reached.

Radbolts collected will gradually decay while this building is disabled.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HIGHWATTAGEWIR: Higher wattage wire is used to avoid power overloads, particularly for strong generators.
Carries more <link=\"POWER\">Wattage</link> than regular <link=\"WIRE\">Wire</link> without overloading.\n\nCannot be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HIJACKEDHEADQU: The access code required to reboot it for testing is located somewhere on this world.
An unsanctioned bioprinter that runs on power siphoned from the <link=\"HEADQUARTERS\">Printing Pod</link>.

Intercepts and stores <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> charges from the <link=\"HEADQUARTERS\">Printing Pod</link>.\n\nConverts stored charges and <link=\"DATABANK\">Data Banks</link> into <link=\"CREATURES\">Seeds</link> and <link=\"CREATURES\">Eggs</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HOTTUB.DESC: Relaxes Duplicants with massaging jets of heated liquid.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HOTTUB.EFFECT:
Requires <link="LIQUIDPIPING">Pipes</link> to and from tub and <link="POWER">Power</link> to run the jets.

Water must be a comfortable temperature and will cool rapidly.

Increases Duplicant <link="MORALE">Morale</link> and leaves them feeling deliciously warm.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HOTTUB.NAME: <link=\"HOTTUB\">Hot Tub</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HOTTUB.TEMPERA: The Hot Tub will only be usable if supplied with {temperature} {element}. If the {element} gets too cold, the Hot Tub will drain and require refilling with {element}.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HOTTUB.WATER_R: This building must be filled with {amount} {element} in order to function.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HYDROGENENGINE: Hydrogen engines can propel rockets further than steam or petroleum engines.

Burns <link="LIQUIDHYDROGEN">Liquid Hydrogen</link> to propel rockets for long-range space exploration.

Hydrogen Engines have the same generous height restrictions as <link="KEROSENEENGINE">Petroleum Engines</link> but are slightly faster.

The engine must be built first before more rocket modules can be added.
Hydrogen engines can propel rockets further than steam or petroleum engines.

Burns <link="LIQUIDHYDROGEN">Liquid Hydrogen</link> to propel rockets for long-range space exploration.

Hydrogen Engines have the same generous height restrictions as <link="KEROSENEENGINE">Petroleum Engines</link> but are slightly faster.

Engine must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>, and requires an oxidizer tank.

Once the engine has been built, more rocket modules can be added.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HYDROGENGENERA: Hydrogen generators are extremely efficient, emitting next to no waste.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.HYDROPONICFARM: Hydroponic farms reduce Duplicant traffic by automating irrigating crops.

Grows one <link="PLANTS">Plant</link> from a <link="PLANTS">Seed</link>.

Can be used as floor tile and rotated before construction.

Must be irrigated through <link="LIQUIDPIPING">Liquid Piping</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ICECOOLEDFAN.D: A Duplicant can work an Ice-E fan to temporarily cool small areas as needed.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ICECOOLEDFAN.E: Uses <link=\"ICEORE\">Ice</link> to dissipate a small amount of the <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ICEKETTLE.DESC: The water never gets hot enough to burn the tongue.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ICEKETTLE.EFFE: Consumes <link=\"WOOD\">Wood</link> to melt <link=\"ICE\">Ice</link> into <link=\"WATER\">Water</link>, which can be bottled for transport.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ICEKETTLE.NAME: <link=\"ICEKETTLE\">Ice Liquefier</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ICEMACHINE.DES: Ice makers can be used as a small renewable source of ice and snow.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ICESCULPTURE.E: Majorly increases <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link>, contributing to <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.\n\nMust be sculpted by a Duplicant.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ICESCULPTURE.F: These incisors are the stuff of dental legend.
A charming depiction of the mighty Pokeshell in mid-rampage.
Some aquarists posit that Pacus are the original creators of the game now known as \"Tag.\"
It's structurally unsound, but otherwise not entirely terrible.
A slow-moving door that works best when it's closed.
Significantly reduces <link=\"HEAT\">Temperature</link> exchange between climate-controlled rooms.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.INSULATEDGASCO: Pipe insulation prevents gas contents from significantly changing temperature in transit.
Carries <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link> with minimal change in <link=\"HEAT\">Temperature</link>.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.INSULATEDLIQUI: Pipe insulation prevents liquid contents from significantly changing temperature in transit.
Carries <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> with minimal change in <link=\"HEAT\">Temperature</link>.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
This stuff won't go melting if things get heated.
Connects buildings to <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> sources in extreme <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link>.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.INSULATIONTILE: The low thermal conductivity of insulated tiles slows any heat passing through them.
Used to build the walls and floors of rooms.\n\nReduces <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link> transfer between walls, retaining ambient heat in an area.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ITEMPEDESTAL.D: Perception can be drastically changed by a bit of thoughtful presentation.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ITEMPEDESTAL.E: Displays a single object, doubling its <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link> value.\n\nObjects with negative Decor will gain some positive Decor when displayed.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ITEMPEDESTAL.F: Perception can be drastically changed by a bit of thoughtful presentation.
This pedestal cradles precious objects in the palm of its hand.
Jet suit docks can refill jet suits with air and fuel, or empty them of waste.

Stores <link="JETSUIT">Jet Suits</link> and refuels them with <link="OXYGEN">Oxygen</link> and <link="COMBUSTIBLELIQUID">Combustible Liquid</link>.

Empties suits of <link="DIRTYWATER">Polluted Water</link>.

Build next to a <link="JETSUITMARKER">Jet Suit Checkpoint</link> to make Duplicants change into suits when passing by.
A checkpoint must have a correlating dock built on the opposite side its arrow faces.

Marks a threshold where Duplicants must change into or out of <link="JETSUIT">Jet Suits</link>.

Must be built next to a <link="JETSUITLOCKER">Jet Suit Dock</link>.

Can be rotated before construction.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.JUICER.DESC: Fruity juice can really brighten a Duplicant's breaktime
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.JUICER.EFFECT: Provides refreshment for Duplicants on their breaks.\n\nDrinking juice increases Duplicant <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.JUICER.NAME: <link=\"JUICER\">Juicer</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.KEROSENEENGINE: Rockets can be used to send Duplicants into space and retrieve rare resources.

Burns <link="PETROLEUM">Petroleum</link> to propel rockets for mid-range space exploration.

Petroleum Engines have generous height restrictions, ideal for hauling many modules.

The engine must be built first before more rocket modules can be added.
More powerful rocket engines can propel heavier burdens.

Burns <link="PETROLEUM">Petroleum</link> to propel rockets for mid-range space exploration.

Petroleum Engines have generous height restrictions, ideal for hauling many modules.

Engine must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>, and requires an oxidizer tank. 

Once the engine has been built, more rocket modules can be added.
Rockets can be used to send Duplicants into space and retrieve rare resources.

Burns <link="PETROLEUM">Petroleum</link> to propel rockets for mid-range space exploration.

Small Petroleum Engines possess the same speed as a <link="KEROSENEENGINE">Petroleum Engines</link> but have smaller height restrictions.

Engine must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>, and requires an oxidizer tank.

Once the engine has been built, more rocket modules can be added.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.KILN.EFFECT: Fires <link=\"CLAY\">Clay</link> to produce <link=\"CERAMIC\">Ceramic</link>, and <link=\"CARBON\">Coal</link> or <link=\"WOOD\">Wood</link> to produce <link=\"REFINEDCARBON\">Refined Carbon</link>.\n\nDuplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.KILN.NAME: <link=\"KILN\">Kiln</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LADDER.NAME: <link=\"LADDER\">Ladder</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LADDERBED.DESC: Duplicant's sleep will be interrupted if another Duplicant uses the ladder.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LADDERBED.EFFE: Provides a sleeping area for one Duplicant and also functions as a ladder.\n\nDuplicants will automatically sleep in their assigned beds at night.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LADDERBED.NAME: <link=\"LADDERBED\">Ladder Bed</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LADDERFAST.DES: Plastic ladders are mildly antiseptic and can help limit the spread of germs in a colony.
Microtarget where your <link=\"RAILGUNPAYLOAD\">Interplanetary Payload</link> lands on a Planetoid surface.

Guides <link=\"RAILGUNPAYLOAD\">Interplanetary Payloads</link> and <link=\"ORBITALCARGOMODULE\">Orbital Cargo Modules</link> to land nearby.\n\n<link=\"RAILGUNPAYLOAD\">Interplanetary Payloads</link> must be launched from a <link=\"RAILGUN\">Interplanetary Launcher</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LANDING_POD.EF: Contains a Duplicant deployed from orbit.\n\nPod will disintegrate on arrival.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LARGEELECTROBA: It's basically its own power grid.
Efficiently converts stored energy from <link=\"ELECTROBANK\">Power Banks</link> into power for connected buildings.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LAUNCHPAD.DESC: A platform from which rockets can be launched and on which they can land.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LAUNCHPAD.EFFE:
Precursor to construction of all other Rocket modules.

Allows Rockets to launch from or land on the host Planetoid.

Automatically links up to <link="MODULARLAUNCHPADPORTSOLID">Rocket Port</link><link="MODULARLAUNCHPADPORTSOLID">s</link> built to either side of the platform.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LAUNCHPAD.LOGI: Sends a Green Signal when its rocket is on the <link=\"LAUNCHPAD\">Rocket Platform</link>
Sends a Green Signal when its rocket is ready for flight
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LAUNCHPAD.NAME: <link=\"LAUNCHPAD\">Rocket Platform</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LEADSUITLOCKER: Lead suit docks can refill lead suits with air and empty them of waste.

Stores <link="LEADSUIT">Lead Suits</link> and refuels them with <link="OXYGEN">Oxygen</link>.

Empties suits of <link="DIRTYWATER">Polluted Water</link>.

Build next to a <link="LEADSUITMARKER">Lead Suit Checkpoint</link> to make Duplicants change into suits when passing by.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LEADSUITMARKER: A checkpoint must have a correlating dock built on the opposite side its arrow faces.

Marks a threshold where Duplicants must change into or out of <link="LEADSUIT">Lead Suits</link>.

Must be built next to a <link="LEADSUITLOCKER">Lead Suit Dock</link>

Can be rotated before construction.
Bottle fillers allow Duplicants to manually deliver liquids from place to place.
Automatically stores piped <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquids</link> into bottles for manual transport.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDCARGOBAY: Duplicants will fill cargo bays with any resources they find during space missions.
Allows Duplicants to store any <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> resources found during space missions.\n\nStored resources become available to the colony upon the rocket's return.
Holds more than a regular cargo tank.

Allows Duplicants to store most of the <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link> resources found during space missions.

Stored resources become available to the colony upon the rocket's return.

Must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>.
Duplicants will fill cargo tanks with whatever resources they find during space missions.

Allows Duplicants to store some of the <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link> resources found during space missions.

Stored resources become available to the colony upon the rocket's return. 

Must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDCONDITIO: A thermo aquatuner cools liquid and outputs the heat elsewhere.
Cools the <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> piped through it, but outputs <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link> in its immediate vicinity.
Liquid pipes are used to connect the inputs and outputs of plumbed buildings.
Carries <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> between <link=\"LIQUIDPIPING\">Outputs</link> and <link=\"LIQUIDPIPING\">Intakes</link>.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDCONDUITB: Separate pipe systems help prevent building damage caused by mingled pipe contents.
Runs one <link=\"LIQUIDPIPING\">Liquid Pipe</link> section over another without joining them.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDCONDUITD: Germ sensors can help control automation behavior in the presence of germs.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal based on the internal Germ count of the pipe.
Sends a Green Signal if the number of Germs in the pipe is within the selected range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDCONDUITE: Element sensors can be used to detect the presence of a specific liquid in a pipe.
Sends a Green Signal when the selected Liquid is detected within a pipe.
Sends a Green Signal if the configured Liquid is detected within the pipe
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDCONDUITO: Overflow valves can be used to prioritize which buildings should receive precious resources first.
Fills a secondary<link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> output only when its primary output is blocked.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDCONDUITP: Priority flows ensure important buildings are filled first when on a system with other buildings.
Diverts <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> to a secondary input when its primary input overflows.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDCONDUITR: Radiant pipes pumping cold liquid can be run through hot areas to help cool them down.
Carries <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link>, allowing extreme <link=\"HEAT\">Temperature</link> exchange with the surrounding environment.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDCONDUITT: Thermo sensors disable buildings when their pipe contents reach a certain temperature.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal when pipe contents enter the chosen Temperature range.
Sends a Green Signal if the contained Liquid is within the selected Temperature range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDCOOLEDFA: A Duplicant can work a hydrofan to temporarily cool small areas as needed.
Dissipates a small amount of the <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDFILTER.D: All liquids are sent into the building's output pipe, except the liquid chosen for filtering.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDFILTER.E: Sieves one <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> out of a mix, sending it into a dedicated <link=\"LIQUIDPIPING\">Filtered Output Pipe</link>.\n\nCan only filter one liquid type at a time.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDFUELTANK: Storing additional fuel increases the distance a rocket can travel before returning.
Stores the <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> fuel piped into it to supply rocket engines.\n\nThe stored fuel type is determined by the rocket engine it is built upon.
Storing additional fuel increases the distance a rocket can travel before returning.

Stores the <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link> fuel piped into it to supply rocket engines.

The stored fuel type is determined by the rocket engine it is built upon. 

Must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDHEATER.D: Tepidizers heat liquid which can kill waterborne germs.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDHEATER.E: Warms large bodies of <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link>.\n\nMust be fully submerged.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDLIMITVAL: Meter Valves let an exact amount of liquid pass through before shutting off.
Connects to an <link=\"LOGIC\">Automation</link> grid to automatically turn <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> flow off when the specified amount has passed through it.
Sends a Green Signal if limit has been reached
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDLOGICVAL: Automated piping saves power and time by removing the need for Duplicant input.
Connects to an <link=\"LOGIC\">Automation</link> grid to automatically turn <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> flow on or off.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDMINIPUMP: Mini pumps are useful for moving small quantities of liquid with minimum power.
Draws in a small amount of <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> and runs it through <link=\"LIQUIDPIPING\">Pipes</link>.\n\nMust be submerged in <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDPUMP.DES: Piping a pump's output to a building's intake will send liquid to that building.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDPUMP.EFF: Draws in <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> and runs it through <link=\"LIQUIDPIPING\">Pipes</link>.\n\nMust be submerged in <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDPUMPINGS: Pitcher pumps allow Duplicants to bottle and deliver liquids from place to place.
Manually pumps <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> into bottles for transport.\n\nDuplicants can only carry liquids that are bottled.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDRESERVOI: Reservoirs cannot receive manually delivered resources.
Stores any <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> resources piped into it.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDVALVE.DE: Valves control the amount of liquid that moves through pipes, preventing waste.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LIQUIDVENT.DES: Vents are an exit point for liquids from plumbing systems.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICALARM.DES: Sends a notification when it receives a Green Signal.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICALARM.EFF: Attach to sensors to send a notification when certain conditions are met.\n\nNotifications can be customized.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICCLUSTERLO: Starmap Location sensors can signal when a spacecraft is at a certain location
Send Green Signals at the chosen Starmap locations and Red Signals everywhere else.
Sends a Green Signalwhen a spacecraft is at the chosen Starmap locations
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICCOUNTER.D: For numbers higher than ten connect multiple counters together.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICCOUNTER.E: Counts how many times a Green Signal has been received up to a chosen number.\n\nWhen the chosen number is reached it sends a Green Signal until it receives another Green Signal, when it resets automatically and begins counting again.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICCOUNTER.O: Sends a Green Signal when the counter matches the selected value
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICCRITTERCO: Detecting critter populations can help adjust their automated feeding and care regimens.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal based on the number of eggs and critters in a room.
Sends a Green Signal if the number of Critters and Eggs in the Room is greater than the selected threshold.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICDISEASESE: Detecting germ populations can help block off or clean up dangerous areas.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal based on quantity of surrounding Germs.
Sends a Green Signal if the number of Germs is within the selected range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICDUPLICANT: Motion sensors save power by only enabling buildings when Duplicants are nearby.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal based on whether a Duplicant is in the sensor's range.
Sends a Green Signal while a Duplicant is in the sensor's tile range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICELEMENTSE: These sensors can detect the presence of a specific gas and alter systems accordingly.
Sends a Green Signal when the selected Gas is detected on this sensor's tile.\n\nSends a Red Signal when the selected Gas is not present.
Sends a Green Signal if the selected Gas is detected
These sensors can detect the presence of a specific liquid and alter systems accordingly.
Sends a Green Signal when the selected Liquid is detected on this sensor's tile.\n\nSends a Red Signal when the selected Liquid is not present.
Sends a Green Signal if the selected Liquid is detected
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEAND.D: This gate outputs a Green Signal when both its inputs are receiving Green Signals at the same time.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEAND.E: Outputs a Green Signal when both Input A AND Input B are receiving Green.\n\nOutputs a Red Signal when even one Input is receiving Red.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEAND.O: Sends a Green Signal if both Inputs are receiving Green
Sends a Red Signal if any Input is receiving Red
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEBUFFE: This gate continues outputting a Green Signal for a short time after the gate stops receiving a Green Signal.
Outputs a Green Signal if the Input is receiving a Green Signal.\n\nContinues sending a Green Signal for an amount of buffer time after the Input receives a Red Signal.
Sends a Green Signal while receiving Green. After receiving Red, will continue sending Green until the timer has expired
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEDEMUL: Signal Distributors can be used to choose which circuit should receive a given automation signal.

Route a single Input signal out one of four possible Outputs, based on the selection made by the Control Inputs.\n\nSend a Green Signal or a Red Signal to the two Control Inputs to determine which Output is selected.
Sends a Green or Red signal to the selected output
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEFILTE: This gate only lets a Green Signal through if its Input has received a Green Signal that lasted longer than the selected filter time.

Only lets a Green Signal through if the Input has received a Green Signal for longer than the selected filter time.\n\nWill continue outputting a Red Signal if the Green Signal did not last long enough.
Sends a Green Signal after receiving Green for longer than the selected filter timer
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEMULTI: Signal Selectors can be used to select which automation signal is relevant to pass through to a given circuit
Select which one of four Input signals should be sent out the Output, using Control Inputs.\n\nSend a Green Signal or a Red Signal to the two Control Inputs to determine which Input is selected.
Receives a Green or Red signal from the selected input
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATENOT.D: This gate reverses automation signals, turning a Green Signal into a Red Signal and vice versa.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATENOT.E: Outputs a Green Signal if the Input is receiving a Red Signal.\n\nOutputs a Red Signal when its Input is receiving a Green Signal.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEOR.DE: This gate outputs a Green Signal if receiving one or more Green Signals.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEOR.EF: Outputs a Green Signal if at least one of Input A OR Input B is receiving Green.\n\nOutputs a Red Signal when neither Input A or Input B are receiving Green.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEOR.OU: Sends a Green Signal if any Input is receiving Green
Sends a Red Signal if both Inputs are receiving Red
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEXOR.D: This gate outputs a Green Signal if exactly one of its Inputs is receiving a Green Signal.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEXOR.E: Outputs a Green Signal if exactly one of its Inputs is receiving Green.\n\nOutputs a Red Signal if both or neither Inputs are receiving a Green Signal.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICGATEXOR.O: Sends a Green Signal if exactly one of its Inputs is receiving Green
Sends a Red Signal if both Input signals match (any color)
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICHAMMER.DE: The hammer makes neat sounds when it strikes buildings.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICHAMMER.EF: In its default orientation, the hammer strikes the building to the left when it receives a Green Signal. Each building has a unique sound when struck by the hammer. The hammer does no damage when it strikes.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICHEPSENSOR: Radbolt sensors can send a signal when a Radbolt passes over them.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal when Radbolts detected enters the chosen range.
Sends a Green Signal if detected Radbolts are within the selected range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICINTERASTE: Receives a Green Signal or a Red Signal from an Automation Broadcaster over vast distances in space.\n\nBoth the Automation Receiver and the Automation Broadcaster must be exposed to space to function.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal to an Automation Receiver over vast distances in space.\n\nBoth the Automation Broadcaster and the Automation Receiver must be exposed to space to function.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICLIGHTSENS: Light sensors can tell surface bunker doors above solar panels to open or close based on solar light levels.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal when ambient Brightness enters the chosen range.
Sends a Green Signal if ambient Brightness is within the selected range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICMEMORY.DE: A Memory stores a Green Signal received in the Set Port (S) until the Reset Port (R) receives a Green Signal.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICMEMORY.EF: Contains an internal Memory, and will output whatever signal is stored in that Memory. Signals sent to the Inputs only affect the Memory, and do not pass through to the Output. Sending a Green Signal to the Set Port (S) will set the memory to Green. Sending a Green Signal to the Reset Port (R) will reset the memory back to Red.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICMEMORY.RE: Outputs a Green Signal if the internal Memory is set to Green
Outputs a Red Signal if the internal Memory is set to Red
Green Signal: Reset the internal Memory to Red
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICMEMORY.SE: Green Signal: Set the internal Memory to Green
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICPOWERRELA: Automated systems save power and time by removing the need for Duplicant input.
Connects to an <link=\"LOGIC\">Automation</link> grid to automatically turn <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> on or off.\n\nDoes not affect circuitry preceding the switch.
Red Signal: Prevent Power from flowing through connected circuits
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICPRESSURES: Atmo sensors can be used to prevent excess oxygen production and overpressurization.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal when Gas pressure enters the chosen range.
Sends a Green Signal if Gas pressure is within the selected range
A hydro sensor can tell a pump to refill its basin as soon as it contains too little liquid.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal when Liquid pressure enters the chosen range.\n\nMust be submerged in Liquid.
Sends a Green Signal if Liquid pressure is within the selected range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICRADIATION: Radiation sensors can disable buildings when they detect dangerous levels of radiation.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal when ambient Radiation enters the chosen range.
Sends a Green Signal if ambient Radiation is within the selected range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICRIBBON.DE: Logic ribbons use significantly less space to carry multiple automation signals.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICRIBBON.EF: A 4-Bit <link=\"LOGICWIRE\">Automation Wire</link> which can carry up to four automation signals.\n\nUse a <link=\"LOGICRIBBONWRITER\">Ribbon Writer</link> to output to multiple Bits, and a <link=\"LOGICRIBBONREADER\">Ribbon Reader</link> to input from multiple Bits.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICRIBBONBRI: Wire bridges allow multiple automation grids to exist in a small area without connecting.
Runs one <link=\"LOGICRIBBON\">Automation Ribbon</link> section over another without joining them.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICRIBBONREA: Inputs the signal from a single Bit in an <link=\"LOGICRIBBON\">Automation Ribbon</link> into an <link=\"LOGICWIRE\">Automation Wire</link>.
Reads a Green Signal or a Red Signal from the specified Bit of an Automation Ribbon onto an Automation Wire.
Green Signal: Reads a Green Signal from selected Bit
Red Signal: Reads a Red Signal from selected Bit
Green Signal: Sends a Green Signal to attached Automation Wire
Red Signal: Sends a Red Signal to attached Automation Wire
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICRIBBONWRI: Translates the signal from an <link=\"LOGICWIRE\">Automation Wire</link> to a single Bit in an <link=\"LOGICRIBBON\">Automation Ribbon</link>
Writes a Green Signal or a Red Signal to the specified Bit of an Automation Ribbon\n\nAutomation Ribbon must be used as the output wire to avoid overloading.
Green Signal: Receives Green Signal to be written to selected Bit
Red Signal: Receives Red Signal to to be written selected Bit
Green Signal: Writes a Green Signal to selected Bit of an Automation Ribbon
Red Signal: Writes a Red Signal to selected Bit of an Automation Ribbon
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICSWITCH.DE: Signal switches don't turn grids on and off like power switches, but add an extra signal.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICSWITCH.EF: Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal on an Automation grid.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICSWITCH.LO: Sends a Green Signal if toggled ON
Sends a Red Signal if toggled OFF
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICTEMPERATU: Thermo sensors can disable buildings when they approach dangerous temperatures.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal when ambient Temperature enters the chosen range.
Sends a Green Signal if ambient Temperature is within the selected range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICTIMEOFDAY: Cycle sensors ensure systems always turn on at the same time, day or night, every cycle.
Sets an automatic Green Signal and Red Signal schedule within one day-night cycle.
Sends a Green Signal if current time is within the selected Green range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICTIMERSENS: Timer sensors create automation schedules for very short or very long periods of time.
Creates a timer to send Green Signals and Red Signals for specific amounts of time.
Sends a Green Signal for the selected amount of Green time
Then, sends a Red Signal for the selected amount of Red time
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICWATTAGESE: Wattage sensors can send a signal when a building has switched on or off.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal when Wattage consumed enters the chosen range.
Sends a Green Signal if current Wattage is within the selected range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICWIRE.DESC: Automation wire is used to connect building ports to automation gates.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICWIRE.EFFE: Connects buildings to <link=\"LOGIC\">Sensors</link>.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICWIRE.NAME: <link=\"LOGICWIRE\">Automation Wire</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LOGICWIREBRIDG: Wire bridges allow multiple automation grids to exist in a small area without connecting.
Runs one <link=\"LOGICWIRE\">Automation Wire</link> section over another without joining them.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
There's nothing quite like receiving homemade gifts in the mail.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LONELYMINIONHO: Its occupant has been alone for so long, he's forgotten what friendship feels like.
A large transport unit from the facility's sub-sub-basement.\n\nIt has been modified into a crude yet functional temporary shelter.
Someone lived inside it for a while.
A super-spacious container for the <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid Materials</link> of your choosing.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LUXURYBED.DESC: Duplicants prefer comfy beds to cots and wake up more rested after sleeping in them.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LUXURYBED.EFFE: Provides a sleeping area for one Duplicant and restores additional stamina.\n\nDuplicants will automatically sleep in their assigned beds at night.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LUXURYBED.FACA: An inflatable party prop makes a surprisingly good bed.
Where every Duplicant wakes up a winner.
The mattress is so soft, it's almost impossible to climb out of.
It's so nice to be held.
A comfy, if somewhat 'fragrant', place to sleep.
A soft landing spot for swooners.
A pink-hued bed for rosy dreams.
Launches sleepy Duplicants into a deep-space slumber.
A little pattern recognition at bedtime soothes the mind.
When life is icky, bed rest is the only answer.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.LUXURYBED.NAME: <link=\"LUXURYBED\">Comfy Bed</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MACHINESHOP.DE: Duplicants will only improve the efficiency of buildings in the same room as this station.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MACHINESHOP.EF: Allows the assigned <link=\"MACHINETECHNICIAN\">Engineer</link> to improve building production efficiency.\n\nThis building is a necessary component of the Machine Shop room.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MANUALGENERATO: Watching Duplicants run on it is adorable... the electrical power is just an added bonus.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MANUALHIGHENER: Radbolts are necessary for producing Materials Science research.
Refines radioactive ores to generate Radbolts.\n\nEmits generated Radbolts in the direction of your choosing.
Creates <link=\"RADIATION\">Radbolts</link> by processing {0}. Also creates {1} as a byproduct.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MANUALPRESSURE: Airlocks can quarter off dangerous areas and prevent gases from seeping into the colony.
Blocks <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> and <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link> flow, maintaining pressure between areas.\n\nWild <link=\"CREATURES\">Critters</link> cannot pass through doors.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MARBLESCULPTUR: Duplicants who have learned art skills can produce more decorative sculptures.
Majorly increases <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link>, contributing to <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.\n\nMust be sculpted by a Duplicant.
She's not afraid to take up space.
The artist took great pleasure in conveying their displeasure.
A masterful celebration of one of the universe's most mysterious - and flatulent - organisms.
A masterful celebration of the deep bond between a horticulturalist and her prize Bristle Blossom.
The artist was a very fungi.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MASSAGETABLE.A: Duplicants must take a massage break when their <style=\"KKeyword\">Stress</style> reaches {0}%
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MASSAGETABLE.D: Breaktime ends when <style=\"KKeyword\">Stress</style> is reduced to {0}%
Massage tables quickly reduce extreme stress, at the cost of power production.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MASSAGETABLE.E: Rapidly reduces <link=\"STRESS\">Stress</link> for the Duplicant user.\n\nDuplicants will automatically seek a massage table when <link=\"STRESS\">Stress</link> exceeds breaktime range.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MASSAGETABLE.F: Massage tables quickly reduce extreme stress, at the cost of power production.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MASSIVEHEATSIN: A self-sustaining machine powered by what appears to be refined <link=\"UNOBTANIUM\">Neutronium</link>.\n\nAbsorbs and neutralizes <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link> energy when provided with piped <link=\"HYDROGEN\">Hydrogen Gas</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MECHANICALSURF: Mechanical waves make for radical relaxation time.
Increases Duplicant <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.\n\nSome <link=\"WATER\">Water</link> gets splashed on the floor during use.
This building will spill {amount} of its contents on to the floor during use, which must be replenished.
This building must be filled with {amount} {element} in order to function.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MEDICALCOT.DES: Duplicants use triage cots to recover from physical injuries and receive aid from peers.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MEDICALCOT.EFF: Accelerates <link=\"HEALTH\">Health</link> restoration and the healing of physical injuries.\n\nRevives incapacitated Duplicants.
An organic multi-cortex repository and processing system fuelled by <link="OXYGEN">Oxygen</link>.

Analyzes <link="DREAMJOURNAL">Dream Journals</link> produced by Duplicants wearing <link="SLEEPCLINICPAJAMAS">Pajamas</link>.

Provides a sustainable boost to Duplicant skills and abilities throughout the colony.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MERCURYCEILING: Mercury ceiling lights take a while to reach full brightness, but once they do...zowie!
Uses <link=\"MERCURY\">Mercury</link> and <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> to produce <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link>.\n\nLight reduces Duplicant stress and is required to grow certain plants.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MESHTILE.DESC: Mesh tile can be used to make Duplicant pathways in areas where liquid flows.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MESHTILE.EFFEC: Used to build the walls and floors of rooms.\n\nDoes not obstruct <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> or <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link> flow.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MESHTILE.NAME: <link=\"MESHTILE\">Mesh Tile</link>
Refined metals are necessary to build advanced electronics and technologies.

Produces <link="REFINEDMETAL">Refined Metals</link> from raw <link="RAWMETAL">Metal Ore</link>.

Significantly <link="HEAT">Heats</link> and outputs the <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link> piped into it.

Duplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.METALSCULPTURE: Duplicants who have learned art skills can produce more decorative sculptures.
Majorly increases <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link>, contributing to <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.\n\nMust be sculpted by a Duplicant.
It's quite lovely, until someone stubs their toe on it in the dark.
Not quite expressionist, but undeniably expressive.
It emits no light, but it sure does brighten up a room.
A masterful likeness of the mischievous critter that Duplicants love to love.
What if the entire head is one big bump?
Actually, it's a very good likeness.
The Morb's eye is mounted on a swivel that activates at random intervals.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.METALTILE.DESC: Heat travels much more quickly through metal tile than other types of flooring.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.METALTILE.EFFE: Used to build the walls and floors of rooms.\n\nSignificantly increases Duplicant runspeed.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.METALTILE.NAME: <link=\"METALTILE\">Metal Tile</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.METHANEGENERAT: Natural gas generators leak polluted water and are best built above a waste reservoir.
Converts <link=\"METHANE\">Natural Gas</link> into electrical <link=\"POWER\">Power</link>.\n\nProduces <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link> and <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Polluted Water</link>.
Musher recipes will keep Duplicants fed, but may impact health and morale over time.
Produces low quality <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link> using common ingredients.\n\nDuplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
Musher recipes will keep Duplicants fed, but may impact health and morale over time.
A colorful distraction from the actual quality of the food.
Hunger strikes are not an option, but color-coordination is.
Makes meals that are memorable for all the wrong reasons.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MILKFATSEPARAT: Duplicants can slather up with brackwax to increase their travel speed in transit tubes.
Refines <link=\"MILK\">Brackene</link> into <link=\"BRINE\">Brine</link> and <link=\"MILKFAT\">Brackwax</link>, and emits <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MILKFEEDER.DES: It's easier to tolerate overcrowding when you're all hopped up on brackene.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MILKFEEDER.EFF: Dispenses <link=\"MILK\">Brackene</link> to a wide variety of <link=\"CREATURES\">Critters</link>.\n\nAccessing the fountain significantly improves <link=\"CREATURES\">Critters</link>' moods.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MILKINGSTATION: The harvested liquid is basically the equivalent of soda for critters.

Allows Duplicants with the <link=\"RANCHING2\">Critter Ranching II</link> skill to milk <link=\"MOO\">Gassy Moos</link> for <link=\"MILK\">Brackene</link>.\n\n<link=\"MILK\">Brackene</link> can be used to refill the <link=\"MILKFEEDER\">Critter Fountain</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MILKPRESS.DESC: For Duplicants who are too squeamish to milk critters.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MILKPRESS.EFFE: Crushes organic materials to extract liquids such as <link=\"MILK\">Brackene</link> or <link=\"PHYTOOIL\">Phyto Oil</link>.\n\n<link=\"MILK\">Brackene</link> can be used to refill the <link=\"MILKFEEDER\">Critter Fountain</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MILKPRESS.NAME: <link=\"MILKPRESS\">Plant Pulverizer</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MILKPRESS.RESI: Converts {0} into {1}, {2}, and a small amount of {3}
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MINERALDEOXIDI: Oxygen diffusers are inefficient, but output enough oxygen to keep a colony breathing.
Converts large amounts of <link=\"ALGAE\">Algae</link> into <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link>.\n\nBecomes idle when the area reaches maximum pressure capacity.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MISSILEFABRICA: Blastshot shells are an effective defense against incoming meteor showers.

Produces <link=\"MISSILELAUNCHER\">Blastshot</link> from <link=\"REFINEDMETAL\">Refined Metals</link> combined with <link=\"PETROLEUM\">Petroleum</link>.\n\nDuplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MISSILELAUNCHE:
Fires <link="MISSILELAUNCHER">Blastshot</link> shells at meteor showers to defend the colony from impact-related damage.

Range: 16 tiles horizontally, 32 tiles vertically.

Meteors that have been blown to smithereens leave behind no harvestable resources.
Some meteors drop harvestable resources when they're blown to smithereens.

Fires explosive projectiles at incoming space objects to defend the colony from impact-related damage.

Projectiles must be crafted at a <link="MISSILEFABRICATOR">Blastshot Maker</link>.

Range: 16 tiles horizontally, 32 tiles vertically.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MISSILESETLOCK: A locker that once belonged to an explosives engineer.\n\nIt holds one <link=\"MISSILELAUNCHER\">Intracosmic Blastshot</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MISSIONCONTROL: Like a backseat driver who actually does know better.

Provides guidance data to rocket pilots, to improve rocket speed.

Must be operated by a Duplicant with the <link="ASTRONOMY">Astronomy</link> skill.

Requires a clear line of sight to space in order to function.
Like a backseat driver who actually does know better.

Provides guidance data to rocket pilots within range, to improve rocket speed.

Must be operated by a Duplicant with the <link="ASTRONOMY">Astronomy</link> skill.

Requires a clear line of sight to space in order to function.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MODULARGASINPU: A hub from which to input <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MODULARLAUNCHP: <link=\"MODULARLAUNCHPADPORTSOLID\">Rocket Port</link>
<link=\"MODULARLAUNCHPADPORTSOLID\">Rocket Ports</link>
Allows rocket platforms to be built farther apart.
Automatically links when built to the side of a <link=\"LAUNCHPAD\">Rocket Platform</link> or any <link=\"MODULARLAUNCHPADPORTSOLID\">Rocket Port</link>.
<link=\"MODULARLAUNCHPADPORTBRIDGE\">Rocket Port Extension</link>
Rockets must be landed to load or unload resources.

Loads <link="ELEMENTSGAS">Gases</link> to the storage of a linked rocket.

Automatically links when built to the side of a <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link> or another <link="MODULARLAUNCHPADPORTSOLID">Rocket Port</link>.

Uses the gas filters set on the rocket's cargo bays.
<link=\"MODULARLAUNCHPADPORTGAS\">Gas Rocket Port Loader</link>
Rockets must be landed to load or unload resources.

Unloads <link="ELEMENTSGAS">Gases</link> from the storage of a linked rocket.

Automatically links when built to the side of a <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link> or another <link="MODULARLAUNCHPADPORTSOLID">Rocket Port</link>.

Uses the gas filters set on this unloader.
<link=\"MODULARLAUNCHPADPORTGASUNLOADER\">Gas Rocket Port Unloader</link>
Rockets must be landed to load or unload resources.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MODULARLIQUIDI: A hub from which to input <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquids</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MODULARSOLIDIN: A hub from which to input <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solids</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MONUMENTBOTTOM: The base of a monument must be constructed first.

Builds the bottom section of a Great Monument.

Can be customized.

A Great Monument must be built to achieve the Colonize Imperative.
One knee tucked toward the other.
Atop a pair of conquered critters.
One must give the soul time to truly hatch.
In honor of the sugar engine.
Riding a carbon dioxide rocket engine to glory.
Atop a small petroleum rocket engine.
Atop a solo spacefarer rocket nosecone.
Atop a happy lil' Sweepy bot.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MONUMENTMIDDLE: Customized sections of a Great Monument can be mixed and matched.

Builds the middle section of a Great Monument.

Can be customized.

A Great Monument must be built to achieve the Colonize Imperative.
Makes the torso seem bigger and more intimidating than it is.
Sometimes things are good enough just as they are.
Hands hover slightly away from the body, as though raised in wonder.
Cradling a couple of smooth lil' critter babies.
An armful of chonky lil' critter babies.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MONUMENTTOP.DE: Building a Great Monument will declare to the universe that this hunk of rock is your own.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MONUMENTTOP.EF:
Builds the top section of a Great Monument.

Can be customized.

A Great Monument must be built to achieve the Colonize Imperative.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MONUMENTTOP.FA: A massive replica of Leira's smiling face.
A massive replica of Gossmann's determined gaze.
A massive replica of Nikola's post-explosion expression.
A massive replica of Burt's critter-spotting expression.
A massive replica of Rowan's serene smile.
A massive replica of Nisbet when she sees someone whose name she's forgotten.
A massive replica of Ashkan's fossil-discovering expression.
A massive replica of Ren's smoochy face.
A great-monument-sized Gassy Moo. Gassier and moo-ier than ever.
A great-monument-sized Plug Slug. Does not require a power source.
It has no mouth, but still looks like it's smiling.
A visual reminder about radiation safety.
A cautionary tale for careless Duplicants.
Excellent choice of decor for the entrance to highly radioactive site.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MORBROVERMAKER: Allows a skilled Duplicant to manufacture a steady supply of icky yet effective bots.

Uses <link=\"ZOMBIESPORES\">Zombie Spores</link> and <link=\"STEEL\">Steel</link> to craft biofueled machines that can be sent into hostile environments.\n\nDefunct <link=\"STORYTRAITMORBROVER\">Biobots</link> drop harvestable <link=\"STEEL\">Steel</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MOULDINGTILE.D: Trimming is used as purely decorative lining for walls and structures.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MOULDINGTILE.E: Used to build the walls and floors of rooms.\n\nIncreases <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link>, contributing to <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.MULTIMINIONDIN: Given the option, Duplicants prefer to dine with friends.
Gives three Duplicants a place to eat.\n\nSharing a meal with one or more companions provides a <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link> boost.
Every rocket requires a nosecone to fly.
Protects a rocket during takeoff and entry, enabling space travel.\n\nMust be built via <link=\"LAUNCHPAD\">Rocket Platform</link>, and built at the top of a rocket.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.NOSECONEHARVES: Collecting the drilled-out resources requires a storage module.

Enables a rocket to drill into interstellar debris to free up <link="ELEMENTSGAS">gas</link>, <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">liquid</link> and <link="ELEMENTSSOLID">solid</link> resources in space.

Engine must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>. 

Must be built at the top of a rocket with <link="ELEMENTSGAS">gas</link>, <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">liquid</link> or <link="ELEMENTSSOLID">solid</link> Cargo Module attached to store the appropriate resources.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.NUCLEARREACTOR: Radbolt generators and reflectors make radiation usable by other buildings.

Uses <link=\"ENRICHEDURANIUM\">Enriched Uranium</link> to produce <link=\"RADIATION\">Radiation</link> for Radbolt production.\n\nGenerates a massive amount of <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link>. Overheating will result in an explosive meltdown.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.NUCLEARRESEARC: Comes with a few ions thrown in, free of charge.

Conducts <link="RESEARCHDLC1">Materials Science Research</link> to unlock new technologies.

Consumes Radbolts.

Assigned Duplicants must possess the <link="ATOMICRESEARCH">Applied Sciences Research</link> skill.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OBJECTDISPENSE: Automatic dispensers will store and drop resources in small quantities.
Stores any Solid Materials delivered to it by Duplicants.\n\nDumps stored materials back into the world when it receives a Green Signal.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OILCHANGER.DES: A fresh supply of oil keeps the ol' joints from getting too creaky.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OILCHANGER.EFF: Uses <link=\"LUBRICATINGOIL\">Gear Oil</link> to keep Duplicants' bionic parts running smoothly.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OILREFINERY.DE: Petroleum can only be produced from the refinement of crude oil.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OILWELLCAP.DES: Water pumped into an oil reservoir cannot be recovered.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OILWELLCAP.EFF: Extracts <link=\"CRUDEOIL\">Crude Oil</link> using clean <link=\"WATER\">Water</link>.\n\nMust be built atop an <link=\"OILWELL\">Oil Reservoir</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ORBITALCARGOMO: It's a generally good idea to pack some supplies when exploring unknown worlds.
Delivers cargo to the surface of Planetoids that do not yet have a <link=\"LAUNCHPAD\">Rocket Platform</link>. \n\nMust be built via Rocket Platform.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ORBITALRESEARC: Orbital Data Collection Labs record data while orbiting a Planetoid and write it to a <link=\"ORBITALRESEARCHDATABANK\">Data Bank</link>.

Creates <link=\"ORBITALRESEARCHDATABANK\">Data Banks</link> that can be consumed at a <link=\"DLC1COSMICRESEARCHCENTER\">Virtual Planetarium</link> to unlock new technologies.\n\nConsumes <link=\"POLYPROPYLENE\">Plastic</link> and <link=\"POWER\">Power</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ORESCRUBBER.DE: Scrubbers sanitize freshly mined materials before they're brought into the colony.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ORESCRUBBER.EF: Kills a significant amount of <link=\"DISEASE\">Germs</link> present on <link=\"RAWMINERAL\">Raw Ore</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OUTHOUSE.DESC: The colony that eats together, excretes together.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OUTHOUSE.EFFEC:
Gives Duplicants a place to relieve themselves.

Requires no <link="LIQUIDPIPING">Piping</link>.

Must be periodically emptied of <link="TOXICSAND">Polluted Dirt</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OUTHOUSE.NAME: <link=\"OUTHOUSE\">Outhouse</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OXIDIZERTANK.D: Solid oxidizers allows rocket fuel to be efficiently burned in the vacuum of space.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OXIDIZERTANK.E: Stores <link=\"OXYROCK\">Oxylite</link> and other oxidizers for burning rocket fuels.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OXIDIZERTANKCL: Solid oxidizers allows rocket fuel to be efficiently burned in the vacuum of space.
Stores <link=\"OXYROCK\">Oxylite</link> and other oxidizers for burning rocket fuels.\n\nMust be built via <link=\"LAUNCHPAD\">Rocket Platform</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OXIDIZERTANKLI: Liquid oxygen improves the thrust-to-mass ratio of rocket fuels.
Stores <link=\"LIQUIDOXYGEN\">Liquid Oxygen</link> for burning rocket fuels.
Liquid oxygen improves the thrust-to-mass ratio of rocket fuels.
Stores <link=\"LIQUIDOXYGEN\">Liquid Oxygen</link> for burning rocket fuels. \n\nMust be built via <link=\"LAUNCHPAD\">Rocket Platform</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OXYGENMASKLOCK: An oxygen mask dock will store and refill masks while they're not in use.

Stores <link=\"OXYGENMASK\">Oxygen Masks</link> and refuels them with <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link>.\n\nBuild next to an <link=\"OXYGENMASKMARKER\">Oxygen Mask Checkpoint</link> to make Duplicants put on masks when passing by.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OXYGENMASKMARK: A checkpoint must have a correlating dock built on the opposite side its arrow faces.

Marks a threshold where Duplicants must put on or take off an <link="OXYGENMASK">Oxygen Mask</link>.

Must be built next to an <link="OXYGENMASKLOCKER">Oxygen Mask Dock</link>.

Can be rotated before construction.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OXYGENMASKSTAT: Duplicants can't pass by a station if it lacks enough oxygen to fill a mask.

Uses designated <link="METAL">Metal Ores</link> from filter settings to create <link="OXYGENMASK">Oxygen Masks</link>.

Automatically draws in ambient <link="OXYGEN">Oxygen</link> to fill masks.

Marks a threshold where Duplicants must put on or take off a mask.

Can be rotated before construction.

Synthesizes <link=\"OXYROCK\">Oxylite</link> using <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link> and a small amount of <link=\"GOLD\">Gold</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OXYSCONCE.DESC: Sconces prevent diffused oxygen from being wasted inside storage bins.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OXYSCONCE.EFFE: Stores a small chunk of <link=\"OXYROCK\">Oxylite</link> which gradually releases <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link> into the environment.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.OXYSCONCE.NAME: <link=\"OXYSCONCE\">Oxylite Sconce</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PARKSIGN.DESC: Passing through parks will increase Duplicant Morale.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PARKSIGN.EFFEC: Classifies an area as a Park or Nature Reserve.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PARKSIGN.NAME: <link=\"PARKSIGN\">Park Sign</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PARTYCAKE.DESC: Any way you slice it, that's a good looking cake.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PARTYCAKE.EFFE: Increases <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link>, contributing to <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.\n\nAdds a <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link> bonus to Duplicants' parties.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PARTYCAKE.NAME: <link=\"PARTYCAKE\">Triple Decker Cake</link>
It gives off an aroma that some Duplicants find inexplicably nostalgic.

Burns <link=\"PEAT\">Peat</link> to produce electrical <link=\"POWER\">Power</link>.\n\nProduces a small amount of <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link> and <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Polluted Water</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PETROLEUMGENER: Petroleum generators have a high energy output but produce a great deal of waste.

Converts <link=\"PETROLEUM\">Petroleum</link>, <link=\"ETHANOL\">Ethanol</link> or <link=\"REFINEDLIPID\">Biodiesel</link> into electrical <link=\"POWER\">Power</link>.\n\nProduces <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link> and <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Polluted Water</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PHONOBOX.DESC: Dancing helps Duplicants get their innermost feelings out.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PHONOBOX.EFFEC: Plays music for Duplicants to dance to on their breaks.\n\nIncreases Duplicant <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PHONOBOX.NAME: <link=\"PHONOBOX\">Jukebot</link>
Lands a Duplicant on a Planetoid from an orbiting <link=\"PIONEERMODULE\">Trailblazer Module</link>.
That's one small step for Dupekind.

Enables travel to Planetoids that do not yet have a <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>.

Can hold one Duplicant traveller.

Deployment is available while in a Starmap hex adjacent to a Planetoid. 

Must be built via Rocket Platform.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PIXELPACK.DESC: Four pixels which can be individually designated different colors.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PIXELPACK.EFFE: Pixels can be designated a color when it receives a Green Signal and a different color when it receives a Red Signal.\n\nInput from an Automation Wire controls the whole strip. Input from an Automation Ribbon can control individual pixels on the strip.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PIXELPACK.INPU: Green Signal: Display the configured Green Signal pixels
Red Signal: Display the configured Red Signal pixels
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PIXELPACK.NAME: <link=\"PIXELPACK\">Pixel Pack</link>
