STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PLANTERBOX.FAC: The interior is lined with tiny barbs.
Domestically grown seeds mature more quickly than wild plants.
It's not exactly a subtle color.
The thick paint drips are invisible from a distance.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PLASTICFLOWERS: Maintenance-free blooms that will outlive us all.
Manufactured by Home Staging Heroes Ltd. as commissioned by the Gravitas Facility, to \"Make Space Feel More Like Home.\"\n\nThis bouquet is designed to smell like freshly baked cookies.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PLASTICTILE.DE: Plastic tile is mildly antiseptic and can help limit the spread of germs in a colony.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PLASTICTILE.EF: Used to build the walls and floors of rooms.\n\nSignificantly increases Duplicant runspeed.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.POIBUNKEREXTER: A strong door with a sophisticated genetic lock.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.POIDLC2SHOWROO: Large double doors identical to those you might find at the main entrance to a large facility.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.POIDOORINTERNA: A strong door with a sophisticated genetic lock.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.POIFACILITYDOO: Large double doors that were once the main entrance to a large facility.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.POLYMERIZER.DE: Plastic can be used to craft unique buildings and goods.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.POWERCONTROLST: Only one Duplicant may be assigned to a station at a time.

Produces <link=\"POWERSTATIONTOOLS\">Microchip</link> to increase the <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> output of generators.\n\nAssigned Duplicants must possess the <link=\"TECHNICALS2\">Tune Up</link> trait.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.POWERTRANSFORM: It's a power transformer, but larger.

Limits <link="POWER">Power</link> flowing through the Transformer to 4 kW.

Connect <link="BATTERY">Batteries</link> on the large side to act as a valve and prevent <link="WIRE">Wires</link> from drawing more than 4 kW.

Can be rotated before construction.
Limiting the power drawn by wires prevents them from incurring overload damage.

Limits <link="POWER">Power</link> flowing through the Transformer to 1000 W.

Connect <link="BATTERY">Batteries</link> on the large side to act as a valve and prevent <link="WIRE">Wires</link> from drawing more than 1000 W.

Can be rotated before construction.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PRESSUREDOOR.D: Mechanized airlocks open and close more quickly than other types of door.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PRESSUREDOOR.E:
Blocks <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link> and <link="ELEMENTSGAS">Gas</link> flow, maintaining pressure between areas.

Functions as a <link="MANUALPRESSUREDOOR">Manual Airlock</link> when no <link="POWER">Power</link> is available.

Wild <link="CREATURES">Critters</link> cannot pass through doors.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PRESSURESWITCH: An atmo switch shuts off power when the air pressure surrounding it surpasses the set threshold.
Automatically turns <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> on or off using ambient <link=\"PRESSURE\">Gas Pressure</link> .\n\nDoes not affect circuitry preceding the switch.
A hydro switch shuts off power when the liquid pressure surrounding it surpasses the set threshold.

Automatically turns <link="POWER">Power</link> on or off using ambient <link="PRESSURE">Liquid Pressure</link>.

Does not affect circuitry preceding the switch.

Must be submerged in <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPCERESPOSTE: A poster promoting a local tourist attraction.\n\nActual scenery may vary.
A poster promoting local wildlife.\n\nThe first in an unfinished series.
A sound-absorbing panel that makes small-space living more bearable.\n\nThe artwork features a  power source.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPCLOCK.DESC: A simple wall clock.\n\nIt is no longer ticking.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPCLOCK.NAME: Clock
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPCLOTHESHAN: Holds one <link=\"WARMVEST\">Warm Coat</link>.\n\nIt'd be silly not to use it.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPDESK.DESC: An intact office desk, decorated with several personal belongings and a barely functioning computer.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPDESK.NAME: Computer Desk
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPDLC2DISPLA: An electronic display projecting the blueprint of an engineering project.\n\nIt looks like a pump of some kind.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPDLC2GEOTHE: Maintenance equipment that once flushed debris out of complex mechanisms.\n\nOne of the wheels is squeaky.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPELEVATOR.D: Out of service.\n\nThe buttons inside indicate it went down more than a dozen floors at one point in time.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPEXOSETLOCK: A locker made with ultra-lightweight textiles.\n\nIt contains an assortment of personal effects.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPEXOSHELFLO: A shelf made out of flat-packed pieces that can be assembled in various ways.\n\nThis is the long way.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPEXOSHELSHO: A shelf made out of flat-packed pieces that can be assembled in various ways.\n\nIt looks nice, actually.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPFACILITYCH: A chair where visitors can comfortably wait before their appointments.
A large chandelier that hangs from the ceiling.\n\nIt does not appear to function.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPFACILITYCO: A couch where visitors can comfortably wait before their appointments.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPFACILITYDE:
A spotless desk filled with impeccably organized office supplies.

A photo peeks out from beneath the desk pad, depicting two beaming young women in caps and gowns.

The photo is quite old.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPFACILITYDI: An electronic display projecting the blueprint of a familiar device.\n\nIt looks like a Printing Pod.
An electronic display projecting the blueprint of a familiar device.\n\nIt looks like a Mining Gun.
An electronic display projecting the blueprint of a strange device.\n\nPerhaps these displays were used to entice visitors.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPFACILITYGL: A filing cabinet for storing hard copy employee records.\n\nThe contents have been shredded.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPFACILITYLA: A long light fixture that hangs from the ceiling.\n\nIt does not appear to function.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPFACILITYPA: A painting featuring a copse of fir trees and a magnificent mountain range on the horizon.\n\nThe air in the room prickles with the sensation that I'm not meant to be here.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPFACILITYST: A large, modern sculpture that sits in the center of the lobby.\n\nIt's an artistic cross between an hourglass shape and a double helix.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPFACILITYTA: A low coffee table that may have once held old science magazines.
It's survived the vacuum of space by virtue of being plastic.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPFACILITYWA: Certification in Applied Physics, awarded in recognition of one \"Jacquelyn A. Stern\".
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASBA: A one-way mirror and shelf.\n\nThe skincare products still smell faintly of shea butter.
A handwashing station that looks suspiciously under-utilized.\n\nIt was once part of a bulk office order.
It holds one roll of sanitary paper.\n\nThe sheets are single-ply.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASCE: A flush mount ceiling light that no longer functions.\n\nThere's dust inside.
Non-functioning robotic arms that once assisted lab technicians.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASCL: A square wall clock.\n\nIt's quite damaged.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASCR: An anatomical illustration of the very first <link=\"HATCH\">Hatch</link> ever produced.\n\nWhile the ratio of egg sac to brain may appear outlandish, it is in fact to scale.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASDE: A tall, thin window which once pointed to a courtyard.
The unkempt workspace of a long-departed scientist who expected to return.
A clutter-proof desk to minimize distractions.\n\nThere appears to be something stored in the computer.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASDI: An electronic display projecting the blueprint of a robotic device.\n\nIt looks like a ceiling robot.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASFI: Essential lab equipment.\n\nThe inspection tag indicates it has long expired.
It looks like it's been used a lot.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASFL: An outdated phone left behind by a distracted lab technician.\n\nIt doesn't work.
The grasping robotic claw designed to assist technicians in a lab.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASFR: A non-functional cold storage unit full of expired samples.\n\nIt was originally someone's home appliance.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASHA: A sophisticated security device.\n\nIt appears to use a method other than fingerprints to verify an individual's identity.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASJA: An abnormally large brain floating in embalming liquid to prevent decomposition.
The corpse of a proto-hatch creature meticulously preserved in a jar.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASLA: The quaint research desk of a departed lab technician.\n\nPerhaps the computer stores something of interest.
A regular wall that once existed in a working lab.
A lab window. Formerly a portal to the outside world.
A lab window.\n\nSomeone once stared out of this, contemplating the results of an experiment.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASPA: It once dispensed paper made from 100% post-consumer recycled content.\n\nThe remaining sheet is jammed.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASPO: A handy reference text with illustrations.\n\nIt details the genetic makeup of proprietary botanicals.
A handy reference text with illustrations.\n\nIt compares the genetic makeup of select organisms.
A very dead plant.\n\nIt's a wonder it hasn't crumbled into nothingness.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASRO: The work space of an extinct robotics technician who left behind some unfinished prototypes.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASSH: A shelf holding jars just out of reach for a short person.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASSM: A small glass cabinet.\n\nThere's a biohazard symbol on it.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASTO: A packing crate intended for safety equipment.\n\nIt has been repurposed for tool storage.
A wall-mounted rack for storing and displaying useful tools at a not-so-useful height.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASTR: A wall-mounted garbage receptacle.\n\nThe lid does not close.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPGRAVITASWA: The wall of a once-great scientific facility.
The wall of an ambitious research and development department.
The wall of an ambitious research and development department.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPHUMANCHEST: A luxurious chair where future generations can comfortably sit and dream of home.
A luxurious couch where potential residents can comfortably nap and dream of home.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPHUMANMURPH: A bed that folds into the wall, for small live/work spaces.\n\nThis is the display model.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPLIGHT.DESC: An elegant ceiling lamp, slightly worse for wear.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPLIGHT.NAME: Light Fixture
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPRECEPTIOND: A full coffee cup and a note abandoned mid sentence sit behind the desk.\n\nIt gives me an eerie feeling, as if the receptionist has stepped out and will return any moment.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPSKELETON.D: A detailed anatomical model.\n\nIt appears to be made of resin.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPSURFACESAT: All that remains of a once peacefully orbiting satellite.
All that remains of a once peacefully orbiting satellite.
All that remains of a once peacefully orbiting satellite.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.PROPTABLE.NAME: Table
Looking closely, it appears to be fake.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RADIATIONLIGHT: Duplicants can become sick if exposed to radiation without protection.
Emits <link=\"RADIATION\">Radiation</link> when <link=\"POWER\">Powered</link> that can be collected by a <link=\"HIGHENERGYPARTICLESPAWNER\">Radbolt Generator</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RAILGUN.DESC: It's tempting to climb inside but trust me... don't.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RAILGUN.EFFECT:
Launches <link="RAILGUNPAYLOAD">Interplanetary Payloads</link> between Planetoids.

Payloads can contain <link="ELEMENTSSOLID">Solid</link>, <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link>, or <link="ELEMENTSGAS">Gas</link> materials.

Cannot transport Duplicants.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RAILGUN.NAME: <link=\"RAILGUN\">Interplanetary Launcher</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RAILGUNPAYLOAD: Payload openers can be hooked up to conveyors, plumbing and ventilation for improved sorting.

Unpacks <link=\"RAILGUNPAYLOAD\">Interplanetary Payloads</link> delivered by Duplicants.\n\nAutomatically separates <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link>, <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link>, and <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link> materials and distributes them to the appropriate systems.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RANCHSTATION.D: A groomed critter is a happy, healthy, productive critter.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RANCHSTATION.E: Allows the assigned <link=\"RANCHER\">Rancher</link> to care for <link=\"CREATURES\">Critters</link>.\n\nAssigned Duplicants must possess the <link=\"RANCHING1\">Critter Ranching</link> skill.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RATIONBOX.DESC: Ration boxes keep food safe from hungry critters, but don't slow food spoilage.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RATIONBOX.EFFE: Stores a small amount of <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.\n\nFood must be delivered to boxes by Duplicants.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RATIONBOX.NAME: <link=\"RATIONBOX\">Ration Box</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.REFRIGERATOR.D: Food spoilage can be slowed by ambient conditions as well as by refrigerators.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.REFRIGERATOR.E: Stores <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link> at an ideal <link=\"HEAT\">Temperature</link> to prevent spoilage.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.REFRIGERATOR.F: For food so cold, it brings a tear to the eye.
Food spoilage can be slowed by ambient conditions as well as by refrigerators.
Honestly, this hue is particularly chilling.
This fridge makes color-coordination a (cold) snap.
Inspired by the Duplicant poem, \"Pretty in Puce.\"
Bold on the outside, cold on the inside!
Some Duplicants call it \"sunny\" yellow, but only because they've never seen the sun.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.REMOTEWORKERDO: <link=\"REMOTEWORKERDOCK\">Remote Worker Docks</link> deploy automatons that operate machinery based on instructions received from a connected <link=\"REMOTEWORKTERMINAL\">Remote Controller</link>.\n\nMust be placed within range of its target building.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.REMOTEWORKTERM: Remote controllers cut down on colony commute times.
Enables Duplicants to operate machinery remotely via a connected <link=\"REMOTEWORKERDOCK\">Remote Worker Dock</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RESEARCHCENTER: Research stations are necessary for unlocking all research tiers.
Conducts <link=\"RESEARCH\">Novice Research</link> to unlock new technologies.\n\nConsumes <link=\"DIRT\">Dirt</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RESEARCHCLUSTE: Unlocks the possibility of Gathering Databanks floating in space
The Research module allows the rocket to gather Data banks that happen to be on the same hex cell than the rocket when it travels through the galaxy
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RESEARCHMODULE: Data banks can be used at virtual planetariums to produce additional research.

Completes one <link="RESEARCH">Research Task</link> per space mission.

Produces a small Data Bank regardless of mission destination.

Generated <link="RESEARCH">Research Points</link> become available upon the rocket's return.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RESETSKILLSSTA: Erase skills from a Duplicant's mind, returning them to their default abilities.
Refunds a Duplicant's Skill Points for reassignment.\n\nDuplicants will lose all assigned skills in the process.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.REUSABLETRAP.L: Sends a Green Signal when a critter has been trapped
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROBOPILOTCOMMA: Robo-pilot modules do not require a Duplicant astronaut.
Enables rockets to travel swiftly and safely without a <link=\"COMMANDMODULE\">Command Capsule</link>.\n\nA Robo-Pilot Capsule must be the last module installed at the top of a rocket.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROBOPILOTMODUL: Robo-pilot modules do not require a Duplicant astronaut.
Enables rockets to travel swfitly without a <link=\"ROCKETCONTROLSTATION\">Rocket Control Station</link>.\n\nMust be built via <link=\"LAUNCHPAD\">Rocket Platform</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROCKCRUSHER.DE: Rock Crushers loosen nuggets from raw ore and can process many different resources.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROCKCRUSHER.EF: Inefficiently produces refined materials from raw resources.\n\nDuplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROCKCRUSHER.FA: Wherever there's raw ore, there's a rock crusher lurking nearby.
Buffs rough ore into smooth little nuggets.
Rock Crushers loosen nuggets from raw ore and can process many different resources.
Uncrushed ore really grinds its gears.
Inspired by the traditional mortar and pestle.
Not designed to handle overcooked food waste.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROCKCRUSHER.LI: Crushes {0} into {1} and a small amount of pure {2}
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROCKCRUSHER.RE: Crushes {0} into {1} and {2}, and a small amount of {3}
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROCKETCOMMANDC: Allows a Duplicant to pilot a rocket.\n\nCargo rockets must possess a Rocket Cockpit in order to function.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROCKETCONTROLS: Someone needs to be around to jiggle the controls when the screensaver comes on.
Allows Duplicants to use pilot-operated rockets and control access to interior buildings.\n\nAssigned Duplicants must have the <link=\"ROCKETPILOTING1\">Rocket Piloting</link> skill.
Green Signal: Restrict access to interior buildings
Red Signal: Unrestrict access to interior buildings
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROCKETENVELOPE: I can see my asteroid from here!
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROCKETINTERIOR: It's basically central-vac.

Allows <link="ELEMENTSGAS">Gases</link> to be pumped into rocket storage via <link="GASCONDUIT">Pipes</link>.

Sends gas to the first Rocket Module with available space.

Must be built within the interior of a Rocket Module.
<link=\"ROCKETINTERIORGASINPUT\">Gas Intake Fitting</link>
A direct attachment leading to the output port on the exterior of the rocket.
Allows a direct conduit connection out of the <link=\"HABITATMODULEMEDIUM\">Spacefarer Module</link> of the rocket.\nCan be used to vent <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gasses</link> to space during flight.
<link=\"ROCKETINTERIORGASINPUTPORT\">Gas Spacefarer Input Port</link>
Refreshing breezes, on-demand.

Allows <link="ELEMENTSGAS">Gases</link> to be drawn from rocket storage via <link="GASCONDUIT">Pipes</link>.

Draws gas from the first Rocket Module with the requested material.

Must be built within the interior of a Rocket Module.
<link=\"ROCKETINTERIORGASOUTPUT\">Gas Output Fitting</link>
A direct attachment to the input port on the exterior of a rocket.
Allows a direct conduit connection into the <link=\"HABITATMODULEMEDIUM\">Spacefarer Module</link> of a rocket.
<link=\"ROCKETINTERIORGASOUTPUTPORT\">Gas Spacefarer Output Port</link>
Begone, foul waters!

Allows <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquids</link> to be pumped into rocket storage via <link="LIQUIDCONDUIT">Pipes</link>.

Sends liquid to the first Rocket Module with available space.

Must be built within the interior of a Rocket Module.
<link=\"ROCKETINTERIORLIQUIDINPUT\">Liquid Intake Fitting</link>
A direct attachment to the output port on the exterior of a rocket.
Allows a direct conduit connection out of the <link=\"HABITATMODULEMEDIUM\">Spacefarer Module</link> of a rocket.\nCan be used to vent <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquids</link> to space during flight.
<link=\"ROCKETINTERIORLIQUIDINPUTPORT\">Liquid Spacefarer Input Port</link>
Now if only we had some water balloons...

Allows <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquids</link> to be drawn from rocket storage via <link="LIQUIDCONDUIT">Pipes</link>.

Draws liquid from the first Rocket Module with the requested material.

Must be built within the interior of a Rocket Module.
<link=\"ROCKETINTERIORLIQUIDOUTPUT\">Liquid Output Fitting</link>
A direct attachment to the input port on the exterior of a rocket.
Allows a direct conduit connection into the <link=\"HABITATMODULEMEDIUM\">Spacefarer Module</link> of a rocket.
<link=\"ROCKETINTERIORLIQUIDOUTPUTPORT\">Liquid Spacefarer Output Port</link>
Outlets conveniently power buildings inside a cockpit using their rocket's power stores.

Provides <link="POWER">Power</link> to connected buildings.

Pulls power from <link="BATTERYMODULE">Battery Modules</link> and Rocket Engines.

Must be built within the interior of a Rocket Module.
<link=\"ROCKETINTERIORPOWERPLUG\">Power Outlet Fitting</link>
Why organize your shelves when you can just shove everything in here?

Allows <link="ELEMENTSSOLID">Solid Materials</link> to be moved into rocket storage via <link="SOLIDCONDUIT">Conveyor Rails</link>.

Sends solid material to the first Rocket Module with available space.

Must be built within the interior of a Rocket Module.
<link=\"ROCKETINTERIORSOLIDINPUT\">Conveyor Receptacle Fitting</link>
For accessing your stored luggage mid-flight.

Allows <link="ELEMENTSSOLID">Solid Materials</link> to be moved out of rocket storage via <link="SOLIDCONDUIT">Conveyor Rails</link>.

Draws solid material from the first Rocket Module with the requested material.

Must be built within the interior of a Rocket Module.
<link=\"ROCKETINTERIORSOLIDOUTPUT\">Conveyor Loader Fitting</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROCKETPOD.DESC: The Duplicant inside is equal parts nervous and excited.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROCKETPOD.EFFE: Contains a Duplicant deployed from orbit by a <link=\"PIONEERMODULE\">Trailblazer Module</link>.\n\nPod will disintegrate on arrival.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROCKETPOD.NAME: <link=\"ROCKETPOD\">Trailblazer Deploy Pod</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROLESTATION.DE: A skills board can teach special skills to Duplicants they can't learn on their own.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.ROLESTATION.EF: Allows Duplicants to spend Skill Points to learn new <link=\"JOBS\">Skills</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.RUSTDEOXIDIZER: Rust and salt goes in, oxygen comes out.
Converts <link=\"RUST\">Rust</link> into <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link> and <link=\"CHLORINE\">Chlorine Gas</link>.\n\nBecomes idle when the area reaches maximum pressure capacity.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SAUNA.DESC: A steamy sauna soothes away all the aches and pains.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SAUNA.EFFECT: Uses <link=\"STEAM\">Steam</link> to create a relaxing atmosphere.\n\nIncreases Duplicant <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link> and provides a lingering sense of warmth.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SAUNA.NAME: <link=\"SAUNA\">Sauna</link>
Allows Duplicants to boldly go where other Duplicants haven't been yet.
Automatically analyzes adjacent space while on a voyage. \n\nMust be built via <link=\"LAUNCHPAD\">Rocket Platform</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SCOUTLANDER.DE: Lands <link=\"SCOUT\">Rover</link> on a Planetoid when <link=\"SCOUTMODULE\">Rover's Module</link> is in orbit.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SCOUTMODULE.DE: Rover can conduct explorations of planetoids that don't have rocket platforms built.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SCOUTMODULE.EF:
Deploys one <link="SCOUT">Rover Bot</link> for remote Planetoid exploration.

Deployment is available while in a Starmap hex adjacent to a Planetoid. 

Must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SCOUTROCKETPOD: Contains a <link=\"SCOUT\">Rover</link> deployed from an orbiting <link=\"SCOUTMODULE\">Rover's Module</link>.\n\nPod will disintegrate on arrival.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SCULPTURE.DESC: Duplicants who have learned art skills can produce more decorative sculptures.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SCULPTURE.EFFE: Moderately increases <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link>, contributing to <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.\n\nMust be sculpted by a Duplicant.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SCULPTURE.FACA: A masterful portrayal of a scientist lost in thought.
A masterful portrayal of an athlete who's been banned from the communal kitchen.
A masterful portrayal of a slingshot-wielding hero.
A masterful portrayal of a gentle, plant-tending critter.
No amount of material success will ever fill the void within.
Ode to the bow and arrow, love's equivalent to a mining gun...but for hearts.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SCULPTURE.NAME: <link=\"SCULPTURE\">Large Sculpting Block</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SETLOCKER.DESC: A basic metal locker.\n\nIt contains an assortment of personal effects.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SETLOCKER.NAME: Locker
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SHEARINGSTATIO: Those critters aren't gonna shear themselves.

Shearing stations allow eligible <link=\"CREATURES\">Critters</link> to be safely sheared for useful raw materials.\n\nVisiting this building restores <link=\"CREATURES\">Critters'</link> physical and emotional well-being.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SHELF.DESC: It looks great even when it's empty.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SHELF.EFFECT: Displays cherished items and increases <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link>, contributing to <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.\n\nMust be installed on a back wall.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SHELF.NAME: <link=\"SHELF\">Display Shelf</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SHOWER.DESC: Regularly showering will prevent Duplicants spreading germs to the things they touch.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SHOWER.NAME: <link=\"SHOWER\">Shower</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SINGLEPLAYERAR: Space Brawler IV! For one player.
Allows a Duplicant to play video games solo on their breaks.\n\nIncreases Duplicant <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SLUDGEPRESS.DE: What Duplicant doesn't love playing with mud?
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SLUDGEPRESS.EF: Separates <link=\"MUD\">Mud</link> and other sludges into their base elements.\n\nDuplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SMALLELECTROBA: A small standalone power center that can be mounted on the floor or wall.
Converts stored energy from <link=\"ELECTROBANK\">Power Banks</link> into power for connected buildings.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SMALLOXIDIZERT: Solid oxidizers allows rocket fuel to be efficiently burned in the vacuum of space.
Stores <link=\"FERTILIZER\">Fertilizer</link> and <link=\"OXYROCK\">Oxylite</link> for burning rocket fuels. \n\nMust be built via <link=\"LAUNCHPAD\">Rocket Platform</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SMALLSCULPTURE: Duplicants who have learned art skills can produce more decorative sculptures.
Minorly increases <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link>, contributing to <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.\n\nMust be sculpted by a Duplicant.
A masterful celebration of the Sweepy's unbeatable work ethic and cheerful, can-clean attitude.
A three-dimensional rebellion against the rules of Euclidean space.
Tribute to the artist's friend, who once attempted to catch a meteor with their bare hands.
It must be a moon, because there are no bananas in space.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SMARTRESERVOIR: Sends a Green Signal when reservoir is less than {0}% full, until it is {1}% (High Threshold) full
Sends a Red Signal when reservoir is {0}% full, until it is less than {1}% (Low Threshold) full
Sends a Green Signal when reservoir is less than Low Threshold full, until High Threshold is reached again
Sends a Red Signal when reservoir is High Threshold full, until Low Threshold is reached again
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SMOKER.DESC: With a little patience, even tough meat can become deliciously edible.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SMOKER.EFFECT: Cooks improved <link=\"FOOD\">foods</link> over low, slow heat.\n\nDuplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SMOKER.NAME: <link=\"SMOKER\">Smoker</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SNOWTILE.DESC: Snow tiles have low thermal conductivity, but will melt if temperatures get too high.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SNOWTILE.EFFEC: Used to build the walls and floors of rooms.\n\nInsulates rooms to reduce <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link> loss in cold climates.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SNOWTILE.NAME: <link=\"SNOWTILE\">Snow Tile</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SODAFOUNTAIN.D: Sparkling water puts a twinkle in a Duplicant's eye.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SODAFOUNTAIN.E: Creates soda from <link=\"WATER\">Water</link> and <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link>.\n\nConsuming soda water increases Duplicant <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLARPANEL.DES: Solar panels convert high intensity sunlight into power and produce zero waste.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLARPANEL.EFF: Converts <link=\"LIGHT\">Sunlight</link> into electrical <link=\"POWER\">Power</link>.\n\nMust be exposed to space.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLARPANELMODU: Collect solar energy before takeoff and during flight.

Converts <link="LIGHT">Sunlight</link> into electrical <link="POWER">Power</link> for use on rockets.

Must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>. 

Must be exposed to space.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDBOOSTER.D: Additional thrusters allow rockets to reach far away space destinations.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDBOOSTER.E: Burns <link=\"IRON\">Iron</link> and <link=\"OXYROCK\">Oxylite</link> to increase rocket exploration distance.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDCARGOBAYS: Duplicants will fill cargo bays with any resources they find during space missions.

Allows Duplicants to store some of the <link="ELEMENTSSOLID">Solid Materials</link> found during space missions.

Stored resources become available to the colony upon the rocket's return. 

Must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDCONDUIT.D: Rails move materials where they'll be needed most, saving Duplicants the walk.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDCONDUIT.E: Transports <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid Materials</link> on a track between <link=\"SOLIDCONDUITINBOX\">Conveyor Loader</link> and <link=\"SOLIDCONDUITOUTBOX\">Conveyor Receptacle</link>.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDCONDUITBR: Separating rail systems helps ensure materials go to the intended destinations.
Runs one <link=\"SOLIDCONDUIT\">Conveyor Rail</link> section over another without joining them.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDCONDUITDI: Germ sensors can help control automation behavior in the presence of germs.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal based on the internal Germ count of the object on the rail.
Sends a Green Signal if the number of Germs on the object on the rail is within the selected range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDCONDUITEL: Element sensors can be used to detect the presence of a specific item on a rail.
Sends a Green Signal when the selected item is detected on a rail.
Sends a Green Signal if the configured item is detected on the rail
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDCONDUITIN: Material filters can be used to determine what resources are sent down the rail.
Loads <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid Materials</link> onto <link=\"SOLIDCONDUIT\">Conveyor Rail</link> for transport.\n\nOnly loads the resources of your choosing.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDCONDUITOU: When materials reach the end of a rail they enter a receptacle to be used by Duplicants.
Unloads <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid Materials</link> from a <link=\"SOLIDCONDUIT\">Conveyor Rail</link> into storage.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDCONDUITTE: Thermo sensors disable buildings when their rail contents reach a certain temperature.
Sends a Green Signal or a Red Signal when rail contents enter the chosen Temperature range.
Sends a Green Signal if the contained item is within the selected Temperature range
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDFILTER.DE: All solids are sent into the building's output conveyor, except the solid chosen for filtering.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDFILTER.EF: Separates one <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid Material</link> from the conveyor, sending it into a dedicated <link=\"SOLIDCONDUIT\">Conveyor Rail</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDLIMITVALV: Conveyor Meters let an exact amount of materials pass through before shutting off.
Connects to an <link=\"LOGIC\">Automation</link> grid to automatically turn material transfer off when the specified amount has passed through it.
Sends a Green Signal if limit has been reached
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDLOGICVALV: Automated conveyors save power and time by removing the need for Duplicant input.
Connects to an <link=\"LOGIC\">Automation</link> grid to automatically turn <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid Material</link> transport on or off.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDTRANSFERA: An auto-sweeper's range can be viewed at any time by (ClickType/clicking) on the building.

Automates <link=\"CHORES\">Sweeping</link> and <link=\"CHORES\">Supplying</link> errands by sucking up all nearby <link=\"DECOR\">Debris</link>.\n\nMaterials are automatically delivered to any <link=\"SOLIDCONDUITINBOX\">Conveyor Loader</link>, <link=\"SOLIDCONDUITOUTBOX\">Conveyor Receptacle</link>, storage, or buildings within range.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDVENT.DESC: When materials reach the end of a rail they are dropped back into the world.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDVENT.EFFE: Unloads <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid Materials</link> from a <link=\"SOLIDCONDUIT\">Conveyor Rail</link> onto the floor.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SOLIDVENT.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDVENT\">Conveyor Chute</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SPACEHEATER.DE: Space heaters are a welcome cure for cold, soggy feet.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SPACEHEATER.EF: Radiates a moderate amount of <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link>.\n\nRequires <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> in order to function.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SPECIALCARGOBA: Biological cargo bays allow Duplicants to retrieve alien plants and wildlife from space.
Allows Duplicants to store unusual or organic resources found during space missions.\n\nStored resources become available to the colony upon the rocket's return.
Critters do not require feeding during transit.

Allows Duplicants to transport <link="CREATURES">Critters</link> through space.

Specimens can be released into the colony upon the rocket's return.

Must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SPICEGRINDER.D: Crushed seeds and other edibles make excellent meal-enhancing additives.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SPICEGRINDER.E: Produces ingredients that add benefits to <link=\"FOOD\">foods</link> prepared at skilled cooking stations.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.STATERPILLAREG: The electrifying egg of the <link=\"STATERPILLAR\">Plug Slug</link>.
Slug Eggs can be connected to a <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> circuit as an energy source.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.STEAMENGINE.DE: Rockets can be used to send Duplicants into space and retrieve rare resources.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.STEAMENGINE.EF: Utilizes <link=\"STEAM\">Steam</link> to propel rockets for space exploration.\n\nThe engine of a rocket must be built first before more rocket modules may be added.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.STEAMENGINECLU: Rockets can be used to send Duplicants into space and retrieve rare resources.

Utilizes <link="STEAM">Steam</link> to propel rockets for space exploration.

Engine must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>. 

Once the engine has been built, more rocket modules can be added.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.STEAMTURBINE.D: Useful for converting the geothermal energy of magma into usable power.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.STEAMTURBINE.E:
THIS BUILDING HAS BEEN DEPRECATED AND CANNOT BE BUILT.

Generates exceptional electrical <link="POWER">Power</link> using pressurized, <link="HEAT">Scalding</link> <link="STEAM">Steam</link>.

Outputs significantly cooler <link="STEAM">Steam</link> than it receives.

Air pressure beneath this building must be higher than pressure above for air to flow.
Useful for converting the geothermal energy into usable power.
Draws in <link=\"STEAM\">Steam</link> from the tiles directly below the machine's foundation and uses it to generate electrical <link=\"POWER\">Power</link>.\n\nOutputs <link=\"WATER\">Water</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.STICKERBOMB.DE: Surprise decor sneak attacks a Duplicant's gloomy day.
Resources left on the floor become \"debris\" and lower decor when not put away.
Stores the <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid Materials</link> of your choosing.
Color-coded storage makes things easier to find.
<link=\"STORAGELOCKER\">Weepy Blue Storage Bin</link>
Resources left on the floor become \"debris\" and lower decor when not put away.
<link=\"STORAGELOCKER\">Storage Bin</link>
Color-coded storage makes things easier to find.
<link=\"STORAGELOCKER\">Mush Green Storage Bin</link>
A fun storage solution for fun-damental materials.
<link=\"STORAGELOCKER\">Party Dot Storage Bin</link>
Groovy storage, because messy colonies are such a drag.
<link=\"STORAGELOCKER\">Mod Dot Storage Bin</link>
Color-coded storage makes things easier to find.
<link=\"STORAGELOCKER\">Faint Purple Storage Bin</link>
Color-coded storage makes things easier to find.
<link=\"STORAGELOCKER\">Puce Pink Storage Bin</link>
It's the merriest storage bin of all.
Bold Stripe Storage Bin
Color-coded storage makes things easier to find.
<link=\"STORAGELOCKER\">Ick Yellow Storage Bin</link>
<link=\"STORAGELOCKER\">Storage Bin</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.STORAGELOCKERS: Smart storage bins can automate resource organization based on type and mass.
Stores the Solid Materials of your choosing.\n\nSends a Green Signal when bin is full.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.STORAGETILE.DE: Storage tiles keep selected non-edible solids out of the way.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.STORAGETILE.EF: Used to build the walls and floors of rooms.\n\nProvides built-in storage for small spaces.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SUBLIMATIONSTA: Sublimation is the sublime process by which solids convert directly into gas.
Speeds up the conversion of <link=\"TOXICSAND\">Polluted Dirt</link> into <link=\"CONTAMINATEDOXYGEN\">Polluted Oxygen</link>.\n\nBecomes idle when the area reaches maximum pressure capacity.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SUGARENGINE.DE: Not the most stylish way to travel space, but certainly the tastiest.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SUGARENGINE.EF:
Burns <link="SUCROSE">Sucrose</link> to propel rockets for short range space exploration.

Sugar Engines have higher height restrictions than <link="CO2ENGINE">Carbon Dioxide Engines</link>, but move slower.

Engine must be built via <link="LAUNCHPAD">Rocket Platform</link>, and requires a <link="OXIDIZERTANKCLUSTER">Large Solid Oxidizer Tank</link>. 

Once the engine has been built, more rocket modules can be added.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SUITFABRICATOR: Exosuits can be filled with oxygen to allow Duplicants to safely enter hazardous areas.
Forges protective <link=\"EQUIPMENT\">Exosuits</link> for Duplicants to wear.\n\nDuplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SUITLOCKER.DES: An atmo suit dock will empty atmo suits of waste, but only one suit can charge at a time.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SUITLOCKER.EFF:
Stores <link="ATMOSUIT">Atmo Suits</link> and refuels them with <link="OXYGEN">Oxygen</link>.

Empties suits of <link="DIRTYWATER">Polluted Water</link>.

Build next to an <link="SUITMARKER">Atmo Suit Checkpoint</link> to make Duplicants change into suits when passing by.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SUITMARKER.DES: A checkpoint must have a correlating dock built on the opposite side its arrow faces.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SUITMARKER.EFF:
Marks a threshold where Duplicants must change into or out of <link="ATMOSUIT">Atmo Suits</link>.

Must be built next to an <link="SUITLOCKER">Atmo Suit Dock</link>.

Can be rotated before construction.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SUNLAMP.EFFECT: Gives off <link=\"LIGHT\">Sunlight</link> level Lux.\n\nCan be paired with <link=\"BEACHCHAIR\">Beach Chairs</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SUNLAMP.NAME: <link=\"SUNLAMP\">Sun Lamp</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SUPERMATERIALR: Rare materials can be procured through rocket missions into space.

Processes <link="RAREMATERIALS">Rare Materials</link> into advanced industrial goods.

Rare materials can be retrieved from space missions.

Duplicants will not fabricate items unless recipes are queued.
Fullerene is a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid Material</link> used in the production of <link=\"SUPERCOOLANT\">Super Coolant</link>.
Plastium is a highly heat-resistant, plastic-like <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid Material</link> used for space buildings.
Atomic Power Banks are portable, self-charging units used for isolated <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> grids.
Super Coolant is an industrial-grade <link=\"FULLERENE\">Fullerene</link> coolant.
Insulite reduces <link=\"HEAT\">Heat Transfer</link> and is composed of recrystallized <link=\"KATAIRITE\">Abyssalite</link>.
Thermium is an industrial metal alloy formulated to maximize <link=\"HEAT\">Heat Transfer</link> and thermal dispersion.
Visco-Gel Fluid is a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> polymer with high surface tension.
Yellowcake is a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid Material</link> used in uranium enrichment.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SWEEPBOTSTATIO: The cute little face comes pre-installed.

Deploys an automated <link="SWEEPBOT">Sweepy Bot</link> to sweep up <link="ELEMENTSSOLID">Solid</link> debris and <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link> spills.

Dock stores <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquids</link> and <link="ELEMENTSSOLID">Solids</link> gathered by the Sweepy.

Uses <link="POWER">Power</link> to recharge the Sweepy.

Duplicants will empty Dock storage into available storage bins.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SWITCH.DESC: Switches can only affect buildings that come after them on a circuit.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SWITCH.EFFECT: Turns <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> on or off.\n\nDoes not affect circuitry preceding the switch.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.SWITCH.NAME: <link=\"SWITCH\">Switch</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TELEPHONE.DESC: You never know who you'll meet on the other line.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TELEPHONE.EFFE: Can be used by one Duplicant to chat with themselves or with other Duplicants in different locations.\n\nChatting increases Duplicant <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.
Duplicants will gain {amount} {attrib} if they chat only with themselves.
Duplicants will gain {amount} {attrib} if they chat with at least one other Duplicant.
Duplicants will gain {amount} {attrib} if they chat with at least one other Duplicant across space.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TELEPHONE.NAME: <link=\"TELEPHONE\">Party Line Phone</link>
Duplicants are just atoms as far as the pad's concerned.
Instantly transports Duplicants and items to another portal with the same portal code.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TELESCOPE.DESC: Telescopes are necessary for learning starmaps and conducting rocket missions.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TELESCOPE.EFFE:
Maps Starmap destinations, producing <link="DATABANK">Data Banks</link> in the process.

Assigned Duplicants must possess the <link="RESEARCHING2">Field Research</link> skill.

Building must be exposed to space to function.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TELESCOPE.NAME: <link=\"TELESCOPE\">Telescope</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TELESCOPE.REQU: A steady {0} supply is required to sustain working Duplicants.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TEMPERATURECON: Automated switches can be used to manage circuits in areas where Duplicants cannot enter.
Automatically turns <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> on or off using ambient <link=\"HEAT\">Temperature</link>.\n\nDoes not affect circuitry preceding the switch.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TEMPORALTEAROP: Infinite possibilities, with a complimentary side of meteor showers.
A powerful mechanism capable of tearing through the fabric of reality.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.THERMALBLOCK.D: The thermal properties of construction materials determine their heat retention.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.THERMALBLOCK.E: Accelerates or buffers <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link> dispersal based on the construction material used.\n\nHas a small area of effect.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TILE.DESC: Tile can be used to bridge gaps and get to unreachable areas.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TILE.EFFECT: Used to build the walls and floors of rooms.\n\nIncreases Duplicant runspeed.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TILE.NAME: <link=\"TILE\">Tile</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TILEPOI.EFFECT: Used to build the walls and floor of rooms.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TILEPOI.NAME: <link=\"TILEPOI\">Tile</link>
An astronaut must accompany sight seeing Duplicants on rocket flights.
Allows one non-Astronaut Duplicant to visit space.\n\nSight-Seeing Rocket flights decrease <link=\"STRESS\">Stress</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TRAVELTUBE.DES: Duplicants will only exit a transit tube when a safe landing area is available beneath it.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TRAVELTUBE.EFF: Quickly transports Duplicants from a <link=\"TRAVELTUBEENTRANCE\">Transit Tube Access</link> to the tube's end.\n\nOnly transports Duplicants.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TRAVELTUBEENTR: Duplicants require access points to enter tubes, but not to exit them.
Allows Duplicants to enter the connected <link=\"TRAVELTUBE\">Transit Tube</link> system.\n\nStops drawing <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> once fully charged.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.TRAVELTUBEWALL: Tube crossings can run transit tubes through walls without leaking gas or liquid.
Allows <link=\"TRAVELTUBE\">Transit Tubes</link> to be run through wall and floor tile.\n\nFunctions as regular tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.UNCONSTRUCTEDR: Something useful could be put here someday
Can be changed into a different rocket module
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.UNDERWATERCRIT: Even wild critters are happier after they've had a little R&R.
A fancy respite area for adult <link=\"CRABSPECIES\">Pokeshells</link> and <link=\"PACUSPECIES\">Pacu</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.URANIUMCENTRIF: Enriched uranium is a specialized substance that can be used to fuel powerful research reactors.
Extracts <link=\"ENRICHEDURANIUM\">Enriched Uranium</link> from <link=\"URANIUMORE\">Uranium Ore</link>.\n\nOutputs <link=\"DEPLETEDURANIUM\">Depleted Uranium</link> in molten form.
Convert Uranium ore to Molten Uranium and Enriched Uranium
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.VERTICALWINDTU: Duplicants love the feeling of high-powered wind through their hair.
This building will displace {amount} Gas while in use.
Must be connected to a <link=\"POWER\">Power Source</link>. To properly function, the area under this building must be left vacant.\n\nIncreases Duplicants <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WALLTOILET.DES: Wall Toilets transmit fewer germs to Duplicants and require no emptying.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WALLTOILET.EFF: Gives Duplicants a place to relieve themselves. Empties directly on the other side of the wall.\n\nSpreads very few <link=\"DISEASE\">Germs</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WARPCONDUITREC: The tubes at the back disappear into nowhere.

A machine capable of teleporting <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link>, <link="ELEMENTSSOLID">Solid</link>, and <link="ELEMENTSGAS">Gas</link> resources to another asteroid.

It can be activated by a Duplicant with the <link="RESEARCHING2">Field Research</link> skill.

This is the receiving side.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WARPCONDUITSEN: The tubes at the back disappear into nowhere.

A machine capable of teleporting <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link>, <link="ELEMENTSSOLID">Solid</link>, and <link="ELEMENTSGAS">Gas</link> resources to another asteroid.

It can be activated by a Duplicant with the <link="RESEARCHING2">Field Research</link> skill.

This is the transmitting side.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WARPPORTAL.DES: The functional remnants of an intricate teleportation system.\n\nThis is the outgoing side, and has one pre-programmed destination.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WARPRECEIVER.D: The functional remnants of an intricate teleportation system.\n\nThis is the incoming side.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WASHBASIN.DESC: Germ spread can be reduced by building these where Duplicants often get dirty.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WASHBASIN.EFFE: Removes some <link=\"DISEASE\">Germs</link> from Duplicants.\n\nGerm-covered Duplicants use Wash Basins when passing by in the selected direction.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WASHBASIN.NAME: <link=\"WASHBASIN\">Wash Basin</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WASHSINK.DESC: Sinks are plumbed and do not need to be manually emptied or refilled.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WASHSINK.EFFEC: Removes <link=\"DISEASE\">Germs</link> from Duplicants.\n\nGerm-covered Duplicants use Sinks when passing by in the selected direction.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WASHSINK.FACAD: A calm, colorful sink for heavy-hearted Duplicants.
Sinks are plumbed and do not need to be manually emptied or refilled.
A refreshing splash of color for the light-headed.
Some Duplicants say it looks like a germ-devouring mouth.
The juxtaposition of 'ick' and 'clean' can be very satisfying.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WASHSINK.NAME: <link=\"WASHSINK\">Sink</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WATERCOOLER.DE: Chatting with friends improves Duplicants' moods and reduces their stress.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WATERCOOLER.EF: Provides a gathering place for Duplicants during Downtime.\n\nImproves Duplicant <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WATERCOOLER.FA: Ideal for post-Mush Bar palate cleansing.
Most Duplicants agree that it really should dispense juice.
Rose-colored paper cups: the shatter-proof alternative to rose-colored glasses.
It really classes up a breakroom.
Did someone boil eggs in this water?
Sieves cannot kill germs and pass any they receive into their waste and water output.
Produces clean <link=\"WATER\">Water</link> from <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Polluted Water</link> using <link=\"SAND\">Sand</link>.\n\nProduces <link=\"TOXICSAND\">Polluted Dirt</link>.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WATERTRAP.DESC: Trapped fish will automatically be bagged for transport.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WATERTRAP.EFFE: Attracts and traps swimming <link=\"PACU\">Pacu</link>.\n\nOnly Duplicants with the <link=\"RANCHING1\">Critter Ranching I</link> skill can arm this trap. It's reusable!
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WATERTRAP.NAME: <link=\"WATERTRAP\">Fish Trap</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WIRE.DESC: Electrical wire is used to connect generators, batteries, and buildings.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WIRE.EFFECT: Connects buildings to <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> sources.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WIRE.NAME: <link=\"WIRE\">Wire</link>
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WIREBRIDGE.DES: Splitting generators onto separate grids can prevent overloads and wasted electricity.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WIREBRIDGE.EFF: Runs one wire section over another without joining them.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WIREBRIDGEHIGH: Joint plates can run Heavi-Watt wires through walls without leaking gas or liquid.
Allows <link=\"HIGHWATTAGEWIRE\">Heavi-Watt Wire</link> to be run through wall and floor tile.\n\nFunctions as regular tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WIREREFINED.DE: My Duplicants prefer the look of conductive wire to the regular raggedy stuff.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WIREREFINED.EF: Connects buildings to <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> sources.\n\nCan be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WIREREFINEDBRI: Splitting generators onto separate systems can prevent overloads and wasted electricity.

Carries more <link="POWER">Wattage</link> than a regular <link="WIREBRIDGE">Wire Bridge</link> without overloading.

STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WIREREFINEDHIG: Higher wattage wire is used to avoid power overloads, particularly for strong generators.
Carries more <link=\"POWER\">Wattage</link> than regular <link=\"WIRE\">Wire</link> without overloading.\n\nCannot be run through wall and floor tile.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WOODENDOOR.DES: A breezy wooden door combines style and function.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WOODENDOOR.EFF: Encloses areas without blocking <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> or <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link> flow.\n\nWild <link=\"CREATURES\">Critters</link> cannot pass through doors.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WOODGASGENERAT: Wood burners are small and easy to maintain, but produce a fair amount of heat.
Burns <link=\"WOOD\">Wood</link> to produce electrical <link=\"POWER\">Power</link>.\n\nProduces <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link> and <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link>.
A great fit for smaller spaces.
Moderately increases <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link>, contributing to <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.\n\nMust be sculpted by a Duplicant.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WOODSTORAGE.DE: Once it's empty, there's no use pining for more.
STRINGS.BUILDINGS.PREFABS.WOODSTORAGE.EF: Stores a finite supply of <link=\"WOOD\">Wood</link>, which can be used for construction or to produce <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link>.

STRINGS.CODEX.A0_PRELIMINARYCALCULATIONS:
<indent=5%>Director,

Even with dramatic optimization, we can't fit the massive volume of resources needed for a colony seed aboard the craft. Not even when calculating for a very small interplanetary travel duration.

Some serious changes are gonna have to be made for this to work.</indent>
STRINGS.CODEX.A0_PROPFACILITYDISPLAY1.BO:
Introducing the latest in 3D printing technology:
The Gravitas Home Printing Pod

We are proud to announce that printing advancements developed here in the Gravitas Facility will soon bring new, bio-organic production capabilities to your old home printers.

What does that mean for the average household?

Dinner frustrations are a thing of the past. Simply select any of the pod's 5398 pre-programmed recipes, and voila! Delicious pot roast ready in only .87 seconds.

Prefer the patented family recipe? Program your own custom meal template for an instant taste of home, or go old school and create fresh, delicious ingredients and prepare your own home cooked meal.

Dinnertime has never been easier!
\nProjected for commercial availability early next year.\nBrought to you by the Gravitas Facility.
STRINGS.CODEX.A0_PROPFACILITYDISPLAY2.BO:
Bring your mining operations into the twenty-third century with new Gravitas personal excavators.

Improved particle condensers reduce raw volume for more efficient product shipping - and that's good for your bottom line.

Licensed for industrial use only, resale of Gravitas equipment may carry a fine of up to $200,000 under the Global Restoration Act.
Brought to you by the Gravitas Facility.
STRINGS.CODEX.A0_PROPFACILITYDISPLAY3.BO:
Tired of shutting down during seasonal heat waves? Looking to cut weather-related operating costs?

Look no further: Gravitas's revolutionary Anti Entropy Thermo-Nullifier is the exciting, affordable new way to eliminate operational downtime.

Powered by our proprietary renewable power sources, the AETN efficiently cools an entire office building without incurring any of the environmental surcharges associated with comparable systems.

Initial setup includes hydrogen duct installation and discounted monthly maintenance visits from our elite team of specially trained contractors.

Now available for pre-order!
Brought to you by the Gravitas Facility.\n<smallcaps>Patent Pending</smallcaps>
STRINGS.CODEX.A1A_B111.BODY.CONTAINER1:
I sent Dr. Holland home today after I found him wandering the lab mumbling to himself. He looked like he hadn't slept in days!

I worry that everyone here is so afraid of disappointing ‘The Director' that they are pushing themselves to the breaking point. Next chance I get, I'm going to bring this up with Jackie.
------------------
STRINGS.CODEX.A1A_B111.BODY.CONTAINER2:
Well, that didn't work.

Bringing up the need for some office bonding activities with the Director only met with her usual stubborn insistence that we "don't have time for any fun".

This is ridiculous. Tomorrow I'm going to organize something fun for everyone and Jackie will just have to deal with it. She just needs to see the long term benefits of short term stress relief to fully understand the importance of this.
------------------
STRINGS.CODEX.A1A_B111.BODY.CONTAINER3:
I can't believe this! I organized a potluck lunch thinking it would be a nice break but Jackie discovered us as we were setting up and insisted that no one had time for "fooling around". Of course, everyone was too afraid to defy 'The Director' and went right back to work.

All the food was just thrown out. Someone had even brought homemade perogies! Seeing the break room garbage full of potato salad and chicken wings made me even more depressed than before. Those perogies looked so good.
------------------
STRINGS.CODEX.A1A_B111.BODY.CONTAINER4:
I keep finding senseless mistakes from stressed-out lab workers. It's getting dangerous. I'm worried this colony we're building will be plagued with these kinds of problems if we don't prioritize mental health as much as physical health. What's the use of making all these plans for the future if we can't build a better world?

Maybe there's some way I can sneak some prerequisite downtime activities into the Printing Pod without Jackie knowing.
------------------
STRINGS.CODEX.A1A_B111.SUBTITLE: ENCRYPTION LEVEL: THREE
STRINGS.CODEX.A1A_B111.TITLE: Personal Journal: B111
STRINGS.CODEX.A1_A046.BODY.CONTAINER1: Gravitas has been growing pretty rapidly since our first product hit the market. I just got a look at some of the new hires - they're practically babies! Not quite what I was expecting, but then I've never had an opportunity to mentor someone before. Could be fun!\n------------------\n
STRINGS.CODEX.A1_A046.BODY.CONTAINER2: Well, mentorship hasn't gone quite how I'd expected. Turns out the young hires don't need me to show them the ropes. Actually, since the facility's gotten rid of our swipe cards one of the nice young men had to show me how to operate the doors after I got stuck outside my own lab. Don't I feel silly.\n------------------\n
STRINGS.CODEX.A1_A046.BODY.CONTAINER3:
Well, if that isn't just gravy, hm? One of the new hires will be acting as the team lead on my next project.

When I first started it wasn't that uncommon to sample a whole rack of test tubes by hand. Now a machine can do hundreds of them in seconds. Who knows what this job will look like in another ten or twenty years. Will I still even be in it?
------------------
STRINGS.CODEX.A1_A046.BODY.CONTAINER4: That nice young man who helped me with the door the other day, Mr. Kraus, has been an absolute angel. He's been kind enough to help me with this horrible e-mail system and even showed me how to digitize my research notes. I'm learning a lot. Turns out I wasn't the mentor, I'm the mentee! If that isn't a chuckle. At any rate, I feel like I have a better handle on things around here due to Mr. Kraus' help. Turns out you're never too old to learn something new!\n------------------\n

STRINGS.CODEX.A2_B327.BODY.CONTAINER1: I'm starting my new job at Gravitas today. I'm... well, I'm nervous. It turns out they hired a bunch of new people - I guess they're expanding - and most of them are about my age, but I'm the only one that hasn't done my doctorate. They all call me "Mister" Kraus and it's the worst. I have no idea where I'll find the time to do my PhD while working a full time job. ------------------
STRINGS.CODEX.A2_B327.BODY.CONTAINER2: I screwed up so much today. At one point I spaced on the formula for calculating the volume of a cone. They must have thought I was completely useless. The only time I knew what I was doing was when I helped an older coworker figure out her dumb old email. People say education isn't so important as long as you've got the skills, but there's things my colleagues know that I just don't. They're not mean about it or anything, it's just so frustrating. I feel dumb when I talk to them! I bet they're gonna realize soon that I don't belong here, and then I'll be fired for sure. Man... I'm still paying off my student loans (WITH international fees), I can't lose this income. ------------------
STRINGS.CODEX.A2_B327.BODY.CONTAINER3:
Dr. Sklodowska's been really nice and welcoming since I started working here. Sometimes she comes and sits with me in the cafeteria. The food she brings from home smells like old feet but she chats with me about what new research papers we're each reading and it's very kind.

She tells me the fact I got hired without a doctorate means I must be very smart, and management must see something in me.

I'm not sure I believe her but it's nice to hear something that counters little voice in my head anyway.
------------------
STRINGS.CODEX.A2_B327.BODY.CONTAINER4:
It's been about a week and a half and I think I'm finally starting to settle in. I'm feeling a lot better about my position - some of the senior scientists have even started using my ideas in the lab.

Dr. Sklodowska might have been right, my anxiety was just growing pains. This is my first real job and I guess afraid to let myself believe I could really, actually do it, just in case it went wrong.

I think I want to buy Dr. Sklowdoska a digital reader for her books and papers as a thank-you one day, if I ever pay off my student loans.

ONCE I pay off my student loans.
------------------

STRINGS.CODEX.A2_BACTERIALCULTURES.TITLE: Unattended Cultures
Hello Mr. Kraus! I was just e-mailing you after our little chat today to pass along something you might like to read - I think you'll find it super useful in your research!
FIRST LAW\nEnergy can neither be created or destroyed, only change forms.
SECOND LAW\nEntropy in an isolated system that is not in equilibrium tends to increase over time, approaching the maximum value at equilibrium.
THIRD LAW\nEntropy in a system approaches a constant minimum as temperature approaches absolute zero.
ZEROTH LAW\nIf two thermodynamic systems are in thermal equilibrium with a third, then they are in thermal equilibrium with each other.
\nIf this is too complicated for you, you can come by to chat. I'd be thrilled to answer your questions. ;)

XOXO,
Dr. Jones
<size=11>Information and Statistics Department
The Gravitas Facility</size>
------------------

STRINGS.CODEX.A3_B556.BODY.CONTAINER1:
I've been so tired lately. I've probably spent the last 3 nights sleeping at my desk, and I've used the lab's safety shower to bathe twice already this month.

We're technically on schedule, but for some reason Director Stern has been breathing down my neck to get these new products ready for market.

Normally I'd be mad about the added pressure on my work, but something in the Director's voice tells me that time is of the essence.
------------------
STRINGS.CODEX.A3_B556.BODY.CONTAINER2:
I keep finding myself staring at my computer screen, totally unable to remember what it was I was doing.

I try to force myself to type up some notes or analyze my data but it's like my brain is paralyzed, I can't get anything done.

I'll have to stay late to make up for all this time I've wasted staying late.
------------------
STRINGS.CODEX.A3_B556.BODY.CONTAINER3:
Dr. Broussard told me I looked half dead and sent me home today. I don't think she even has the authority to do that, but I did as I was told. She wasn't messing around if you know what I mean.

I can probably get a head start on my paper from home today, anyway.

I think I have an idea for a circuit configuration that will improve the battery life of all our technologies by a whole 2.3%.
------------------
STRINGS.CODEX.A3_B556.BODY.CONTAINER4: I got home yesterday fully intending to work on my paper after Broussard sent me home, but the second I walked in the door I hit the pillow and didn't get back up. I slept for 12 straight hours. I had no idea I needed that. When I got into the lab this morning I looked over my work from the past few weeks, and realized it's completely useless. It'll take me hours to correct all the mistakes I made these past few months. Is this what I was killing myself for? I'm such a rube, I owe Broussard a huge thanks. I'll start keeping more regular hours from now on... Also, I was considering maybe getting a dog.

STRINGS.CODEX.A4_B835.BODY.CONTAINER1: I started work at a new company called the \"Gravitas Facility\" today! I was nervous I wouldn't get the job at first because I was fresh out of school, and I was so so so pushy in the interview, but the Director apparently liked my thesis on the physiological thermal regulation of Arctic lizards. I'll be working with some brilliant geneticists, bioengineering organisms for space travel in harsh environments! It's like a dream come true. I get to work on exciting new research in a place where no one knows me!\n------------------\n
STRINGS.CODEX.A4_B835.BODY.CONTAINER2: No no no no no! It can't be! BANHI ANSARI is here, working on space shuttle thrusters in the robotics lab! As soon as she saw me she called me \"Bubbles\" and told everyone about the time I accidentally inhaled a bunch of fungal spores during lab, blew a big snot bubble out my nose and then sneezed all over Professor Avery! Everyone's calling me \"Bubbles\" instead of \"Doctor\" at work now. Some of them don't even know it's a nickname, but I don't want to correct them and seem rude or anything. Ugh, I can't believe that story followed me here! BANHI RUINS EVERYTHING!\n------------------\n
STRINGS.CODEX.A4_B835.BODY.CONTAINER3: I've spent the last few days buried in my work, and I'm actually feeling a lot better. We finally perfected a gene manipulation that controls heat sensitivity in rats. Our test subjects barely even shiver in subzero temperatures now. We'll probably do a testrun tomorrow with Robotics to see how the rats fare in the prototype shuttles we're developing.\n------------------\n
STRINGS.CODEX.A4_B835.BODY.CONTAINER4: HAHAHAHAHA! Bioengineering and Robotics did the test run today and Banhi was securing the live cargo pods when one of the rats squeaked at her. She was so scared, she fell on her butt and TOOTED in front of EVERYONE! They're all calling her \"Pipsqueak\". \"Bubbles\" doesn't seem quite so bad now. Pipsqueak's been a really good sport about it though, she even laughed it off at the time. I think we might actually be friends now? It's weird.\n------------------\n
STRINGS.CODEX.A4_B835.BODY.CONTAINER5: I lied. Me and Banhi aren't friends - we're BEST FRIENDS. She even showed me how she does her hair. We're gonna book the wind tunnel after work and run experiments together on thermo-rat rockets! Haha!\n------------------\n

STRINGS.CODEX.A4_HIBISCUS3.BODY.CONTAINE:
Hypothesis: Subjects cloned from Hibiscus will correctly operate a lever apparatus when introduced, demonstrating retention of original donor's conditioned memories.

Donor subject #650, "Hibiscus", conditioned to pull a lever to the right for a reward (almonds). Conditioning took place over a period of two weeks.

Hibiscus quickly learned that pulling the lever to the left produced no results, and was reliably demonstrating the desired behavior by the end of the first week.

Training continued for one additional week to strengthen neural pathways and ensure the intended behavioral conditioning was committed to long term and muscle memory.

Cloning subject #762, "Hibiscus-3", was introduced to the lever apparatus to ascertain memory retention and recall.

Hibiscus-3 showed no signs of recognition and did not perform the desired behavior. Subject initially failed to interact with the apparatus on any level.

On second introduction, Hibiscus-3 pulled the lever to the left.

Conclusion: Printed subject retains no memory from donor.

STRINGS.CODEX.A6_MEMORYIMPLANTATION.BODY:
[LOG BEGINS]

Traditionally, cloning produces a subject that is genetically identical to the donor but develops independently, producing a being that is, in its own way, unique.

The pod, conversely, attempts to print an exact atomic copy. Theoretically all neural pathways should be intact and identical to the original subject.

It's fascinating, given this, that memories are not already inherent in our subjects; however, no cloned subjects as of yet have shown any signs of recognition when introduced to familiar stimuli, such as the donor subject's enclosure.

Refer to Experiment 7D.

Refer to Experiment 7F.

Memories must be embedded within the physical brainmaps of our subjects. The only question that remains is how to activate them. Hormones? Chemical supplements? Situational triggers? The Director seems eager to move past this problem, and I am concerned at her willingness to bypass essential stages of the research development process. We cannot move on to the fine polish of printing systems until the core processes have been perfected - which they have not. Dr. Broussard, signing off. [LOG ENDS]
STRINGS.CODEX.A6_NEWSECURITY2.BODY.CONTA:

The folks in engineering say the door device doesn't look like a fingerprint scanner, but the duo working over in bioengineering won't comment at all.

I can't say I like it.</indent>

STRINGS.CODEX.A7_EMPLOYEEPROCESSING.BODY:
<smallcaps>[Voice Recognition Initialized]
[Subjects Identified: A001, A435, B111]</smallcaps>

[LOG BEGINS]

Technician: Thank you for the fingerprints, doctor. We just need a quick voice sample, then you can be on your way.

Dr. Broussard: Wow Jackie, your new security's no joke.

Director: Please address me as "Director" while on Facility grounds.

Dr. Broussard: ...R-right.

(clicking)

Technician: This should only take a moment. Speak clearly and the system will derive a vocal signature for you.

Technician: When you're ready.

(throat clearing)

Dr. Broussard: Security code B111, Dr. Olivia Broussard. Gravitas Facility Bioengineering Department.

(pause)

Technician: Great.

Dr. Broussard: What was that light just now?

Director: A basic security scan. No need for concern.

(machine printing)

Technician: Here's your ID. You should have access to all doors in the facility now, Dr. Broussard.

Dr. Broussard: Thank you.

Director: Come along, Doctor.

[LOG ENDS]
STRINGS.CODEX.A7_NEUTRONIUM.BODY.CONTAIN:
[LOG BEGINS]

Director: I've determined the substance to be metallic in nature. The exact cause of its formation is still unknown, though I believe it to be something of an autoimmune reaction of the natural universe, a quarantining of foreign material to prevent temporal contamination.

Director: A method has yet to be found that can successfully remove the substance from an affected object, and the larger implication that two molecularly, temporally identical objects cannot coexist at one point in time has dire implications for all time manipulation technology research, not just the Bow.

Director: For the moment I have dubbed the substance "Neutronium", and assigned it a theoretical place on the table of elements. Research continues.

[LOG ENDS]

STRINGS.CODEX.A8_FIRSTSUCCESS.BODY.CONTA:
We've successfully compressed and expanded small portions of time under .03 milliseconds. This proves that time is something that can be physically acted upon, suggesting that our vision is attainable.

An unintentional consequence of both the expansion and contraction of time is the creation of a "vacuum" in the space between the affected portion of time and the much more expansive unaffected portions.

So far, we are seeing that the unaffected time on either side of the manipulated portion will expand or contract to fill the vacuum, although we are unsure how far-reaching this consequence is or what effect it has on the laws of the natural universe. At the end of all compression and expansion experiments, alterations to time are undone and leave no lasting change.

STRINGS.CODEX.A8_FIRSTSUCCESS.TITLE: Encouraging Results
STRINGS.CODEX.A8_NEWSECURITY3.BODY.CONTA:
<indent=5%>I'm almost certain now that the Facility's stolen our genetic information.

Forty-odd employees would make for mighty convenient lab rats, and even if we discovered what Gravitas did, we wouldn't have a lot of legal options. We can't exactly go to the public given the nature of our work.

I can't stop thinking about what sort of experiments they might be conducting on my DNA, but I have to keep my mouth shut.

I can't risk losing my job.</indent>

Arbor Trees have been cultivated to spread horizontally when they grow so as to produce a high yield of lumber in vertically cramped spaces.

Arbor Trees are related to the oak tree, specifically the Japanese Evergreen, though they have been genetically hybridized significantly.

Despite having many hardy, evenly spaced branches, the short stature of the Arbor Tree makes climbing it rather irrelevant.

STRINGS.CODEX.AUTOMATION.PARAGRAPH_1:
Automation is a tool for controlling the operation of buildings based on what sensors in the colony are detecting.

A <link="CEILINGLIGHT">Ceiling Light</link> could be configured to automatically turn on when a <link="LOGICDUPLICANTSENSOR">Duplicant Motion Sensor</link> detects a Duplicant in the room.

A <link="LIQUIDPUMP">Liquid Pump</link> might activate only when a <link="LOGICELEMENTSENSORLIQUID">Liquid Element Sensor</link> detects water.

A <link="AIRCONDITIONER">Thermo Regulator</link> might activate only when the <link="LOGICTEMPERATURESENSOR">Thermo Sensor</link> detects too much heat.
STRINGS.CODEX.AUTOMATION.PARAGRAPH_2: In addition to an <link=\"WIRE\">electrical wire</link>, most powered buildings can also have an <link=\"LOGICWIRE\">Automation Wire</link> connected to them. This wire can signal the building to turn on or off. If the other end of a <link=\"LOGICWIRE\">Automation Wire</link> is connected to a sensor, the building will turn on and off as the sensor outputs signals.\n\n
STRINGS.CODEX.AUTOMATION.PARAGRAPH_3: There are two signals that an <link=\"LOGICWIRE\">Automation Wire</link> can send: Green and Red. The green signal will usually cause buildings to turn on, and the red signal will usually cause buildings to turn off. Sensors can often be configured to send their green signal only under certain conditions. A <link=\"LOGICTEMPERATURESENSOR\">Thermo Sensor</link> could be configured to only send a green signal if detecting temperatures greater than a chosen value.\n\n
STRINGS.CODEX.AUTOMATION.PARAGRAPH_4:
The signals of sensor wires can be combined using special buildings called "Gates" in order to create complex activation conditions.
The <link="LOGICGATEAND">AND Gate</link> can have two automation wires connected to its input slots, and one connected to its output slots. It will send a "Green" signal to its output slot only if it is receiving a "Green" signal from both its input slots. This could be used to activate a building only when multiple sensors are detecting something.
STRINGS.CODEX.AUTOMATION.TITLE: <link=\"LOGIC\">Automation</link>
STRINGS.CODEX.B10_AI.BODY.CONTAINER1: [Voice Recognition Initialized] [Subject Identified: B111-1] [LOG BEGINS] I made a horrible discovery today while reviewing work on the artificial intelligence programming. It seems Dr. Ali mixed up a file when uploading a program onto a rudimentary robot and discovered that the device displayed the characteristics of what he called "a puppy that was lost in a teleportation experiment weeks ago". This is unbelievable! Jackie has been hiding the nature of the teleportation experiments from me. What's worse is I know from previous conversations that she knows I would never approve of pursuing this line of experimentation. The societal benefits of teleportation aside, you cannot kill a living being every time you want to send them to another room. The moral and ethical implications of this are horrendous. I know she has been keeping this information from me. When I searched through the Gravitas database I found nothing to do with these teleportation experiments. It was only because this reference showed up in Dr. Ali's AI paper that I was able to discover what has been happening. Jackie has to be stopped. But I know she is beyond reasonable discussion. I hope this is the only thing she is hiding from me, but I fear it is not. [LOG ENDS] [LOG BEGINS] Despite myself, I can't help thinking of the intriguing possiblities this presents for the AI development. It haunts me. I fear I may be sliding down a slippery slope, at the bottom of which Jackie is waiting for me with open arms. [LOG ENDS]

<indent=%5>From the time she was old enough to walk Captain Johannsen dreamed of reaching the sky. Growing up on an air force base she came to love the sound jet engines roaring overhead. At 16 she became the youngest pilot ever to fly a fighter jet, and at 22 she had already entered the space flight program.

Four years later Gravitas nabbed her for an exclusive contract piloting our space shuttles. In her time at Gravitas, Captain Johannsen has logged over 1,000 hours space flight time shuttling and deploying satellites to Low Earth Orbits and has just been named the pilot of our inaugural civilian space tourist program, slated to begin in the next year.

Gravitas is excited to have Captain Johannsen in the pilot seat as we reach for the stars...and beyond!</indent>

STRINGS.CODEX.B6_TIMEMUSINGS.BODY.CONTAI:
When we discuss Time as a concrete aspect of the universe, not seconds on a clock or perceptions of the mind, it is important first of all to establish that we are talking about a unique dimension that layers into the three physical dimensions of space: length, width, depth.

We conceive of Real Time as a straight line, one dimensional, uncurved and stretching forward infinitely. This is referred to as the "Arrow of Time".

Logically this Arrow can move only forward and can never be reversed, as such a reversal would break the natural laws of the universe. Effect would precede cause and universal entropy would be undone in a blatant violation of the Second Law.

Still, one can't help but wonder; what if the Arrow's trajectory could be curved? What if it could be redirected, guided, or loosed? What if we could create Time's Bow?

STRINGS.CODEX.B8_MAGAZINEARTICLE.BODY.CO: Incredible Technology From Independent Lab Harnesses Time into Energy

Scientists from the recently founded Gravitas Facility have unveiled their first technology prototype, dubbed the "Temporal Bow". It is a device which manipulates the 4th dimension to generate infinite, clean and renewable energy.

While it may sound like something from science fiction, facility founder Dr. Jacquelyn Stern confirms that it is very much real.

"It has already been demonstrated that Newton's Second Law of Motion can be violated by negative mass superfluids under the correct lab conditions," she says.

"If the Laws of Motion can be bent and altered, why not the Laws of Thermodynamics? That was the main intent behind this project."

The Temporal Bow works by rapidly vibrating sections of the 4th dimension to send small quantities of mass forward and backward in time, generating massive amounts of energy with virtually no waste.

"The fantastic thing about using the 4th dimension as fuel," says Stern, "is that it is really, categorically infinite".

For those eagerly awaiting the prospect of human time travel, don't get your hopes up just yet. The Facility says that although they have successfully transported matter through time, the technology was expressly developed for the purpose of energy generation and is ill-equipped for human transportation.
