STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.EGGHUG.TOOLT: This egg was recently hugged by an affectionate critter\n\nIncreased <style=\"KKeyword\">Incubation Rate</style>
This prey critter recently evaded a predator\n\nWhew!
STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.GLUM.NAME: Mood: Glum
STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.GLUM.TOOLTIP: This critter's feeling down because its needs aren't being met\n\nIt will produce less materials as a result
STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.GOLDBELLYWEL: This critter's recent meal is boosting their <style=\"KKeyword\">Regal Bammoth Crest</style> growth
STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.GOTMILK.NAME: Hydrated
STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.GOTMILK.TOOL: This critter recently drank <style=\"KKeyword\">Brackene</style>\n\nIt doesn't mind overcrowding quite as much right now
STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.HAPPY_TAME.T: This critter's in high spirits because its needs are being exceeded\n\nIt will lay more eggs as a result
STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.HAPPY_WILD.T: This critter's in high spirits because its needs are being exceeded

STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.HUSKYMOOWELL: This critter's recent meal is boosting their <style=\"KKeyword\">Biodiesel</style> supply
STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.ICEBELLYWELL: This critter's recent meal is boosting their fur growth

STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.MOOWELLFED.T: This critter's recent meal is boosting their <style=\"KKeyword\">Brackene</style> supply and making them wish all their friends were here\n\nThey're thinking about calling a new Moo to this asteroid

STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.RANCHED.TOOL: This critter has recently been attended to by a kind Duplicant\n\nDuplicants must possess the <style=\"KKeyword\">Critter Ranching</style> skill to care for critters
STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.RAPTORWELLFE: This critter's recent meal is boosting their feather growth
STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.TAME.NAME: Tame
STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.UNDERWATERCR: This critter recently enjoyed a visit to a water fort
STRINGS.CREATURES.MODIFIERS.WILD.NAME: Wild
STRINGS.CREATURES.PLANT_MUTATIONS.BLOOMS: Vestigial flowers increase the beauty of this plant. Don't inhale the pollen, though!
STRINGS.CREATURES.PLANT_MUTATIONS.BONUSL: Something about this mutation causes Meal Lice to pupate on this plant.
STRINGS.CREATURES.PLANT_MUTATIONS.EXTREM: Plants with this mutation are very difficult to keep alive, but produce a bounty.
STRINGS.CREATURES.PLANT_MUTATIONS.HEAVYF: Extra water in these plump mutant veggies causes them to fall right off the plant! There's no extra nutritional value, though...
STRINGS.CREATURES.PLANT_MUTATIONS.LOADED: This mutation produces lots of extra produce, though it also takes a long time to pick it all!
STRINGS.CREATURES.PLANT_MUTATIONS.MODERA: Plants with this mutation are easier to take care of, but don't yield as much produce.
Plants with this mutation are pickier about their conditions but yield more produce.
STRINGS.CREATURES.PLANT_MUTATIONS.ROTTEN: Plants with this mutation grow extremely quickly, though the produce they make is sometimes questionable.
STRINGS.CREATURES.PLANT_MUTATIONS.SLOWBU: These plants grow almost as slow as their wild cousins, but also consume almost no fertilizer.
STRINGS.CREATURES.PLANT_MUTATIONS.SUNNYS: This mutation provides the plant with sun-collecting leaves, allowing faster growth.
STRINGS.CREATURES.PLANT_MUTATIONS.UNIDEN: This seed must be identified at the <link=\"GENETICANALYSISSTATION\">Botanical Analyzer</link> before it can be planted.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.ALGAE_STEGO.BA: A slightly moist Blum Lumb baby.\n\nIn time, it will grow into a stompy <link=\"ALGAESTEGO\">Blum Lumb</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.ALGAE_STEGO.DE: Blum Lumbs are non-hostile critters that produce <link=\"ALGAE\">Algae</link>.\n\nWhen they stomp heavily near <link=\"PLANTS\">plants</link>, the commotion causes harvestable items to fall to the ground.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BASICFABRICMAT: Thimble Reeds produce indescribably soft <link=\"BASICFABRIC\">Reed Fiber</link> for <link=\"EQUIPMENT\">Clothing</link> production.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BASICFORAGEPLA: Muckroots are incapable of propagating but can be harvested for a single <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link> serving.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BASICSINGLEHAR: Mealwoods produce <link=\"BASICPLANTFOOD\">Meal Lice</link>, an oddly wriggly grain that can be harvested for <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BEAN_PLANT.DES: Nosh Sprouts thrive in colder climates and produce edible <link=\"BEANPLANTSEED\">Nosh Beans</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BEE.BABY.DESC: A harmless little Beetiny.\n\nIn time, it will mature into a vicious adult <link=\"BEE\">Beeta</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BEE.BABY.NAME: <link=\"BEE\">Beetiny</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BEE.DESC: Beetas are hostile critters that thrive in <link=\"RADIATION\">Radioactive</link> environments.\n\nThey commonly gather <link=\"URANIUMORE\">Uranium Ore</link> for their <link=\"BEEHIVE\">Beeta Hives</link> to produce <link=\"ENRICHEDURANIUM\">Enriched Uranium</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BEE.NAME: <link=\"BEE\">Beeta</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BLUE_GRASS.DES: Alveo Veras consume <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link> and <link=\"ICE\">Ice</link>, and form harvestable <link=\"OXYROCK\">Oxylite</link> deposits.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BULBPLANT.DESC: Buddy Buds are leafy plants that have a positive effect on <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>, much like a friend.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BULBPLANT.NAME: <link=\"BULBPLANT\">Buddy Bud</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BUTTERFLY.DESC: Mimikas are airborne organisms that help nearby <link=\"PLANTS\">Plants</link> grow more quickly.\n\nWhen its leaves dry up, it will harden into <link=\"BUTTERFLYPLANTSEED\">Mimillet</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BUTTERFLY.NAME: <link=\"BUTTERFLY\">Mimika</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.BUTTERFLYPLANT: Mimika Buds are self-harvesting plants that produce airborne <link=\"BUTTERFLY\">Mimikas</link>.\n\n<link=\"BUTTERFLY\">Mimikas</link> boost growth for nearby <link=\"PLANTS\">Plants</link> before hardening into <link=\"BUTTERFLYPLANTSEED\">Mimillet</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CACTUSPLANT.DE: Joyas are <link=\"DECOR\">Decorative</link> <link=\"PLANTS\">Plants</link> that are colloquially said to make gardeners \"jump for joy\".
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CARROTPLANT.DE: Plume Squashes are sweet, nutrient-rich tubers that can be harvested for <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CHAMELEON.BABY: A wide-eyed little Dartlet.\n\nSomeday it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"CHAMELEON\">Dartle</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CHAMELEON.DESC: Dartles are non-hostile critters who eat <link=\"DEWDRIP\">Dewdrips</link> and excrete <link=\"BLEACHSTONE\">Bleach Stone</link> and <link=\"CHLORINEGAS\">Chlorine Gas</link> .\n\nThey are preyed on by <link=\"RAPTOR\">Rhexes</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CHAMELEON.NAME: <link=\"CHAMELEON\">Dartle</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CHLORINEGEYSER: A highly pressurized geyser that periodically erupts with <link=\"CHLORINEGAS\">Chlorine Gas</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.COLDBREATHER.D: Wheezeworts can be planted in <link=\"PLANTERBOX\">Planter Boxes</link>, <link=\"FARMTILE\">Farm Tiles</link> or <link=\"HYDROPONICFARM\">Hydroponic Farms</link>, and absorb <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link> by respiring through their porous outer membranes.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.COLDBREATHERCL: Wheezeworts can be planted in <link=\"PLANTERBOX\">Planter Boxes</link>, <link=\"FARMTILE\">Farm Tiles</link> or <link=\"HYDROPONICFARM\">Hydroponic Farms</link>, and absorb <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link> by respiring through their porous outer membranes.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.COLDWHEAT.DESC: Sleet Wheat produces <link=\"COLDWHEATSEED\">Sleet Wheat Grain</link>, a chilly grain that can be processed into <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.COLDWHEAT.DOME: This plant produces edible <link=\"COLDWHEATSEED\">Sleet Wheat Grain</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.COLDWHEAT.NAME: <link=\"COLDWHEAT\">Sleet Wheat</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CRAB.BABY.DESC: A snippy little Pokeshell Spawn.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"CRAB\">Pokeshell</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CRAB.BABY.NAME: <link=\"CRAB\">Pokeshell Spawn</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CRAB.DESC:
Pokeshells are nonhostile critters unless their eggs are nearby.

They eat <link="TOXICSAND">Polluted Dirt</link> and <link="COMPOST">Rot Piles</link>.

The shells they leave behind after molting can be crushed into <link="LIME">Lime</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CRAB.NAME: <link=\"CRAB\">Pokeshell</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CRAB.VARIANT_F: A picky little Sanishell Spawn.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"CRABFRESHWATER\">Sanishell</link>.

Sanishells are nonhostile critters unless their eggs are nearby.

They thrive in <link="WATER">Water</link> and eliminate <link="DISEASE">Germs</link> from any liquid it inhabits.

They eat <link="TOXICSAND">Polluted Dirt</link>, <link="SLIMEMOLD">Slime</link> and <link="COMPOST">Rot Piles</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CRAB.VARIANT_W: A knotty little Oakshell Spawn.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"CRABWOOD\">Oakshell</link>.

Oakshells are nonhostile critters unless their eggs are nearby.

They eat <link="TOXICSAND">Polluted Dirt</link>, <link="SLIMEMOLD">Slime</link> and <link="COMPOST">Rot Piles</link>.

The shells they leave behind after molting can be crushed into <link="WOOD">Wood</link>.

Oakshells thrive in <link="ETHANOL">Ethanol</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CRITTERTRAPPLA: Critter Traps are carnivorous plants that consume small-to-medium-sized critters and release <link=\"HYDROGEN\">Hydrogen Gas</link> as waste.
This plant eats small critters and produces <link=\"HYDROGEN\">Hydrogen Gas</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.CYLINDRICA.DES: Bliss Bursts release an explosion of <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link> into otherwise dull environments.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.DEWDRIPPERPLAN: Dew Drippers produce <link=\"DEWDRIP\">Dewdrips</link> that can be crushed into <link=\"MILK\">Brackene</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.DIESELMOO.DESC: Husky Moos are extraterrestrial critters that feed on <link=\"PLANTFIBER\">Plant Husk</link> and <link=\"GASGRASS\">Gas Grass</link>, and excrete <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link>.\n\nWhen domesticated and fed, they can be milked for <link=\"REFINEDLIPID\">Biodiesel</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.DIESELMOO.NAME: <link=\"DIESELMOO\">Husky Moo</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.DINOFERN.DESC: Megafronds produce <link=\"FERNFOOD\">Megafrond Grain</link>, an ancient grain that can be processed into <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.DINOFERN.NAME: <link=\"DINOFERN\">Megafrond</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.DIVERGENT.VARI: A crawly little Sweetle Larva.\n\nIn time, it will mature into an adult <link=\"DIVERGENTBEETLE\">Sweetle</link>.

Sweetles are nonhostile critters that excrete large amounts of <link=\"SUCROSE\">Sucrose</link>.\n\nThey are closely related to the <link=\"DIVERGENTWORM\">Grubgrub</link> and exhibit similar, albeit less effective farming behaviors.
A squirmy little Grubgrub Wormling.\n\nIn time, it will mature into an adult <link=\"WORM\">Grubgrub</link> and drastically grow in size.

Grubgrubs form symbiotic relationships with plants, especially <link=\"WORMPLANT\">Grubfruit Plants</link>, and instinctually tend to them.\n\nGrubgrubs are closely related to <link=\"DIVERGENTBEETLE\">Sweetles</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.DRECKO.BABY.DE: A little, bug-eyed Drecklet.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"DRECKO\">Drecko</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.DRECKO.DESC: Dreckos are nonhostile critters that graze on <link=\"SPICEVINE\">Pincha Pepperplants</link>, <link=\"SWAMPLILY\">Balm Lily</link> or <link=\"BASICSINGLEHARVESTPLANT\">Mealwood Plants</link>.\n\nTheir backsides are covered in thick woolly fibers that only grow in <link=\"HYDROGEN\">Hydrogen</link> climates.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.DRECKO.NAME: <link=\"DRECKO\">Drecko</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.DRECKO.VARIANT: A bug-eyed little Glossy Drecklet.\n\nIn time it will mature into an adult Drecko morph, the <link=\"DRECKOPLASTIC\">Glossy Drecko</link>.

Glossy Dreckos are nonhostile critters that graze on live <link=\"BASICSINGLEHARVESTPLANT\">Mealwood Plants</link> and <link=\"PRICKLEFLOWER\">Bristle Blossoms</link>.\n\nTheir backsides are covered in bioplastic scales that only grow in <link=\"HYDROGEN\">Hydrogen Gas</link> climates.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.EVILFLOWER.DES: Sporechids have an eerily alluring appearance to mask the fact that they host particularly nasty strain of brain fungus.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.EVILFLOWER.DOM: This plant improves ambient <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link> but produces high quantities of <link=\"ZOMBIESPORES\">Zombie Spores</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.FILTERPLANT.DE: Hydrocacti act as natural <link=\"WATER\">Water</link> filters when given access to <link=\"SAND\">Sand</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.FILTERPLANT.DO: This plant uses <link=\"SAND\">Sand</link> to convert <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Polluted Water</link> into <link=\"WATER\">Water</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.FLYTRAPPLANT.D: Lura plants are carnivorous plants that trap flying critters, such as <link=\"MOSQUITO\">Gnits</link>.\n\nTheir digestive processes produce harvestable <link=\"AMBER\">Amber</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.FORESTFORAGEPL: Hexalents are incapable of propagating but can be harvested for a single, calorie dense <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link> serving.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GARDENDECORPLA: Ring Rosebushes are <link=\"DECOR\">Decorative</link> <link=\"PLANTS\">Plants</link> that add a touch of whimsy wherever they are planted.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GARDENFOODPLAN: Sweatcorn Stalks produce <link=\"GARDENFOODPLANTFOOD\">Sweatcorn</link>, a crisp vegetable that can be harvested for <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GARDENFORAGEPL: Snacti are incapable of propagating but can be harvested for a single <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link> serving.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GASGRASS.DESC: Gas Grass is an alien lifeform tentatively categorized as a \"plant.\"\n\nIt can be harvested for <link=\"PLANTFIBER\">Plant Husk</link> or eaten as-is by <link=\"MOOSPECIES\">Moos</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GASGRASS.DOMES: An alien grass variety that is eaten by <link=\"MOO\">Gassy Moos</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GASGRASS.NAME: <link=\"GASGRASS\">Gas Grass</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.BIG_VOL: A massive volcano that periodically erupts with molten <link=\"MAGMA\">Magma</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.CHLORIN: A highly pressurized vent that periodically erupts with warm <link=\"CHLORINEGAS\">Chlorine Gas</link>.
A highly pressurized vent that periodically erupts with cool <link=\"CHLORINEGAS\">Chlorine Gas</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.DESC: A highly pressurized geyser that periodically erupts, spraying <link=\"STEAM\">Steam</link> and boiling hot <link=\"WATER\">Water</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.FILTHY_: A highly pressurized vent that periodically erupts with boiling <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Polluted Water</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.HOT_CO2: A highly pressurized vent that periodically erupts with hot <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.HOT_HYD: A highly pressurized vent that periodically erupts with hot gaseous <link=\"HYDROGEN\">Hydrogen</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.HOT_PO2: A highly pressurized vent that periodically erupts with hot <link=\"CONTAMINATEDOXYGEN\">Polluted Oxygen</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.HOT_STE: A highly pressurized vent that periodically erupts with scalding <link=\"STEAM\">Steam</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.HOT_WAT: A highly pressurized geyser that periodically erupts with hot <link=\"WATER\">Water</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.LIQUID_: A highly pressurized geyser that periodically erupts with boiling <link=\"LIQUIDCARBONDIOXIDE\">Liquid Carbon Dioxide</link>.
A highly pressurized geyser that periodically erupts with boiling <link=\"LIQUIDSULFUR\">Liquid Sulfur</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.METHANE: A highly pressurized geyser that periodically erupts with hot <link=\"METHANE\">Natural Gas</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.MOLTEN_: A large volcano that periodically erupts with <link=\"MOLTENALUMINUM\">Molten Aluminum</link>.
A large volcano that periodically erupts with <link=\"MOLTENCOBALT\">Molten Cobalt</link>.
A large volcano that periodically erupts with <link=\"MOLTENCOPPER\">Molten Copper</link>.
A large volcano that periodically erupts with <link=\"MOLTENGOLD\">Molten Gold</link>.
A large volcano that periodically erupts with <link=\"MOLTENIRON\">Molten Iron</link>.
A large volcano that periodically erupts with <link=\"NIOBIUM\">Niobium</link>.
A large volcano that periodically erupts with <link=\"MOLTENTUNGSTEN\">Molten Tungsten</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.NAME: <link=\"GEYSER\">Steam Geyser</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.OIL_DRI: A fissure that periodically erupts with boiling <link=\"CRUDEOIL\">Crude Oil</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.SALT_WA: A highly pressurized geyser that periodically erupts with <link=\"SALTWATER\">Salt Water</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.SLIMY_P: A highly pressurized vent that periodically erupts with warm <link=\"CONTAMINATEDOXYGEN\">Polluted Oxygen</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.SLUSH_S: A highly pressurized geyser that periodically erupts with freezing <link=\"BRINE\">Brine</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.SLUSH_W: A highly pressurized geyser that periodically erupts with freezing <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Polluted Water</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.SMALL_V: A miniature volcano that periodically erupts with molten <link=\"MAGMA\">Magma</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GEYSER.STEAM.D: A highly pressurized vent that periodically erupts with <link=\"STEAM\">Steam</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GLASSDEER.BABY: A little yipping Shatter Flox Fawn.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"GLASSDEER\">Shatter Flox</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GLASSDEER.DESC: Shatter Floxes are nonhostile critters that can subsist on <link=\"PRICKLEFLOWER\">Bristle Blossom</link> and <link=\"HARDSKINBERRYPLANT\">Pikeapple Bush</link>.\n\nTheir shearable <link=\"GLASS\">Glass</link> antlers grow only when they are fed <link=\"KATAIRITE\">Abyssalite</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GLASSDEER.NAME: <link=\"GLASSDEER\">Shatter Flox</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GLOM.DESC: Morbs are attracted to unhygienic conditions and frequently excrete bursts of <link=\"CONTAMINATEDOXYGEN\">Polluted Oxygen</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.GLOM.NAME: <link=\"GLOM\">Morb</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.HARDSKINBERRYP: Pikeapple bushes produce <link=\"HARDSKINBERRY\">Pikeapple</link>, a useful yet almost unbearably fragrant <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.HATCH.BABY.DES: An innocent little Hatchling.\n\nIn time, it will mature into an adult <link=\"HATCH\">Hatch</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.HATCH.DESC: Hatches excrete solid <link=\"CARBON\">Coal</link> as waste and may be uncovered by digging up Buried Objects.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.HATCH.NAME: <link=\"HATCH\">Hatch</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.HATCH.VARIANT_: A doofy little Stone Hatchling.\n\nIt matures into an adult Hatch morph, the <link=\"HATCHHARD\">Stone Hatch</link>, which loves nibbling on various rocks and metals.
Stone Hatches excrete solid <link=\"CARBON\">Coal</link> as waste and enjoy burrowing into the ground.
A doofy little Smooth Hatchling.\n\nIt matures into an adult Hatch morph, the <link=\"HATCHMETAL\">Smooth Hatch</link>, which loves nibbling on different types of metals.
Smooth Hatches enjoy burrowing into the ground and excrete <link=\"REFINEDMETAL\">Refined Metal</link> when fed <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal Ore</link>.
A doofy little Sage Hatchling.\n\nIt matures into an adult Hatch morph, the <link=\"HATCHVEGGIE\">Sage Hatch</link>, which loves nibbling on organic materials.
Sage Hatches excrete solid <link=\"CARBON\">Coal</link> as waste and enjoy burrowing into the ground.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.HEATBULB.NAME: <link=\"HEATBULB\">Fervine</link>
A floofy little Bammini.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"ICEBELLY\">Bammoth</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.ICEBELLY.DESC: Bammoths are lumbering, nonhostile creatures that subsist on <link=\"CARROT\">Plume Squash</link>, <link=\"BEANPLANTSEED\">Nosh Beans</link> and <link=\"FRIESCARROT\">Squash Fries</link>.\n\nTheir thick overcoats can be shorn for <link=\"BASICFABRIC\">Reed Fiber</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.ICEBELLY.NAME: <link=\"ICEBELLY\">Bammoth</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.ICEBELLY.VARIA: A haughty little Regal Bammini.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"GOLDBELLY\">Regal Bammoth</link>.

Regal Bammoths are nonhostile creatures that subsist on <link=\"CARROT\">Plume Squash</link> and <link=\"BEANPLANTSEED\">Nosh Beans</link>.\n\nTheir ornate crests grow only when they are fed <link=\"FRIESCARROT\">Squash Fries</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.ICECAVESFORAGE: Sherberries are incapable of propagating, but can be harvested for a single <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link> serving.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.ICEFLOWER.DESC: Idyllas are <link=\"DECOR\">Decorative</link> <link=\"PLANTS\">Plants</link> with soft, pompom-shaped blossoms.\n\nGazing dreamily at them has a positive effect on <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.ICEFLOWER.NAME: <link=\"ICEFLOWER\">Idylla Flower</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.JUNGLEGASPLANT: A large, chlorine-dwelling <link=\"PLANTS\">Plant</link> that can be grown in farm buildings.\n\nPalmeras grow inedible buds that emit unbreathable hydrogen gas.
A large, chlorine-dwelling <link=\"PLANTS\">Plant</link> that grows inedible buds which emit unbreathable hydrogen gas.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.KELPPLANT.DESC: Seakombs consume <link=\"TOXICSAND\">Polluted Dirt</link>.\n\nTheir leaves can be processed to extract <link=\"PHYTOOIL\">Phyto Oil</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.KELPPLANT.NAME: <link=\"KELPPLANT\">Seakomb</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.LEAFYPLANT.DES: Mirth Leaves sport a calm green hue known for alleviating <link=\"STRESS\">Stress</link> and improving <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.LIGHTBUG.DESC: Shine Bugs emit a soft <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link> in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.\n\nTheir eggs contain small amounts of <link=\"NATURALRESIN\">Resin</link> that can be harvested when cracked at the <link=\"EGGCRACKER\">Egg Cracker</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.LIGHTBUG.NAME: <link=\"LIGHTBUG\">Shine Bug</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.LIGHTBUG.VARIA: A chubby baby <link=\"LIGHTBUGBLACK\">Shine Bug</link>.\n\nThis one is an Abyss morph.

This Shine Bug emits no <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link>, but it makes up for it by having an excellent personality.\n\nTheir eggs contain small amounts of <link=\"NATURALRESIN\">Resin</link> that can be harvested when cracked at the <link=\"EGGCRACKER\">Egg Cracker</link>.
A chubby baby <link=\"LIGHTBUGBLUE\">Shine Bug</link>.\n\nThis one is an Azure morph.

Azure Bugs emit a soft blue <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link> in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.\n\nTheir eggs contain small amounts of <link=\"NATURALRESIN\">Resin</link> that can be harvested when cracked at the <link=\"EGGCRACKER\">Egg Cracker</link>.
A chubby baby <link=\"LIGHTBUGCRYSTAL\">Shine Bug</link>.\n\nThis one is a Radiant morph.

Radiant Bugs emit an extra-bright <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link> in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.\n\nTheir eggs contain small amounts of <link=\"NATURALRESIN\">Resin</link> that can be harvested when cracked at the <link=\"EGGCRACKER\">Egg Cracker</link>.
A chubby baby <link=\"LIGHTBUGORANGE\">Shine Bug</link>.\n\nThis one is a Sun morph.

Sun Bugs emit a soft orange <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link> in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.\n\nTheir eggs contain small amounts of <link=\"NATURALRESIN\">Resin</link> that can be harvested when cracked at the <link=\"EGGCRACKER\">Egg Cracker</link>.
A chubby baby <link=\"LIGHTBUGPINK\">Shine Bug</link>.\n\nThis one is a Coral morph.

Coral Bugs emit a soft pink <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link> in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.\n\nTheir eggs contain small amounts of <link=\"NATURALRESIN\">Resin</link> that can be harvested when cracked at the <link=\"EGGCRACKER\">Egg Cracker</link>.
A chubby baby <link=\"LIGHTBUGPURPLE\">Shine Bug</link>.\n\nThis one is a Royal morph.

Royal Bugs emit a soft purple <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link> in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.\n\nTheir eggs contain small amounts of <link=\"NATURALRESIN\">Resin</link> that can be harvested when cracked at the <link=\"EGGCRACKER\">Egg Cracker</link>.
A chubby baby <link=\"LIGHTBUGRADIOACTIVE\">Shine Bug</link>.\n\nThis one is an Ionizing morph.
Shine Bugs emit a dangerously radioactive <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link> in hopes of attracting more of their kind for company.
A highly pressurized geyser that periodically erupts with <link=\"METHANE\">Natural Gas</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.MOLE.BABY.DESC: A snuggly little pup.\n\nOne day it will grow into an adult <link=\"MOLE\">Shove Vole</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.MOLE.BABY.NAME: <link=\"MOLE\">Vole Pup</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.MOLE.DESC: Shove Voles are burrowing critters that eat the <link=\"REGOLITH\">Regolith</link> collected on terrestrial surfaces.\n\nThey cannot burrow through <link=\"REFINEDMETAL\">Refined Metals</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.MOLE.NAME: <link=\"MOLE\">Shove Vole</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.MOLE.VARIANT_D: A tender little Delecta Vole pup.\n\nOne day it will grow into an adult Shove Vole morph, the <link=\"MOLEDELICACY\">Delecta Vole</link>.

Delecta Voles are burrowing critters whose bodies sprout shearable <link=\"GINGERCONFIG\">Tonic Root</link> when <link=\"REGOLITH\">Regolith</link> is ingested at preferred temperatures.\n\nThey cannot burrow through <link=\"REFINEDMETAL\">Refined Metals</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.MOO.DESC: Moos are extraterrestrial critters that feed on <link=\"GASGRASS\">Gas Grass</link> and excrete <link=\"METHANE\">Natural Gas</link>.\n\nWhen domesticated and fed, they can be milked for <link=\"MILK\">Brackene</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.MOO.NAME: <link=\"MOO\">Gassy Moo</link>
A wiggly little Gnit Larva.\n\nIn time, it will mature into an irritating <link=\"MOSQUITO\">Gnit</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.MOSQUITO.DESC: Gnits are hostile airborne critters primarily bred as food for the carnivorous <link=\"FLYTRAPPLANT\">Lura Plants</link> to produce <link=\"AMBER\">Amber</link>.\n\nTheir offspring must be exposed to <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> in order to survive.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.MOSQUITO.NAME: <link=\"MOSQUITO\">Gnit</link>
Dusk Caps produce <link=\"MUSHROOM\">Mushrooms</link>, fungal growths that can be harvested for <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.MYSTERYEGG.DES: What's growing inside? Something nice? Something mean?
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.OILFLOATER.BAB: A goopy little Slickster Larva.\n\nOne day it will grow into an adult <link=\"OILFLOATER\">Slickster</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.OILFLOATER.DES: Slicksters are slimy critters that consume <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link> and exude <link=\"CRUDEOIL\">Crude Oil</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.OILFLOATER.VAR: A snuggly little Longhair Larva.\n\nOne day it will grow into an adult Slickster morph, the <link=\"OILFLOATERDECOR\">Longhair Slickster</link>.
Longhair Slicksters are friendly critters that consume <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link> and thrive in close contact with Duplicant companions.\n\nLonghairs have extremely beautiful and luxurious coats.
A goopy little Molten Larva.\n\nOne day it will grow into an adult Slickster morph, the <link=\"OILFLOATERHIGHTEMP\">Molten Slickster</link>.
Molten Slicksters are slimy critters that consume <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link> and exude <link=\"PETROLEUM\">Petroleum</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.OILSPOUT.DESC: A rocky vent that spouts <link=\"CRUDEOIL\">Crude Oil</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.OILSPOUT.NAME: <link=\"OILSPOUT\">Oil Spout</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.OIL_WELL.DESC: Oil Reservoirs are rock formations with <link=\"CRUDEOIL\">Crude Oil</link> deposits beneath their surface.\n\nOil can be extracted from a reservoir with sufficient pressure.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.OIL_WELL.NAME: <link=\"OILWELL\">Oil Reservoir</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.OXYFERN.DESC: Oxyferns absorb <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide Gas</link> and exude breathable <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.OXYFERN.NAME: <link=\"OXYFERN\">Oxyfern</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PACU.BABY.DESC: A wriggly little Pacu Fry.\n\nIn time, it will mature into an adult <link=\"PACU\">Pacu</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PACU.BABY.NAME: <link=\"PACU\">Pacu Fry</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PACU.DESC: Pacus are aquatic creatures that can live in any liquid, such as <link=\"WATER\">Water</link> or <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Polluted Water</link>.\n\nEvery organism in the known universe finds the Pacu extremely delicious.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PACU.NAME: <link=\"PACU\">Pacu</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PACU.VARIANT_C: A wriggly little Gulp Fry.\n\nIn time, it will mature into an adult <link=\"PACUCLEANER\">Gulp Fish</link>.
Gulp Fishes are aquatic critters who inhabit cold liquid pools.\n\nTheir gills filter <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Polluted Water</link> into <link=\"WATER\">Water</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PACU.VARIANT_T: A wriggly little Tropical Fry.\n\nIn time it will mature into an adult Pacu morph, the <link=\"PACUTROPICAL\">Tropical Pacu</link>.
Tropical Pacus are aquatic critters who inhabit warm liquid pools.\n\nTheir vibrant colors provide a significant <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link> boost to their environment.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PACUEGG.DESC: A tiny Pacu is nestled inside.\n\nIt is not yet ready for the world.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PACUEGG.NAME: <link=\"PACUEGG\">Pacu Egg</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PINKROCK.CODEX: Lumen quartz is a naturally occurring object found in the <link=\"BIOMECARROTQUARRY\">Cool Pool</link> biome.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PINKROCK.DESC: Lumen quartz emits a soft glowing <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link> that makes everything look and feel a little rosier.\n\nIt's even brighter and more beautiful once it's been carved.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PINKROCK.NAME: <link=\"PINKROCK\">Lumen Quartz</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PINKROCKCARVED: A Duplicant has carved this Lumen quartz in a way that really maximizes its <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link> value and <link=\"LIGHT\">brightness</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PREHISTORICPAC: A grumpy little Jawbo fry.\n\nIn time, it will grow into a toothy <link=\"PREHISTORICPACU\">Jawbo</link>.
Jawbos are carnivorous aquatic critters that feed on <link=\"PACU\">Pacus</link> and produce <link=\"RUST\">Rust</link>.\n\nThey pose no danger to Duplicants.
Bristle Blossoms produce <link=\"PRICKLEFRUIT\">Bristle Berry</link>, a prickly edible bud.
This plant produces edible <link=\"BRISTLE BERRY\">Bristle Berries</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PRICKLEGRASS.D: Bluff Briars exude pheromones causing critters to view them as especially beautiful.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PROPANESPOUT.D: A rocky vent that spouts <link=\"PROPANE\">Propane Gas</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PUFT.BABY.DESC: A gassy little Puftlet.\n\nIn time it will grow into an adult <link=\"PUFT\">Puft</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PUFT.BABY.NAME: <link=\"PUFT\">Puftlet</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PUFT.DESC: Pufts are non-aggressive critters that excrete lumps of <link=\"SLIMEMOLD\">Slime</link> with each breath.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PUFT.NAME: <link=\"PUFT\">Puft</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PUFT.VARIANT_A:
A gassy little Puftlet Prince.

One day it will grow into an adult Puft morph, the <link="PUFTALPHA">Puft Prince</link>.

It seems a bit snobby...
The Puft Prince is a lazy critter that excretes little <link=\"SOLID\">Solid</link> lumps of whatever it has been breathing.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PUFT.VARIANT_B: A frazzled little Squeaky Puftlet.\n\nOne day it will grow into an adult Puft morph, the <link=\"PUFTBLEACHSTONE\">Squeaky Puft</link>.
Squeaky Pufts are non-aggressive critters that excrete lumps of <link=\"BLEACHSTONE\">Bleachstone</link> with each breath.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.PUFT.VARIANT_O: A stocky little Dense Puftlet.\n\nOne day it will grow into an adult Puft morph, the <link=\"PUFTOXYLITE\">Dense Puft</link>.
Dense Pufts are non-aggressive critters that excrete condensed <link=\"OXYROCK\">Oxylite</link> with each breath.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.RAPTOR.BABY.DE: A feathery little Rhex fledgling.\n\nOne day, it will grow into a fearsome <link=\"RAPTOR\">Rhex</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.RAPTOR.DESC: Rhexes are carnivorous critters that feed on smaller <link=\"CREATURES\">Critters</link> and produce <link=\"BRINEICE\">Brine Ice</link>.\n\nTheir tailfeathers can be shorn for <link=\"FEATHERFABRIC\">Feather Fiber</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.RAPTOR.NAME: <link=\"RAPTOR\">Rhex</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SALTPLANT.DESC: Dasha Saltvines consume small amounts of <link=\"CHLORINEGAS\">Chlorine Gas</link> and form sodium deposits as they grow, producing harvestable <link=\"SALT\">Salt</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SALTPLANT.NAME: <link=\"SALTPLANT\">Dasha Saltvine</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SAPTREE.DESC: A <link=\"RESIN\">Sap</link>-producing cybernetic tree that shows signs of sentience.\n\nIt is rooted firmly in place, and is waiting for some brave soul to bring it food.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SAPTREE.NAME: <link=\"SAPTREE\">Experiment 52B</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEAL.BABY.DESC: A wobbly little Spigot Pup.\n\nIn time, it will mature into an adult <link=\"SEAL\">Spigot Seal</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEAL.BABY.NAME: <link=\"SEAL\">Spigot Pup</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEAL.DESC: Spigot Seals are charismatic creatures who produce <link=\"ETHANOL\">Ethanol</link>.\n\nThey eat <link=\"SUCROSE\">Sucrose</link>, and drink <link=\"SUGARWATER\">Nectar</link> straight from the <link=\"SPACETREE\">Bonbon Tree</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEAL.NAME: <link=\"SEAL\">Spigot Seal</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEALETTUCE.DES: Waterweeds thrive in salty water and can be harvested for fresh, edible <link=\"LETTUCE\">Lettuce</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.BASICFAB: The <link=\"PLANTS\">Seed</link> of a <link=\"BASICFABRICPLANT\">Thimble Reed</link>.\n\nDigging up Buried Objects may uncover a Thimble Reed Seed.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.BASICSIN: The <link=\"PLANTS\">Seed</link> of a <link=\"BASICSINGLEHARVESTPLANT\">Mealwood</link>.\n\nDigging up Buried Objects may uncover a Mealwood Seed.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.BEAN_PLA: The <link=\"PLANTS\">Seed</link> of a <link=\"BEANPLANT\">Nosh Sprout</link>.\n\nDigging up Buried Objects may uncover a Nosh Bean.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.BLUE_GRA: The <link=\"PLANTS\">Seed</link> of a <link=\"BLUEGRASS\">Alveo Vera</link>.\n\nDigging up Buried Objects may uncover an Alveo Vera Seed.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.BULBPLAN: The <link=\"PLANTS\">Seed</link> of a <link=\"BULBPLANT\">Buddy Bud</link>.\n\nDigging up Buried Objects may uncover a Buddy Bud Seed.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.BUTTERFL:
An inedible <link="PLANTS">Seed</link> of a <link="BUTTERFLYPLANT">Mimika Bud</link> plant.

It can be sown to cultivate more plants, or processed into <link="FOOD">Food</link>.

Digging up Buried Objects may uncover Mimillet.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.CACTUSPL: The <link=\"PLANTS\">Seed</link> of a <link=\"CACTUSPLANT\">Jumping Joya</link>.\n\nDigging up Buried Objects may uncover a Joya Seed.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.CARROTPL: The <link=\"PLANTS\">Seed</link> of a <link=\"CARROTPLANT\">Plume Squash Plant</link>.\n\nDigging up Buried Objects may uncover a Plume Squash Seed.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.COLDBREA: The <link=\"PLANTS\">Seed</link> of a <link=\"COLDBREATHER\">Wheezewort</link>.\n\nDigging up Buried Objects may uncover a Wort Seed.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.COLDWHEA: The <link=\"PLANTS\">Seed</link> of a <link=\"COLDWHEAT\">Sleet Wheat</link> plant.\n\nGrain can be sown to cultivate more Sleet Wheat, or processed into <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.CRITTERT: The <link=\"PLANTS\">Seed</link> of a <link=\"CRITTERTRAPPLANT\">Saturn Critter Trap</link>.\n\nDigging up Buried Objects may uncover a Saturn Critter Trap Seed.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.CYLINDRI: The <link=\"PLANTS\">Seed</link> of a <link=\"CYLINDRICA\">Bliss Burst</link>.\n\nDigging up Buried Objects may uncover a Bliss Burst Seed.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SEEDS.EVILFLOW: The <link=\"PLANTS\">Seed</link> of a <link=\"EVILFLOWER\">Sporechid</link>.\n\nDigging up Buried Objects may uncover a <link=\"EVILFLOWER\">Sporechid Seed</link>.

STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SHOCKWORM.DESC: Shockworms are exceptionally aggressive and discharge electrical shocks to stun their prey.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SHOCKWORM.NAME: <link=\"SHOCKWORM\">Shockworm</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SPACETREE.DESC:
Bonbon Tree branches synthesize <link="LIGHT">Light</link> to produce <link="SUGARWATER">Nectar</link>.

Branches can be harvested for <link="WOOD">Wood</link>.

Bonbon Trees can shed most environmental debris, and rarely become entombed.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SPACETREE.NAME: <link=\"SPACETREE\">Bonbon Tree</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SPICE_VINE.DES: Pincha Pepperplants produce flavorful <link=\"SPICENUT\">Pincha Peppernut</link> for spicing <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.
A little purring Pipsqueak.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"SQUIRREL\">Pip</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SQUIRREL.DESC: Pips are pesky, nonhostile critters that subsist on <link=\"BASICFABRICPLANT\">Thimble Reeds</link> and <link=\"FORESTTREE\">Arbor Tree</link> branches.\n\nThey are known to bury <link=\"PLANTS\">Seeds</link> in the ground whenever they can find a suitable area with enough space.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SQUIRREL.NAME: <link=\"SQUIRREL\">Pip</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SQUIRREL.VARIA: A fuzzy little Cuddle Pipsqueak.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"SQUIRREL\">Cuddle Pip</link>.
Cuddle Pips are fluffy, affectionate critters who exhibit a strong snuggling instinct towards all types of eggs.\n\nThis is temporarily amplified when they are hugged by a passing Duplicant.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.STATERPILLAR.B: A chubby little Plug Sluglet.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"STATERPILLAR\">Plug Slug</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.STATERPILLAR.D: Plug Slugs are dynamic creatures that generate electrical <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> during the night.\n\nTheir power can be harnessed by leaving an exposed wire near areas where they like to sleep.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.STATERPILLAR.V: A tubby little Smog Sluglet.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"STATERPILLAR\">Smog Slug</link>.

Smog Slugs are porous creatures that draw in unbreathable <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gases</link> during the day.\n\nAt night, they sleep near exposed <link=\"GASCONDUIT\">Gas Pipes,</link> where they deposit their cache.
A chonky little Sponge Sluglet.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"STATERPILLAR\">Sponge Slug</link>.

Sponge Slugs are thirsty creatures that soak up <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquids</link> during the day.\n\nThey deposit their stored <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquids</link> into the exposed <link=\"LIQUIDCONDUIT\">Liquid Pipes</link> they sleep next to at night.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.STEGO.BABY.DES: A heavy-footed little Lumb baby.\n\nIn time, it will grow into a stompy <link=\"STEGO\">Lumb</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.STEGO.DESC: Lumbs are non-hostile critters that subsist on <link=\"VINEMOTHER\">Ovagro</link> vines.\n\nWhen they stomp heavily near <link=\"PLANTS\">plants</link>, the commotion causes harvestable items to fall to the ground.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.STEGO.NAME: <link=\"STEGO\">Lumb</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SUPERWORMPLANT: A Grubfruit Plant that has flourished after being tended by a <link=\"DIVERGENTSPECIES\">Divergent</link> critter.\n\nIt will produce high quality <link=\"WORMSUPERFRUIT\">Grubfruits</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SWAMPFORAGEPLA: Swamp Chards are incapable of propagating but can be harvested for a single low quality and calorie dense <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link> serving.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SWAMPHARVESTPL: Bog Buckets produce juicy, sweet <link=\"SWAMPFRUIT\">Bog Jellies</link> for <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SWAMPLILY.DESC: Balm Lilies produce <link=\"SWAMPLILYFLOWER\">Balm Lily Flower</link>, a lovely bloom with medicinal properties.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SWAMPLILY.DOME: This plant produces medicinal <link=\"SWAMPLILYFLOWER\">Balm Lily Flower</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.SWAMPLILY.NAME: <link=\"SWAMPLILY\">Balm Lily</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.TOEPLANT.DESC: Tranquil Toes improve <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link> by giving their surroundings the visual equivalent of a foot rub.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.TOEPLANT.NAME: <link=\"TOEPLANT\">Tranquil Toes</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.VINEBRANCH.DES: Ovagro Vines are plants that produce edible <link=\"VINEFRUIT\">Ovagro Fig</link>.\n\nIf a vine is cut off from its <link=\"VINEMOTHER\">Ovagro Node</link>, it will perish.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.VINEMOTHER.DES: Ovagro Nodes are trellis plants that spread onto nearby available surfaces.\n\nA single <link=\"VINEMOTHER\">Ovagro Node</link> can support several <link=\"VINEMOTHER\">Ovagro Vines</link> without any increase in its <link=\"WATER\">Water</link> requirements.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.WINECUPS.DESC: Mellow Mallows heighten <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link> and alleviate <link=\"STRESS\">Stress</link> with their calming color and cradle shape.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.WINECUPS.NAME: <link=\"WINECUPS\">Mellow Mallow</link>
A little yipping Flox Fawn.\n\nIn time it will mature into a fully grown <link=\"WOODDEER\">Flox</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.WOODDEER.DESC: Floxes are nonhostile critters that graze on <link=\"PRICKLEFLOWER\">Bristle Blossoms</link> and <link=\"HARDSKINBERRY\">Pikeapples</link>.\n\nWhen Flox antlers are fully grown, they harden into shearable <link=\"WOOD\">Wood</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.WOODDEER.NAME: <link=\"WOODDEER\">Flox</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.WOOD_TREE.DESC: Arbor Trees grow <link=\"FORESTTREE\">Arbor Tree Branches</link> and can be harvested for <link=\"WOOD\">Wood</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.WOOD_TREE.DOME: This plant produces <link=\"FORESTTREE\">Arbor Tree Branches</link> that can be harvested for <link=\"WOOD\">Wood</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.WOOD_TREE.NAME: <link=\"FORESTTREE\">Arbor Tree</link>
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.WOOD_TREE_BRAN: Arbor Trees Branches can be harvested for <link=\"WOOD\">Wood</link>.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.WORMPLANT.DESC: Spindly Grubfruit Plants produce <link=\"WORMBASICFRUIT\">Spindly Grubfruit</link> for <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.\n\nIf it is tended by a <link=\"DIVERGENTSPECIES\">Divergent</link> critter, it will produce high quality fruits instead.
STRINGS.CREATURES.SPECIES.WORMPLANT.NAME: <link=\"WORMPLANT\">Spindly Grubfruit Plant</link>

STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.VERTICALWIN: This Duplicant recently had an exhilarating wind tunnel experience\n\nLeisure activities increase Duplicants' <style=\"KKeyword\">Morale</style>
This Duplicant is having an exhilarating time in the wind tunnel\n\nWhoosh!
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.VERTIGO.CAU: This Duplicant got so good at their job they became bad at ladders
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.VERTIGO.TOO: This Duplicant had to climb a tall ladder that left them dizzy and unsettled
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.VOMITING.TO: Better out than in, as they say
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.WAILEDAT.TO: This Duplicant is feeling <style=\"KKeyword\">Stressed</style> by someone's Banshee Wail
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.WARMINGUP.T: This Duplicant is trying to warm back up
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.WARMTOUCH.P: Using this building provides temporary immunity to <style=\"KKeyword\">Chilly Surroundings</style> and <style=\"KKeyword\">Soggy Feet</style>
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.WARMTOUCH.T: This Duplicant recently visited a warming station, sauna, or hot tub\n\nThey are impervious to <style=\"KKeyword\">Chilly Surroundings</style> and <style=\"KKeyword\">Soggy Feet</style> as a result
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.WARMTOUCHFO: Obtained by eating a very spicy meal
Eating this provides temporary immunity to <style=\"KKeyword\">Chilly Surroundings</style> and <style=\"KKeyword\">Soggy Feet</style>
This Duplicant ate spicy food and feels so warm inside that they don't even notice the cold right now
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.WASATTACKED: This Duplicant is stressed out after having been attacked
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.WELLFED.TOO: This Duplicant feels satisfied after having a big meal
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.WORKENCOURA: Someone saw how hard this Duplicant was working and gave them a compliment\n\nThis Duplicant feels great about themselves now!
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.WORKING.TOO: This Duplicant is working up a sweat
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.MODIFIERS.ZOMBIESICKN: This Duplicant recently recovered from <link=\"ZOMBIESICKNESS\">Zombie Spores</link> and is temporarily immune to the <style=\"KKeyword\">Disease</style>
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.NEEDS.DECOR.EXPECTATI: Most objects have Decor values that alter Duplicants' opinions of their surroundings.\nThis Duplicant desires Decor values of {0} or higher, and becomes Stressed in areas with lower Decor.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.NEEDS.DECOR.NAME: Decor Expectation
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.NEEDS.FOOD_QUALITY.EX: Each Duplicant has a minimum quality of <style=\"KKeyword\">Food</style> they'll tolerate eating.\nThis Duplicant desires <b>Tier {0}<b> or better <style=\"KKeyword\">Food</style>, and becomes <style=\"KKeyword\">Stressed</style> when they eat meals of lower quality.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.NEEDS.FOOD_QUALITY.FO: \nThis Duplicant is content to eat Food with a Food Quality of {0} or higher
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.NEEDS.NOISE.NAME: Noise Expectation
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.NEEDS.QUALITYOFLIFE.E: The more responsibilities and stressors a Duplicant has, the more they will desire additional leisure time and improved amenities.\n\nFailing to keep a Duplicant's <style=\"KKeyword\">Morale</style> at or above their <style=\"KKeyword\">Morale Need</style> means they will not be able to unwind, causing them <style=\"KKeyword\">Stress</style> over time.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.ABE.DES: {0}s are sweet, delicate flowers. They need to be treated gingerly, with great consideration for their feelings.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.ADA.DES: {0}s enjoy writing poetry in their downtime. Dark poetry.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.AMARI.D: {0}s likes to keep the peace. Ironically, they're a riot at parties.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.ARI.DES: {0}s tend to space out from time to time, but they always pay attention when it counts.
{0}s have what can only be described as a \"seriously infectious giggle\".
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.BANHI.D: The \"cool loner\" vibes that radiate off a {0} never fail to make the colony swoon.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.BUBBLES: This {0} is constantly challenging others to fight her, regardless of whether or not she can actually take them.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.BURT.DE: This {0} always feels great after a bubble bath and a good long cry.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.CAMILLE: This {0} loves anything that makes her feel nostalgic, including things that haven't aged well.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.CATALIN: A {0} is admired by all for her seemingly tireless work ethic. Little do people know, she's dying on the inside.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.CHIP.DE: This {0} is extremely good at guessing their friends' passwords.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.DEVON.D: This {0} dreams of owning their own personal computer so they can start a blog full of pictures of toast.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.EDWIRED: This {0} once rolled his eye so hard that he powered himself off and on again.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.ELLIE.D: Nothing makes an {0} happier than a big tin of glitter and a pack of unicorn stickers.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.FRANKIE: There's nothing {0}s are more proud of than their thick, dignified eyebrows.
This {0} has never stopped anyone from eating yellow snow.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.GIZMO.D: {0}s love nothing more than a big juicy info dump.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.GOSSMAN: {0}s are major goofballs who can make anyone laugh.
Get a bunch of {0}s together in a room, and you'll have... a bunch of {0}s together in a room.
If someone says something nice to a {0} he'll think about it nonstop for no less than three weeks.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.HIGBY.D: This {0}'s got a song in his heart. Now if only he could remember how it goes.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.JEAN.DE: Just because {0}s are a little slow doesn't mean they can't suffer from soul-crushing existential crises.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.JORGE.D: {0} loves his new colony, even if their collective body odor makes his eyes water.
{0}s are precious goobers. Other Duplicants are strangely incapable of cursing in a {0}'s presence.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.LEIRA.D: {0}s just want everyone to be happy.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.LIAM.DE: No matter how much this {0} scrubs, he can never truly feel clean.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.LINDSAY: A {0} is a charming woman, unless you make the mistake of messing with one of her friends.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.MAE.DES: There's nothing a {0} can't do if she sets her mind to it.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.MARIE.D: This {0} is positively glowing! What's her secret? Radioactive isotopes, of course.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.MAX.DES: At any given moment a {0} is viscerally reliving ten different humiliating memories.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.MAYA.DE: This {0} got her hand crushed in a pneumatic door once. It was the most alive she's ever felt.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.MEEP.DE: {0}s have a face only a two tonne Printing Pod could love.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.MIMA.DE: Ol' {0} here can't stand lookin' at people's knees.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.NAILS.D: People often expect a Duplicant named \"{0}\" to be tough, but they're all pretty huge wimps.
This {0} once claimed he could build a laser so powerful it would rip the colony in half. No one asked him to prove it.
This {0} likes to punch people to show her affection. Everyone's too afraid of her to tell her it hurts.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.OTTO.DE: {0}s always insult people by accident and generally exist in a perpetual state of deep regret.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.PEI.DES: Every {0} spends at least half the day pretending that they remember what they came into this room for.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.QUINN.D: This {0}'s favorite genre of music is \"festive power ballad\".
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.REN.DES: Every {0} has this unshakable feeling that his life's already happened and he's just watching it unfold from a memory.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.ROWAN.D: {0}s have exceptionally large hearts and express their emotions most efficiently by yelling.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.RUBY.DE: This {0} asks the pressing questions, like \"Where can I get a leather jacket in space?\"
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.SENA.DE: {0}s only care about three things: gold accents, true crime, and the advancement of nuclear physics.
{0}s would sooner burn down the colony than read an instruction manual.
{0}s aren't programmed to put up with nonsense, but they do enjoy the occasional shenanigan.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.STEVE.D: This {0} is convinced that he has psychic powers. And he knows exactly what his friends think about that.
This {0} has never been invited to a party, which is a shame. His dance moves are incredible.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.TRAVALD: A {0}'s monotonous voice and lack of facial expression makes it impossible for others to tell when he's messing with them.
This {0} is paralyzed by the knowledge that others have memories and perceptions of them they can't control.
STRINGS.DUPLICANTS.PERSONALITIES.ULTI.DE: This {0}'s favorite dance move is The Robot. They don't get why others think that's funny.
