STRINGS.ELEMENTS.BITUMEN.NAME: <link=\"BITUMEN\">Bitumen</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.BLEACHSTONE.DESC: Bleach stone is an unstable compound that emits unbreathable <link=\"CHLORINEGAS\">Chlorine Gas</link>.\n\nIt is often used in <link=\"HANDSANITIZER\">Hygienic</link> processes.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.BLEACHSTONE.NAME: <link=\"BLEACHSTONE\">Bleach Stone</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.BOTTLEDWATER.NAME: <link=\"BOTTLEDWATER\">Water</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.BRICK.DESC: Brick is a hard, brittle material formed from heated Clay.\n\nIt is a reliable Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.BRICK.NAME: <link=\"BRICK\">Brick</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.BRINE.DESC: Brine is a natural, highly concentrated solution of <link=\"SALT\">Salt</link> dissolved in <link=\"WATER\">Water</link>.\n\nIt can be used in desalination processes, separating out usable salt.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.BRINE.NAME: <link=\"BRINE\">Brine</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.BRINEICE.DESC: Brine Ice is a natural, highly concentrated solution of <link=\"SALT\">Salt</link> dissolved in <link=\"WATER\">Water</link> and frozen into a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.\n\nIt can be used in desalination processes, separating out usable salt.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.BRINEICE.NAME: <link=\"BRINEICE\">Brine Ice</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CARBON.DESC: (C) Coal is a combustible fossil fuel composed of carbon.\n\nIt is useful in <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> production.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CARBON.NAME: <link=\"CARBON\">Coal</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CARBONDIOXIDE.DESC: (CO<sub>2</sub>) Carbon Dioxide is an atomically heavy chemical compound in a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.\n\nIt tends to sink below other gases.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CARBONDIOXIDE.NAME: <link=\"CARBONDIOXIDE\">Carbon Dioxide</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CARBONFIBRE.DESC: Carbon Fiber is a <link=\"REFINEDMINERAL\">Manufactured Material</link> with high tensile strength.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CARBONFIBRE.NAME: <link=\"CARBONFIBRE\">Carbon Fiber</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CARBONGAS.DESC: (C) Carbon is an abundant, versatile element heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CARBONGAS.NAME: <link=\"CARBONGAS\">Carbon Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CEMENT.DESC: Cement is a refined building material used for assembling advanced buildings.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CEMENT.NAME: <link=\"CEMENT\">Cement</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CEMENTMIX.DESC: Cement Mix can be used to create <link=\"CEMENT\">Cement</link> for advanced building assembly.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CEMENTMIX.NAME: <link=\"CEMENTMIX\">Cement Mix</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CERAMIC.DESC: Ceramic is a hard, brittle material formed from heated Clay.\n\nIt is a reliable Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CERAMIC.NAME: <link=\"CERAMIC\">Ceramic</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CHLORINE.DESC: (Cl) Chlorine is a natural <link=\"DISEASE\">Germ</link>-killing element in a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CHLORINE.NAME: <link=\"CHLORINE\">Liquid Chlorine</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CHLORINEGAS.DESC: (Cl) Chlorine is a natural <link=\"DISEASE\">Germ</link>-killing element in a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CHLORINEGAS.NAME: <link=\"CHLORINEGAS\">Chlorine Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CINNABAR.DESC: (HgS) Cinnabar Ore, also known as mercury sulfide, is a conductive <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> that can be refined into <link=\"MERCURY\">Mercury</link>.\n\nIt is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CINNABAR.NAME: <link=\"CINNABAR\">Cinnabar Ore</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CLAY.DESC: Clay is a soft, naturally occurring composite of stone and soil that hardens at high Temperatures.\n\nIt is a reliable Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CLAY.NAME: <link=\"CLAY\">Clay</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.COBALT.DESC: (Co) Cobalt is a <link=\"REFINEDMETAL\">Refined Metal</link> made from <link=\"COBALTITE\">Cobalt Ore</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.COBALT.NAME: <link=\"COBALT\">Cobalt</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.COBALTGAS.DESC: (Co) Cobalt is a <link=\"REFINEDMETAL\">Refined Metal</link>, heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.COBALTGAS.NAME: <link=\"COBALTGAS\">Cobalt Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.COBALTITE.DESC: (Co) Cobalt Ore is a blue-hued <link=\"BUILDINGMATERIALCLASSES\">Metal</link>.\n\nIt is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.COBALTITE.NAME: <link=\"COBALTITE\">Cobalt Ore</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.COMPOSITION.DESC: A mixture of two or more elements.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.COMPOSITION.NAME: <link=\"COMPOSITION\">Composition</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CONTAMINATEDOXYGEN.DESC: (O<sub>2</sub>) Polluted Oxygen is dirty, unfiltered air.\n\nIt is breathable.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CONTAMINATEDOXYGEN.NAME: <link=\"CONTAMINATEDOXYGEN\">Polluted Oxygen</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.COPPER.DESC: (Cu) Copper is a conductive <link=\"METAL\">Metal</link>.\n\nIt is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.COPPER.NAME: <link=\"COPPER\">Copper</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.COPPERGAS.DESC: (Cu) Copper Gas is a conductive <link=\"METAL\">Metal</link> heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.COPPERGAS.NAME: <link=\"COPPERGAS\">Copper Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CORIUM.DESC: A radioactive mixture of nuclear waste and melted reactor materials.\n\nReleases <link=\"FALLOUT\">Nuclear Fallout</link> gas.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CORIUM.NAME: <link=\"CORIUM\">Corium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CREATURE.DESC: (DuPe) Ooze is a slurry of water, carbon, and dozens and dozens of trace elements.\n\nDuplicants are printed from pure Ooze.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CREATURE.NAME: <link=\"CREATURE\">Genetic Ooze</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CRUDEOIL.DESC: Crude Oil is a raw potential <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> source composed of billions of dead, primordial organisms.\n\nIt is also a useful lubricant for certain types of machinery.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CRUDEOIL.NAME: <link=\"CRUDEOIL\">Crude Oil</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CRUSHEDICE.DESC: (H<sub>2</sub>O) A slush of crushed, semi-solid ice.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CRUSHEDICE.NAME: <link=\"CRUSHEDICE\">Crushed Ice</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CRUSHEDROCK.DESC: Crushed Rock is <link=\"IGNEOUSROCK\">Igneous Rock</link> crushed into a mechanical mixture.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CRUSHEDROCK.NAME: <link=\"CRUSHEDROCK\">Crushed Rock</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CUPRITE.DESC: (Cu<sub>2</sub>O) Copper Ore is a conductive <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link>.\n\nIt is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.CUPRITE.NAME: <link=\"CUPRITE\">Copper Ore</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.DEPLETEDURANIUM.DESC: (U) Depleted Uranium is <link=\"URANIUMORE\">Uranium</link> with a low U-235 content.\n\nIt is created as a byproduct of <link=\"ENRICHEDURANIUM\">Enriched Uranium</link> and is no longer suitable as fuel.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.DEPLETEDURANIUM.NAME: <link=\"DEPLETEDURANIUM\">Depleted Uranium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.DIAMOND.DESC: (C) Diamond is industrial-grade, high density carbon.\n\nIt is very difficult to excavate.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.DIAMOND.NAME: <link=\"DIAMOND\">Diamond</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.DIRT.DESC: Dirt is a soft, nutrient-rich substance capable of supporting life.\n\nIt is necessary in some forms of <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link> production.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.DIRT.NAME: <link=\"DIRT\">Dirt</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.DIRTYICE.DESC: Polluted Ice is dirty, unfiltered water frozen into a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.DIRTYICE.NAME: <link=\"DIRTYICE\">Polluted Ice</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.DIRTYWATER.DESC: Polluted Water is dirty, unfiltered <link=\"WATER\">Water</link>.\n\nIt is not fit for consumption.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.DIRTYWATER.NAME: <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Polluted Water</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ELECTRUM.DESC: Electrum is a conductive <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> alloy composed of gold and silver.\n\nIt is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ELECTRUM.NAME: <link=\"ELECTRUM\">Electrum</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ENRICHEDURANIUM.DESC: (U) Enriched Uranium is a refined substance primarily used to <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> potent research reactors.\n\nIt becomes highly <link=\"RADIATION\">Radioactive</link> when consumed.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ENRICHEDURANIUM.NAME: <link=\"ENRICHEDURANIUM\">Enriched Uranium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ETHANOL.DESC: (C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>6</sub>O) Ethanol is an advanced chemical compound in a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.\n\nIt can be used as a highly effective fuel source when burned.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ETHANOL.NAME: <link=\"ETHANOL\">Ethanol</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ETHANOLGAS.DESC: (C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>6</sub>O) Ethanol Gas is an advanced chemical compound heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ETHANOLGAS.NAME: <link=\"ETHANOLGAS\">Ethanol Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FABRICATEDWOOD.DESC: Plywood is a good source of Heat and Power.\n\nIts insulation properties make it a useful Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FABRICATEDWOOD.NAME: <link=\"FABRICATEDWOOD\">Plywood</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FALLOUT.DESC: Nuclear Fallout is a highly toxic gas full of <link=\"RADIATION\">Radioactive Contaminants</link>. Condenses into <link=\"NUCLEARWASTE\">Liquid Nuclear Waste</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FALLOUT.NAME: <link=\"FALLOUT\">Nuclear Fallout</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FERTILIZER.DESC: Fertilizer is a processed mixture of biological nutrients.\n\nIt aids in the growth of certain <link=\"PLANTS\">Plants</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FERTILIZER.NAME: <link=\"FERTILIZER\">Fertilizer</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FOOLSGOLD.DESC: (FeS<sub>2</sub>) Pyrite is a conductive <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link>.\n\nAlso known as \"Fool's Gold\", is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FOOLSGOLD.NAME: <link=\"FOOLSGOLD\">Pyrite</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FOSSIL.DESC: Fossil is organic matter, highly compressed and hardened into a mineral state.\n\nIt is useful as a Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FOSSIL.NAME: <link=\"FOSSIL\">Fossil</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FROZENPHYTOOIL.DESC: Frozen Phyto Oil is thick, slippery <link=\"SLIME\">Slime</link> extract, frozen into a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FROZENPHYTOOIL.NAME: <link=\"FROZENPHYTOOIL\">Frozen Phyto Oil</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FULLERENE.DESC: (C<sub>60</sub>) Fullerene is a form of <link=\"CARBON\">Coal</link> consisting of spherical molecules.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.FULLERENE.NAME: <link=\"FULLERENE\">Fullerene</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GLASS.DESC: Glass is a brittle, transparent substance formed from <link=\"SAND\">Sand</link> fired at high temperatures.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GLASS.NAME: <link=\"GLASS\">Glass</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GOLD.DESC: (Au) Gold is a conductive precious <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link>.\n\nIt is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GOLD.NAME: <link=\"GOLD\">Gold</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GOLDAMALGAM.DESC: Gold Amalgam is a conductive amalgam of gold and mercury.\n\nIt is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GOLDAMALGAM.NAME: <link=\"GOLDAMALGAM\">Gold Amalgam</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GOLDGAS.DESC: (Au) Gold Gas is a conductive precious <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link>, heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GOLDGAS.NAME: <link=\"GOLDGAS\">Gold Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GRANITE.DESC: Granite is a dense composite of Igneous Rock.\n\nIt is useful as a Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GRANITE.NAME: <link=\"GRANITE\">Granite</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GRAPHITE.DESC: (C) Graphite is the most stable form of carbon.\n\nIt has high thermal conductivity and is useful as a Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GRAPHITE.NAME: <link=\"GRAPHITE\">Graphite</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GUNK.DESC: Solid Gunk is the built-up grime and grit produced by Duplicants' bionic mechanisms, which has been frozen into a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.GUNK.NAME: <link=\"GUNK\">Solid Gunk</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.HARDPOLYPROPYLENE.DESC: <link=\"HARDPOLYPROPYLENE\">Plastium</link> is an advanced thermoplastic polymer made from <link=\"TEMPCONDUCTORSOLID\">Thermium</link>, <link=\"POLYPROPYLENE\">Plastic</link> and <link=\"MILKFAT\">Brackwax</link>.\n\nIt is highly heat-resistant and suitable for use in space buildings.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.HARDPOLYPROPYLENE.NAME: <link=\"HARDPOLYPROPYLENE\">Plastium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.HELIUM.DESC: (He) Helium is an atomically lightweight, chemical <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.HELIUM.NAME: <link=\"HELIUM\">Helium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.HYDROGEN.DESC: (H) Hydrogen Gas is the universe's most common and atomically light element in a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.HYDROGEN.NAME: <link=\"HYDROGEN\">Hydrogen Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ICE.DESC: (H<sub>2</sub>O) Ice is clean water frozen into a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ICE.NAME: <link=\"ICE\">Ice</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.IGNEOUSROCK.DESC: Igneous Rock is a composite of solidified volcanic rock.\n\nIt is useful as a Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.IGNEOUSROCK.NAME: <link=\"IGNEOUSROCK\">Igneous Rock</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.IRIDIUM.DESC: (Ir) Iridium is a firm and highly conductive <link=\"METAL\">Metal</link> that can withstand extreme  <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.IRIDIUM.NAME: <link=\"IRIDIUM\">Iridium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.IRIDIUMGAS.DESC: (Ir) Iridium Gas is a highly conductive <link=\"METAL\">Metal</link> heated into a  <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.IRIDIUMGAS.NAME: <link=\"IRIDIUMGAS\">Iridium Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.IRON.NAME: <link=\"IRON\">Iron</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.IRONGAS.DESC: (Fe) Iron Gas is a common industrial <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link>, heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.IRONGAS.NAME: <link=\"IRONGAS\">Iron Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.IRONORE.DESC: (Fe) Iron Ore is a soft <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link>.\n\nIt is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.IRONORE.NAME: <link=\"IRONORE\">Iron Ore</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ISORESIN.DESC: Isosap is a crystallized sap composed of long-chain polymers.\n\nIt is used in the production of rare, high grade materials.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ISORESIN.NAME: <link=\"ISORESIN\">Isosap</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.KATAIRITE.DESC: (Ab) Abyssalite is a resilient, crystalline element.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.KATAIRITE.NAME: <link=\"KATAIRITE\">Abyssalite</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LEAD.DESC: (Pb) Lead is a soft yet extremely dense <link=\"REFINEDMETAL\">Refined Metal</link>.\n\nIt has a low Overheat Temperature and is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LEAD.NAME: <link=\"LEAD\">Lead</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LEADGAS.DESC: (Pb) Lead Gas is a soft yet extremely dense <link=\"REFINEDMETAL\">Refined Metal</link> heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LEADGAS.NAME: <link=\"LEADGAS\">Lead Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIME.DESC: (CaCO3) Lime is a mineral commonly found in Critter egg shells.\n\nIt is useful as a Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIME.NAME: <link=\"LIME\">Lime</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDCARBONDIOXIDE.DES: (CO<sub>2</sub>) Carbon Dioxide is an unbreathable chemical compound.\n\nThis selection is currently in a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDGUNK.DESC: Gunk is the built-up grime and grit produced by Duplicants' bionic mechanisms.\n\nIt is unpleasantly viscous.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDGUNK.NAME: <link=\"LIQUIDGUNK\">Gunk</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDHELIUM.DESC: (He) Helium is an atomically lightweight chemical element cooled into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDHELIUM.NAME: <link=\"LIQUIDHELIUM\">Helium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDHYDROGEN.DESC: (H) Hydrogen in its <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.\n\nIt freezes most substances that come into contact with it.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDHYDROGEN.NAME: <link=\"LIQUIDHYDROGEN\">Liquid Hydrogen</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDMETHANE.DESC: (CH<sub>4</sub>) Methane is an alkane.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDMETHANE.NAME: <link=\"LIQUIDMETHANE\">Liquid Methane</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDOXYGEN.DESC: (O<sub>2</sub>) Oxygen is a breathable chemical.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDOXYGEN.NAME: <link=\"LIQUIDOXYGEN\">Liquid Oxygen</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDPHOSPHORUS.DESC: (P) Phosphorus is a chemical element.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDPHOSPHORUS.NAME: <link=\"LIQUIDPHOSPHORUS\">Liquid Phosphorus</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDPROPANE.DESC:
(C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>8</sub>) Propane is an alkane.

This selection is in a <link="ELEMENTSLIQUID">Liquid</link> state.

It is useful in <link="POWER">Power</link> production.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDPROPANE.NAME: <link=\"LIQUIDPROPANE\">Liquid Propane</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDSULFUR.DESC: (S) Sulfur is a common chemical element and byproduct of <link=\"METHANE\">Natural Gas</link> production.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.LIQUIDSULFUR.NAME: <link=\"LIQUIDSULFUR\">Liquid Sulfur</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MAFICROCK.DESC: Mafic Rock is a variation of Igneous Rock that is rich in Iron.\n\nIt is useful as a Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MAFICROCK.NAME: <link=\"MAFICROCK\">Mafic Rock</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MAGMA.DESC: Magma is a composite of <link=\"IGNEOUSROCK\">Igneous Rock</link> heated into a molten, <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MAGMA.NAME: <link=\"MAGMA\">Magma</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MATERIAL_MODIFIERS.TOOL: This material will add {0} to the finished building's Decor
Buildings constructed from this material will have these properties

<style=\"KKeyword\">Excellent Radiation Shield</style> radiation has a hard time passing through materials with a high <style=\"KKeyword\">Radiation Absorption Factor</style> value. \n\nRadiation Absorption Factor: {1}

<style=\"KKeyword\">Slow Heating</style> materials require a large amount of energy to raise in <style=\"KKeyword\">Temperature</style>, and therefore heat and cool slowly\n\nSpecific Heat Capacity: {1} DTU to raise 1g by 1K

This material disperses Heat because energy transfers quickly through materials with high Thermal Conductivity Between two objects, the rate of Heat transfer will be determined by the object with the lowest Thermal Conductivity Thermal Conductivity: {1} W per degree K difference (Oxygen: 0.024 W)

<style=\"KKeyword\">Thermally Reactive</style> materials require little energy to raise in <style=\"KKeyword\">Temperature</style>, and therefore heat and cool quickly\n\nSpecific Heat Capacity: {1} DTU to raise 1g by 1K

This material retains Heat because energy transfers slowly through materials with low Thermal Conductivity Between two objects, the rate of Heat transfer will be determined by the object with the lowest Thermal Conductivity Thermal Conductivity: {1} W per degree K difference (Oxygen: 0.024 W)
This material will add {0} to the finished building's Overheat Temperature
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MERCURY.NAME: <link=\"MERCURY\">Mercury</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MERCURYGAS.DESC: (Hg) Mercury Gas is a <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MERCURYGAS.NAME: <link=\"MERCURYGAS\">Mercury Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.METHANE.DESC: Natural Gas is a mixture of various alkanes in a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.\n\nIt is useful in <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> production.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.METHANE.NAME: <link=\"METHANE\">Natural Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MILK.DESC: Brackene is a sodium-rich <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link>.\n\nIt is useful in <link=\"RANCHING\">Ranching</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MILK.NAME: <link=\"MILK\">Brackene</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MILKFAT.NAME: <link=\"MILKFAT\">Brackwax</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MILKICE.DESC: Frozen Brackene is <link=\"MILK\">Brackene</link> frozen into a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MILKICE.NAME: <link=\"MILKICE\">Frozen Brackene</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENALUMINUM.DESC: (Al) Molten Aluminum is a low density <link=\"REFINEDMETAL\">Metal</link> heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENALUMINUM.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENALUMINUM\">Molten Aluminum</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENCARBON.DESC: (C) Liquid Carbon is an abundant, versatile element heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENCARBON.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENCARBON\">Liquid Carbon</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENCOBALT.DESC: (Co) Molten Cobalt is a <link=\"REFINEDMETAL\">Refined Metal</link> heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENCOBALT.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENCOBALT\">Molten Cobalt</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENCOPPER.DESC: (Cu) Molten Copper is a conductive <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENCOPPER.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENCOPPER\">Molten Copper</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENGLASS.DESC: Molten Glass is a composite of granular rock, heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENGLASS.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENGLASS\">Molten Glass</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENGOLD.DESC: (Au) Gold, a conductive precious <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link>, heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENGOLD.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENGOLD\">Molten Gold</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENIRIDIUM.DESC: (Ir) Molten Iridium is a highly conductive <link=\"METAL\">Metal</link> heated to a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link>  state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENIRIDIUM.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENIRIDIUM\">Molten Iridium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENIRON.DESC: (Fe) Molten Iron is a common industrial <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENIRON.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENIRON\">Molten Iron</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENLEAD.DESC: (Pb) Lead is an extremely dense <link=\"REFINEDMETAL\">Refined Metal</link> heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENLEAD.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENLEAD\">Molten Lead</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENNICKEL.DESC: (Ni) Molten Nickel is a conductive <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENNICKEL.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENNICKEL\">Molten Nickel</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENNIOBIUM.DESC: (Nb) Molten Niobium is a rare metal heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENNIOBIUM.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENNIOBIUM\">Molten Niobium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENSALT.DESC: (NaCl) Molten Salt is an edible chemical compound that has been heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENSALT.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENSALT\">Molten Salt</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENSTEEL.DESC: Molten Steel is a <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> alloy of iron and carbon, heated into a hazardous <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENSTEEL.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENSTEEL\">Molten Steel</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENSUCROSE.DESC: (C<sub>12</sub>H<sub>22</sub>O<sub>11</sub>) Liquid Sucrose is the raw form of sugar, heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENSUCROSE.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENSUCROSE\">Liquid Sucrose</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENSYNGAS.DESC: Molten Synthesis Gas is an artificial, unbreathable <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link>.\n\nIt can be converted into an efficient fuel.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENSYNGAS.NAME: <link=\"SYNGAS\">Molten Synthesis Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENTUNGSTEN.DESC: (W) Molten Tungsten is a crystalline <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENTUNGSTEN.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENTUNGSTEN\">Molten Tungsten</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENTUNGSTENDISELENID: (WSe<sub>2</sub>) Tungsten Diselenide is an inorganic <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> compound heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENURANIUM.DESC: (U) Liquid Uranium is a highly <link=\"RADIATION\">Radioactive</link> substance, heated into a hazardous <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.\n\nIt is a byproduct of <link=\"ENRICHEDURANIUM\">Enriched Uranium</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MOLTENURANIUM.NAME: <link=\"MOLTENURANIUM\">Liquid Uranium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MUD.DESC: A mixture of <link=\"DIRT\">Dirt</link> and <link=\"WATER\">Water</link>.\n\nCan be separated into its base elements using a <link=\"SLUDGEPRESS\">Sludge Press</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.MUD.NAME: <link=\"MUD\">Mud</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NAPHTHA.DESC: Naphtha a distilled hydrocarbon mixture produced from the burning of <link=\"POLYPROPYLENE\">Plastic</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NAPHTHA.NAME: <link=\"NAPHTHA\">Liquid Naphtha</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NATURALRESIN.DESC: Resin is a viscous organic <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link>.\n\nIt can be treated to become <link=\"POLYPROPYLENE\">Plastic</link> in the <link=\"POLYMERIZER\">Polymer Press</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NATURALRESIN.NAME: <link=\"NATURALRESIN\">Resin</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NATURALSOLIDRESIN.DESC: Resin that has been cooled to a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.\n\nIt can be treated to become <link=\"POLYPROPYLENE\">Plastic</link> in the <link=\"POLYMERIZER\">Polymer Press</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NATURALSOLIDRESIN.NAME: <link=\"NATURALSOLIDRESIN\">Solid Resin</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NICKEL.DESC: (Ni) Nickel is a conductive <link=\"METAL\">Metal</link>.\n\nIt is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NICKEL.NAME: <link=\"NICKEL\">Nickel</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NICKELGAS.DESC: (Ni) Nickel Gas is a conductive <link=\"METAL\">Metal</link> heated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NICKELGAS.NAME: <link=\"NICKELGAS\">Nickel Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NICKELORE.DESC: (Ni) Nickel Ore is a conductive <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link>.\n\nIt can be refined into <link=\"NICKEL\">Nickel</link> and is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NICKELORE.NAME: <link=\"NICKELORE\">Nickel Ore</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NIOBIUM.DESC: (Nb) Niobium is a rare metal with many practical applications in metallurgy and superconductor <link=\"RESEARCH\">Research</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NIOBIUM.NAME: <link=\"NIOBIUM\">Niobium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NIOBIUMGAS.DESC: (Nb) Niobium Gas is a rare metal.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NIOBIUMGAS.NAME: <link=\"NIOBIUMGAS\">Niobium Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NUCLEARWASTE.DESC: Highly toxic liquid full of <link=\"RADIATION\">Radioactive Contaminants</link> which emit <link=\"RADIATION\">Radiation</link> that can be absorbed by <link=\"HIGHENERGYPARTICLESPAWNER\">Radbolt Generators</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.NUCLEARWASTE.NAME: <link=\"NUCLEARWASTE\">Liquid Nuclear Waste</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.OBSIDIAN.DESC: Obsidian is a brittle composite of volcanic <link=\"GLASS\">Glass</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.OBSIDIAN.NAME: <link=\"OBSIDIAN\">Obsidian</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.OXYGEN.DESC: (O<sub>2</sub>) Oxygen is an atomically lightweight and breathable <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link>, necessary for sustaining life.\n\nIt tends to rise above other gases.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.OXYGEN.NAME: <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.OXYROCK.DESC: (Ir<sub>3</sub>O<sub>2</sub>) Oxylite is a chemical compound that slowly emits breathable <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link>.\n\nExcavating <link=\"OXYROCK\">Oxylite</link> increases its emission rate, but depletes the ore more rapidly.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.OXYROCK.NAME: <link=\"OXYROCK\">Oxylite</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PEAT.DESC: Peat is a densely packed material made up of partially decomposed organic matter.\n\nIt is a combustible fuel, useful in <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> production.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PEAT.NAME: <link=\"PEAT\">Peat</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PETROLEUM.DESC: Petroleum is a <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> source refined from <link=\"CRUDEOIL\">Crude Oil</link>.\n\nIt is also an essential ingredient in the production of <link=\"POLYPROPYLENE\">Plastic</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PETROLEUM.NAME: <link=\"PETROLEUM\">Petroleum</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PHOSPHATENODULES.DESC: (PO<sup>3-</sup><sub>4</sub>) Nodules of sedimentary rock containing high concentrations of phosphate.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PHOSPHATENODULES.NAME: <link=\"PHOSPHATENODULES\">Phosphate Nodules</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PHOSPHORITE.DESC: Phosphorite is a composite of sedimentary rock, saturated with phosphate.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PHOSPHORITE.NAME: <link=\"PHOSPHORITE\">Phosphorite</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PHOSPHORUS.DESC: (P) Refined Phosphorus is a chemical element in its <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PHOSPHORUS.NAME: <link=\"PHOSPHORUS\">Refined Phosphorus</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PHOSPHORUSGAS.DESC: (P) Phosphorus Gas is the <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state of <link=\"PHOSPHORUS\">Refined Phosphorus</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PHOSPHORUSGAS.NAME: <link=\"PHOSPHORUSGAS\">Phosphorus Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PHYTOOIL.DESC: Phyto Oil is a thick, slippery <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> extracted from pureed <link=\"SLIME\">Slime</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PHYTOOIL.NAME: <link=\"PHYTOOIL\">Phyto Oil</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.POLYPROPYLENE.BUILD_DES: Buildings made of this <link=\"POLYPROPYLENE\">Plastic</link> have antiseptic properties
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.POLYPROPYLENE.DESC: (C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>6</sub>)<sub>n</sub> <link=\"POLYPROPYLENE\">Plastic</link> is a thermoplastic polymer.\n\nIt is useful for constructing a variety of advanced buildings and equipment.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.POLYPROPYLENE.NAME: <link=\"POLYPROPYLENE\">Plastic</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PONDSCUM.DESC: Pondscum is a soft, naturally occurring composite of biological nutrients.\n\nIt may be processed into <link=\"FERTILIZER\">Fertilizer</link> and aids in the growth of certain <link=\"PLANTS\">Plants</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PONDSCUM.NAME: <link=\"PONDSCUM\">Pondscum</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PROPANE.DESC:
(C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>8</sub>) Propane Gas is a natural alkane.

This selection is in a <link="ELEMENTSGAS">Gaseous</link> state.

It is useful in <link="POWER">Power</link> production.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.PROPANE.NAME: <link=\"PROPANE\">Propane Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.RADIUM.DESC: (Ra) Radium is a <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link> emitting radioactive substance.\n\nIt is useful as a <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> source.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.RADIUM.NAME: <link=\"RADIUM\">Radium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.REFINEDCARBON.DESC: (C) Refined carbon is solid element purified from raw <link=\"CARBON\">Coal</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.REFINEDCARBON.NAME: <link=\"REFINEDCARBON\">Refined Carbon</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.REFINEDLIPID.DESC: Biodiesel is a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> composed of highly processed fatty acids derived from purified natural oils.\n\nIts <link=\"COMBUSTIBLELIQUID\">combustibility</link> makes it useful for <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> production.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.REFINEDLIPID.NAME: <link=\"REFINEDLIPID\">Biodiesel</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.REGOLITH.DESC: Regolith is a sandy substance composed of the various particles that collect atop terrestrial objects.\n\nIt is useful as a <link=\"FILTER\">Filtration Medium</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.REGOLITH.NAME: <link=\"REGOLITH\">Regolith</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.RESIN.DESC: Sticky goo harvested from a grumpy tree.\n\nIt can be polymerized into <link=\"ISORESIN\">Isosap</link> by boiling away its excess moisture.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.RESIN.NAME: <link=\"RESIN\">Sap</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ROCKGAS.DESC: Rock Gas is rock that has been superheated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.ROCKGAS.NAME: <link=\"ROCKGAS\">Rock Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.RUST.DESC: Rust is an iron oxide that forms from the breakdown of <link=\"IRON\">Iron</link>.\n\nIt is useful in some <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link> production processes.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.RUST.NAME: <link=\"RUST\">Rust</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SALT.DESC: (NaCl) Salt, also known as sodium chloride, is an edible chemical compound.\n\nWhen refined, it can be eaten with meals to increase Duplicant <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SALT.NAME: <link=\"SALT\">Salt</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SALTGAS.DESC: (NaCl) Salt Gas is an edible chemical compound that has been superheated into a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SALTGAS.NAME: <link=\"SALTGAS\">Salt Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SALTWATER.DESC: Salt Water is a natural, lightly concentrated solution of <link=\"SALT\">Salt</link> dissolved in <link=\"WATER\">Water</link>.\n\nIt can be used in desalination processes, separating out usable salt.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SALTWATER.NAME: <link=\"SALTWATER\">Salt Water</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SAND.DESC: Sand is a composite of granular rock.\n\nIt is useful as a <link=\"FILTER\">Filtration Medium</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SAND.NAME: <link=\"SAND\">Sand</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SANDCEMENT.NAME: <link=\"SANDCEMENT\">Sand Cement</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SANDSTONE.DESC: Sandstone is a composite of relatively soft sedimentary rock.\n\nIt is useful as a Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SANDSTONE.NAME: <link=\"SANDSTONE\">Sandstone</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SEDIMENTARYROCK.DESC: Sedimentary Rock is a hardened composite of sediment layers.\n\nIt is useful as a Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SEDIMENTARYROCK.NAME: <link=\"SEDIMENTARYROCK\">Sedimentary Rock</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SHALE.DESC: Shale is a brittle composite of sediment layers.\n\nIt is useful as a Construction Material.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SHALE.NAME: <link=\"SHALE\">Shale</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SLABS.DESC: Slabs are a refined mineral building block used for assembling advanced buildings.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SLABS.NAME: <link=\"SLABS\">Building Slab</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SLIMEMOLD.DESC: Slime is a thick biomixture of algae, fungi, and mucopolysaccharides.\n\nIt can be distilled into <link=\"ALGAE\">Algae</link> and emits <link=\"CONTAMINATEDOXYGEN\">Polluted Oxygen</link> once dug up.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SLIMEMOLD.NAME: <link=\"SLIMEMOLD\">Slime</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SNOW.DESC: (H<sub>2</sub>O) Snow is a mass of loose, crystalline ice particles.\n\nIt becomes <link=\"WATER\">Water</link> when melted.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SNOW.NAME: <link=\"SNOW\">Snow</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDCARBONDIOXIDE.DESC: (CO<sub>2</sub>) Carbon Dioxide is an unbreathable compound in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDCARBONDIOXIDE.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDCARBONDIOXIDE\">Solid Carbon Dioxide</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDCHLORINE.DESC: (Cl) Chlorine is a natural <link=\"DISEASE\">Germ</link>-killing element in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDCHLORINE.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDCHLORINE\">Solid Chlorine</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDCRUDEOIL.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDCRUDEOIL\">Solid Crude Oil</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDETHANOL.DESC: (C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>6</sub>O) Solid Ethanol is an advanced chemical compound.\n\nIt can be used as a highly effective fuel source when burned.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDETHANOL.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDETHANOL\">Solid Ethanol</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDHYDROGEN.DESC: (H) Solid Hydrogen is the universe's most common element in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDHYDROGEN.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDHYDROGEN\">Solid Hydrogen</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDMERCURY.DESC: (Hg) Mercury is a rare <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDMERCURY.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDMERCURY\">Mercury</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDMETHANE.DESC: (CH<sub>4</sub>) Methane is an alkane in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDMETHANE.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDMETHANE\">Solid Methane</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDNAPHTHA.DESC: Naphtha is a distilled hydrocarbon mixture in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDNAPHTHA.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDNAPHTHA\">Solid Naphtha</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDNUCLEARWASTE.DESC: Highly toxic solid full of <link=\"RADIATION\">Radioactive Contaminants</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDNUCLEARWASTE.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDNUCLEARWASTE\">Solid Nuclear Waste</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDOXYGEN.DESC: (O<sub>2</sub>) Solid Oxygen is a breathable element in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDOXYGEN.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDOXYGEN\">Solid Oxygen</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDPETROLEUM.DESC: Petroleum is a <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> source.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDPETROLEUM.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDPETROLEUM\">Solid Petroleum</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDPROPANE.DESC: (C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>8</sub>) Solid Propane is a natural gas in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDPROPANE.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDPROPANE\">Solid Propane</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDRESIN.DESC: Solidified goo harvested from a grumpy tree.\n\nIt is used in the production of <link=\"ISORESIN\">Isosap</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDRESIN.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDRESIN\">Solid Sap</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDSUPERCOOLANT.DESC: Super Coolant is an industrial-grade <link=\"FULLERENE\">Fullerene</link> coolant.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDSUPERCOOLANT.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDSUPERCOOLANT\">Solid Super Coolant</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDSYNGAS.DESC: Solid Synthesis Gas is an artificial, unbreathable <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link>.\n\nIt can be converted into an efficient fuel.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDSYNGAS.NAME: <link=\"SYNGAS\">Solid Synthesis Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDVISCOGEL.DESC: Visco-Gel is a polymer that has high surface tension when in <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> form.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOLIDVISCOGEL.NAME: <link=\"SOLIDVISCOGEL\">Solid Visco-Gel</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOURGAS.DESC: Sour Gas is a hydrocarbon <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link> containing high concentrations of hydrogen sulfide.\n\nIt is a byproduct of highly heated <link=\"PETROLEUM\">Petroleum</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SOURGAS.NAME: <link=\"SOURGAS\">Sour Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.STABLESNOW.DESC: (H<sub>2</sub>O) Snow is a mass of loose, crystalline ice particles.\n\nIt becomes <link=\"WATER\">Water</link> when melted.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.STABLESNOW.NAME: Packed <link=\"SNOW\">Snow</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.STEAM.DESC: (H<sub>2</sub>O) Steam is <link=\"WATER\">Water</link> that has been heated into a scalding <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.STEAM.NAME: <link=\"STEAM\">Steam</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.STEEL.DESC: Steel is a <link=\"REFINEDMETAL\">Metal Alloy</link> composed of iron and carbon.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.STEEL.NAME: <link=\"STEEL\">Steel</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.STEELGAS.DESC: Steel Gas is a superheated <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link> composed of iron and carbon.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.STEELGAS.NAME: <link=\"STEELGAS\">Steel Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SUCROSE.DESC: (C<sub>12</sub>H<sub>22</sub>O<sub>11</sub>) Sucrose is the raw form of sugar.\n\nIt can be used for cooking higher-quality <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SUCROSE.NAME: <link=\"SUCROSE\">Sucrose</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SUGARWATER.DESC: Nectar is a natural, lightly concentrated solution of <link=\"SUCROSE\">Sucrose</link> dissolved in <link=\"WATER\">Water</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SUGARWATER.NAME: <link=\"SUGARWATER\">Nectar</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SULFUR.DESC: (S) Sulfur is a common chemical element and byproduct of <link=\"METHANE\">Natural Gas</link> production.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SULFUR.NAME: <link=\"SULFUR\">Sulfur</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SULFURGAS.DESC: (S) Sulfur is a common chemical element and byproduct of <link=\"METHANE\">Natural Gas</link> production.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SULFURGAS.NAME: <link=\"SULFURGAS\">Sulfur Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SUPERCOOLANT.DESC: Super Coolant is an industrial-grade coolant that utilizes the unusual energy states of <link=\"FULLERENE\">Fullerene</link>.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">Liquid</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SUPERCOOLANT.NAME: <link=\"SUPERCOOLANT\">Super Coolant</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SUPERCOOLANTGAS.DESC: Super Coolant is an industrial-grade <link=\"FULLERENE\">Fullerene</link> coolant.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SUPERCOOLANTGAS.NAME: <link=\"SUPERCOOLANTGAS\">Super Coolant Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SUPERINSULATOR.DESC: Insulite reduces <link=\"HEAT\">Heat Transfer</link> and is composed of recrystallized <link=\"KATAIRITE\">Abyssalite</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SUPERINSULATOR.NAME: <link=\"SUPERINSULATOR\">Insulite</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SYNGAS.DESC: Synthesis Gas is an artificial, unbreathable <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link>.\n\nIt can be converted into an efficient fuel.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.SYNGAS.NAME: <link=\"SYNGAS\">Synthesis Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TALLOW.DESC: A chunk of raw grease that can be used in <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link> production or industrial processes.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TALLOW.NAME: <link=\"TALLOW\">Tallow</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TEMPCONDUCTORSOLID.DESC: Thermium is an industrial metal alloy formulated to maximize <link=\"HEAT\">Heat Transfer</link> and thermal dispersion.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TEMPCONDUCTORSOLID.NAME: <link=\"TEMPCONDUCTORSOLID\">Thermium</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TESTELEMENT.DESC: ((Fe,Mn)WO<sub>4</sub>) Wolframite is a dense Metallic element in a <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> state.\n\nIt is a source of <link=\"TUNGSTEN\">Tungsten</link> and is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TESTELEMENT.NAME: <link=\"TESTELEMENT\">Test Element</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TOXICMUD.DESC: A mixture of <link=\"TOXICSAND\">Polluted Dirt</link> and <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Polluted Water</link>.\n\nCan be separated into its base elements using a <link=\"SLUDGEPRESS\">Sludge Press</link>.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TOXICMUD.NAME: <link=\"TOXICMUD\">Polluted Mud</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TOXICSAND.DESC: Polluted Dirt is unprocessed biological waste.\n\nIt emits <link=\"CONTAMINATEDOXYGEN\">Polluted Oxygen</link> over time.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TOXICSAND.NAME: <link=\"TOXICSAND\">Polluted Dirt</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TUNGSTEN.DESC: (W) Tungsten is an extremely tough crystalline <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link>.\n\nIt is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TUNGSTEN.NAME: <link=\"TUNGSTEN\">Tungsten</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TUNGSTENDISELENIDE.DESC: (WSe<sub>2</sub>) Tungsten Diselenide is an inorganic <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> compound with a crystalline structure.\n\nIt is suitable for building <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> systems.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TUNGSTENDISELENIDE.NAME: <link=\"TUNGSTENDISELENIDE\">Tungsten Diselenide</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TUNGSTENDISELENIDEGAS.D: (WSe<sub>2</sub>) Tungsten Diselenide Gasis a superheated <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link> compound in a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TUNGSTENGAS.DESC: (W) Tungsten is a superheated crystalline <link=\"RAWMETAL\">Metal</link>.\n\nThis selection is in a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.TUNGSTENGAS.NAME: <link=\"TUNGSTENGAS\">Tungsten Gas</link>
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.UNOBTANIUM.DESC: (Nt) Neutronium is a mysterious and extremely resilient element.\n\nIt cannot be excavated by any Duplicant mining tool.
STRINGS.ELEMENTS.UNOBTANIUM.NAME: <link=\"UNOBTANIUM\">Neutronium</link>

STRINGS.GAMEPLAY_EVENTS.BONUS.BONUSALGAE: {dupe}'s recent proximity to an Algae Terrarium has left them feeling refreshed and exuberant and is correlated to an increase in their physical attributes. It is unclear whether these physical improvements came from the excess of oxygen or the invigorating smell of algae.\n\nIt's curious that I find myself nostalgic for the smell of algae growing in a lab. But how could this be...?
STRINGS.GAMEPLAY_EVENTS.BONUS.BONUSBUILD: {dupe} has been hard at work building many structures crucial to the future of the colony. It seems this activity has improved this Duplicant's budding construction and mechanical skills beyond what my models predicted.\n\nWhether this increase in ability is due to them learning new skills or simply gaining self-confidence I cannot say, but this unexpected development is a welcome surprise development.
STRINGS.GAMEPLAY_EVENTS.BONUS.BONUSDIGGI:
Some interesting data has revealed that {dupe} has had a marked increase in physical abilities, an increase that cannot entirely be attributed to the usual improvements that occur after regular physical activity.

Based on previous observations this Duplicant's positive associations with digging appear to account for this additional physical boost.

This would mean the personal preferences of my Duplicants are directly correlated to how hard they work. How interesting...
The act of closing a door has apparently lead to a decrease in the <link=\"STRESS\">Stress</link> levels of {dupe}, as well as decreased the exposure of this Duplicant to harmful <link=\"GERMS\">Germs</link>.\n\nWhile it may be more efficient to group all my Duplicants together in common sleeping quarters, it's important to remember the mental benefits to privacy and space to express their individuality.
STRINGS.GAMEPLAY_EVENTS.BONUS.BONUSDREAM: Improving the living conditions of {dupe} will lead to more good dreams.

I've observed many improvements to {dupe}'s demeanor today. Analysis indicates unusually high amounts of dopamine in their system. There's a good chance this is due to an exceptionally good dream and analysis indicates that current sleeping conditions may have contributed to this occurrence.\n\nFurther improvements to sleeping conditions may have additional positive effects to the <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link> of {dupe} and other Duplicants.

{dupe} had another really good dream and the resulting release of dopamine has made this Duplicant energetic and full of possibilities! This is an encouraging byproduct of improving the living conditions of the colony.\n\nBased on these observations, building a better sleeping area for my Duplicants will have a similar effect on their <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.

I have detected a distinct spring in {dupe}'s step today. There is a good chance that this Duplicant had another great dream last night. Such incidents are further indications that working on the care and comfort of the colony is not a waste of time.\n\nI do wonder though: What do Duplicants dream of?

{dupe}'s dream last night must have been simply amazing! Their dopamine levels are at an all time high. Based on these results, it can be safely assumed that improving the living conditions of my Duplicants will reduce <link=\"STRESS\">Stress</link> and have similar positive effects on their well-being.\n\nObservations such as this are an integral and enjoyable part of science. When I see my Duplicants happy, I can't help but share in some of their joy.
STRINGS.GAMEPLAY_EVENTS.BONUS.BONUSGENER: {dupe} ran in a Manual Generator and the physical activity appears to have given this Duplicant increased strength and sense of well-being.\n\nWhile not the primary reason for building Manual Generators, I am very pleased to see my Duplicants reaping the <link=\"STRESS\">Stress</link> relieving benefits to physical activity.
STRINGS.GAMEPLAY_EVENTS.BONUS.BONUSHITTH: {dupe}'s recent Research errand has resulted in a significant increase to this Duplicant's brain activity. The discovery of newly found knowledge has given {dupe} an invigorating jolt of excitement.\n\nI am all too familiar with this feeling.
STRINGS.GAMEPLAY_EVENTS.BONUS.BONUSLITWO: {dupe}'s recent time in a well-lit area has greatly improved this Duplicant's ability to work with, and on, machinery.\n\nThis supports the prevailing theory that a well-lit workspace has many benefits beyond just improving my Duplicant's ability to see.
STRINGS.GAMEPLAY_EVENTS.BONUS.BONUSOXYGE: {dupe} is experiencing a sudden unexpected improvement to their physical prowess which appears to be a result of exposure to elevated levels of oxygen from passing by an Oxygen Diffuser.\n\nObservations such as this are important in documenting just how beneficial having access to oxygen is to my colony.
STRINGS.GAMEPLAY_EVENTS.BONUS.BONUSRESEA: Analysis indicates that the appearance of a <style=\"KKeyword\">Research Station</style> has inspired {dupe} and heightened their brain activity on a cellular level.\n\nBrain stimulation is important if my Duplicants are going to adapt and innovate in their increasingly harsh environment.
STRINGS.GAMEPLAY_EVENTS.BONUS.BONUSSTORA: Data indicates that {dupe}'s activity in storing something in a Storage Bin has led to an increase in this Duplicant's physical strength as well as an overall improvement to their general demeanor.\n\nThere have been many studies connecting organization with an increase in well-being. It is possible this explains {dupe}'s <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link> improvements.
STRINGS.GAMEPLAY_EVENTS.BONUS.BONUSTALKE: {dupe}'s recent conversation with another Duplicant shows a correlation to improved serotonin and <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link> levels in this Duplicant. It is very possible that small talk with a co-worker, however short and seemingly insignificant, will make my Duplicant's feel connected to the colony as a whole.\n\nAs the colony gets bigger and more sophisticated, I must ensure that the opportunity for such connections continue, for the good of my Duplicants' mental well being.
STRINGS.GAMEPLAY_EVENTS.BONUS.BONUSTOILE: {dupe} recently visited an Outhouse and appears to have appreciated the small comforts based on the marked increase to their <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.\n\nHigh <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link> has been linked to a better work ethic and greater enthusiasm for complex jobs, which are essential in building a successful new colony.

{dupe} used a Lavatory and analysis shows a decided improvement to this Duplicant's <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.\n\nAs my colony grows and expands, it's important not to ignore the benefits of giving my Duplicants a pleasant place to relieve themselves.

{dupe} visited a Latrine and experienced luxury unlike they anything this Duplicant had previously experienced as analysis has revealed yet another boost to their <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>.\n\nIt is unclear whether this development is a result of increased hygiene or whether there is something else inherently about working plumbing which would improve <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link> in this way. Further analysis is needed.

{dupe} visited a Washroom and the experience has left this Duplicant with significantly improved <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>. Analysis indicates this improvement should continue for many cycles.\n\nThe relationship of my Duplicants and their surroundings is an interesting aspect of colony life. I should continue to watch future developments in this department closely.

THIS EVENT IS NOT WORKING
{host} is throwing a birthday party for {dupe}. Make sure there is an available Recreation Room for the party.

I could send a Duplicant through safely if I desired.

STRINGS.LORE.BUILDINGS.Desk.ENTRY:
TO: JSTERN@GRAVITASFACILITY.NOVA
FROM: EJONES@GRAVITASFACILITY.NOVA
SUBJECT: Preliminary Calculations

Director,

Even with dramatic optimization we can't make the sheer volume of resources required to sustain a colony seed fit for even a small interplanetary travel duration. We'll need to consider serious changes if this is going to work.

E Jones
Information and Statistics Department
The Gravitas Facility
STRINGS.LORE.BUILDINGS.GeneShuffler.ENTR: "--fascinating that memories are not already inherent in our subjects; however, none as of yet have shown signs of recognition when introduced to familiar stimuli." "Refer to Experiment 7D." "Refer to Experiment 7F." "Memories must be embedded within the physical brainmaps of our subjects. The only question that remains is--"

STRINGS.LORE.BUILDINGS.PropLocker.ENTRY:
To all employees;

The facility is pleased to announced that starting this week, all Fridays will now be Casual Fridays!

Please enjoy the clinically proven destressing benefits of casual attire by wearing your favorite shirt to the lab.

NOTE: Any personnel found on facility premises without regulation fullbody protection will be put on immediate notice.

Thank-you and have fun!
-Admin
STRINGS.LORE.BUILDINGS.SET_LOCKER1.ENTRY:
FIRST LAW
Energy can neither be created or destroyed, only change forms.

SECOND LAW
Entropy in an isolated system that is not in equilibrium tends to increase over time, approaching the maximum value at equilibrium.

THIRD LAW
Entropy in a system approaches a constant minimum as temperature approaches absolute zero.

ZEROTH LAW
If two thermodynamic systems are in thermal equilibrium with a third, then they are in thermal equilibrium with each other.
STRINGS.LORE.BUILDINGS.SET_LOCKER2.ENTRY: A powerful stench emanates from this locker.
STRINGS.LORE.BUILDINGS.SET_OBJECT.BODY.C: Reminder to All Personnel! From: Admin TO: All ------------------ To all employees; The Gravitas Facility does not officially host a "Bring Your Child To Work Day" office event. We ask that personnel please do not bring children into top secret research departments, and especially that they do not let said children play with the high velocity particle accelerators. We thank you for your understanding.
STRINGS.LORE.BUILDINGS.SET_OBJECT.TITLE: Reminder to Staff
STRINGS.LORE.BUILDINGS.VendingMachine.EN:
TO: ALL
FROM: ADMIN@GRAVITASFACILITY.NOVA
SUBJECT: Unattended Cultures

For the health and safety of your fellow Facility employees, please do not store unlabeled bacterial cultures in the cafeteria fridge.
Similarly, be advised that the cafeteria dishwasher is incapable of handling petri "dishes", despite the nomenclature.

We thank you for your consideration.
-The Gravitas Facility

STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.MORALE.MESSAG:
Food, Rooms, Decor, and Recreation all have an effect on Duplicant Morale. Good experiences improve their Morale, while poor experiences lower it. When a Duplicant's Morale is below their Expectations, they will become Stressed.

Duplicants' Expectations will get higher as they are given new Skills, and the colony will have to be improved to keep up their Morale. An overview of Morale and Stress can be viewed on the Vitals screen.

Related <link="MISCELLANEOUSTIPS">Tutorial: Stress Management</link>

STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.PLUMBING.MESS:
When connecting pipes for plumbing, it is useful to have the Plumbing Overlay {Hotkey/Overlay6} selected. Each building which requires plumbing must have their Building Intake connected to the Output Pipe from a source such as a Liquid Pump. Liquid Pumps must be submerged in liquid and attached to a power source to function.

Buildings often output contaminated water which must flow out of the building through piping from the Output Pipe. The water can then be expelled through a Liquid Vent, or filtered through a Water Sieve for reuse.

Ventilation applies the same principles to gases. Select the Ventilation Overlay {Hotkey/Overlay7} to see how gases are being moved around the colony.
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.PLUMBING.NAME: Video: Plumbing and Ventilation
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.PLUMBING.TOOL: Notes on connecting buildings with pipes

STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.POWER.MESSAGE:
Generators are considered "Producers" of Power, while the various buildings and machines in the colony are considered "Consumers". Each Consumer will pull a certain wattage from the power circuit it is connected to, which can be checked at any time by (ClickType/clicking) the building and going to the Energy Tab.

I can use the Power Overlay {Hotkey/Overlay2} to quickly check the status of all my circuits. If the Consumers are taking more wattage than the Generators are creating, the Batteries will drain and there will be brownouts.

Additionally, if the Consumers are pulling more wattage through the Wires than the Wires can handle, they will overload and burn out. To correct both these situations, I will need to reorganize my Consumers onto separate circuits.
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.POWER.NAME: Video: Power Circuits
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.PRIORITIESMES: Duplicants will choose where to work based on the priority of the errands that I give them. I can open the Priorities Screen {Hotkey/ManagePriorities} to set their Duplicant Priorities, and the Priority Tool {Hotkey/Prioritize} to fine tune Building Priority. Many buildings will also let me change their Priority level when I select them.
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.RADIATION.MES: Objects such as Uranium Ore and Beeta Hives emit a Radioactive energy that can be toxic to my Duplicants.\n\nI can use the Radiation Overlay {Hotkey/Overlay15} to check the scope of the Radiation field. Building thick walls around radiation emitters will dampen the field and protect my Duplicants from getting Radiation Sickness.

STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.SLIPPERYSURFA: My Duplicants may slip and fall on wet surfaces, and Duplicants with bionic systems can experience disruptive glitching.\n\nI can help my colony avoid undue Stress and potential injury by using the Mop Tool {Hotkey/Mop} to clean up spills. Building Toilets and Gunk Extractors can help minimize the incidence of spills.
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.SPACETRAVEL.M: Building a rocket first requires constructing a <link=\"LAUNCHPAD\">Rocket Platform</link> and adding modules from the menu. All components of the Rocket Checklist will need to be complete before being capable of launching.\n\nA <link=\"CLUSTERTELESCOPE\">Telescope</link> needs to be built on the surface of a Planetoid in order to use the <style=\"KKeyword\">Starmap Screen</style> {Hotkey/ManageStarmap} to see and set course for new destinations.
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.STRESSMANAGEM:
At 100% <link="STRESS">Stress</link>, a Duplicant will have a nervous breakdown and be unable to work.

Breakdowns can manifest in different colony-threatening ways, such as the destruction of buildings or the binge eating of food.

I can help my Duplicants manage stressful situations by giving them access to good <link="FOOD">Food</link>, fancy <link="DECOR">Decor</link> and comfort items which boost their <link="MORALE">Morale</link>.

I can select a Duplicant and mouse over <link="STRESS">Stress</link> or <link="MORALE">Morale</link> in their CONDITION TAB to view current statuses, and hopefully manage things before they become a problem.

Related <link="VIDEOS13">Video: Duplicant Morale</link>
Notes on keeping Duplicants happy and productive
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.STRUCTURALDAM: These buildings' structural integrity has been compromised
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.SUITS.MESSAGE: <link=\"ATMOSUIT\">Atmo Suits</link> can be equipped to protect my Duplicants from environmental hazards like extreme <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link>, airborne <link=\"DISEASE\">Germs</link>, or unbreathable <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gas</link>. In order to utilize these suits, I'll need to hook up an <link=\"SUITLOCKER\">Atmo Suit Dock</link> to an <link=\"SUITMARKER\">Atmo Suit Checkpoint</link> , then store one of the suits inside.\n\nDuplicants will equip a suit when they walk past the checkpoint in the chosen direction, and will unequip their suit when walking back the opposite way.
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.SUITS.NAME: Tutorial: Atmo Suits
An exosuit was dropped because there were no empty docks available
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.TASKPRIORITIE: Duplicants always perform errands in order of highest to lowest priority. They will harvest Food before they build, for example, or always build new structures before they mine materials.\n\nI can open the Priorities Screen {Hotkey/ManagePriorities} to set which Errand Types Duplicants may or may not perform, or to specialize skilled Duplicants for particular Errand Types.
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.THERMALCOMFOR: Environments that are extremely Hot or Cold affect my Duplicants' internal body temperature and cause undue Stress or unscheduled naps. Opening the Temperature Overlay {Hotkey/Overlay3} and checking the Thermal Tolerance box allows me to view all areas where my Duplicants will feel discomfort and be unable to regulate their internal body temperature. Related Video: Insulation
Notes on helping Duplicants keep their cool
Falling material fell on these Duplicants and displaced them:
STRINGS.MISC.NOTIFICATIONS.TUTORIAL_OVER: When constructing buildings, I should always take note of their Overheat Temperature and plan their locations accordingly. Maintaining low ambient temperatures and good ventilation in the colony will also help keep building temperatures down. The Relative Temperature slider tool in the Temperature Overlay {Hotkey/Overlay3} allows me to change adjust the overlay's color-coding in order to highlight specific temperature ranges. If I allow buildings to exceed their Overheat Temperature they will begin to take damage, and if left unattended, they will break down and be unusable until repaired.
Notes on preventing building from breaking

STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.BUILDABLERAW_DESC: Raw minerals are the unrefined forms of organic solids. Almost all raw minerals can be processed in the <link=\"ROCKCRUSHER\">Rock Crusher</link>, although a handful require the use of the <link=\"SUPERMATERIALREFINERY\">Molecular Forge</link>.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.BUILDINGFIBER_DESC: Fibers are organically sourced polymers which are both sturdy and sensorially pleasant, making them suitable in the construction of <link=\"MORALE\">Morale</link>-boosting buildings.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.BUILDINGWOOD_DESC: Wood is a renewable building material which can also be used as a valuable source of fuel and electricity when refined at the <link=\"WOODGASGENERATOR\">Wood Burner</link> or the <link=\"ETHANOLDISTILLERY\">Ethanol Distiller</link>.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.COMBUSTIBLEGAS_DESC: Combustible Gases can be burned as fuel to be used in the production of <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> and <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link>.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.COMBUSTIBLELIQUID_DESC: Combustible Liquids can be burned as fuels to be used in energy production, such as in a <link=\"PETROLEUMGENERATOR\">Petroleum Generator</link> or a <link=\"KEROSENEENGINECLUSTER\">Petroleum Engine</link>.\n\nThough these liquids have other uses, such as fertilizer for growing a <link=\"BEANPLANTSEED\">Nosh Bean</link>, their primary usefulness lies in their ability to be burned for <link=\"POWER\">Power</link>.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.COMBUSTIBLESOLID_DESC: Combustible Solids can be burned as fuel to be used in <link=\"POWER\">Power</link> production.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.COMPOSTABLE_DESC:
Compostables are biological materials which can be put into a <link="COMPOST">Compost</link> to generate clean <link="DIRT">Dirt</link>.

Composting also generates a small amount of <link="HEAT">Heat</link>.

Once it starts to rot, consumable food should be composted to prevent <link="FOODPOISONING">Food Poisoning</link>.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.FARMABLE_DESC: Cultivable soil is a fundamental building block of basic agricultural systems and can also be useful in the production of clean <link=\"OXYGEN\">Oxygen</link>.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.FILTER_DESC: Filtration mediums are materials used to separate purified <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">gases</link> or <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">liquids</link> from their polluted forms.\n\nThey are consumables that will be transformed by the filtering process. For example, <link=\"SAND\">Sand</link> that has been used to filter <link=\"DIRTYWATER\">Polluted Water</link> will become <link=\"TOXICSAND\">Polluted Dirt</link>.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.FOSSILS_DESC: Fossil is a category of composite rocks and minerals that contain traces of petrified lifeforms.\n\nThey have varied uses as basic building materials, sculpting blocks, or raw ingredients in the production of higher-grade materials.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.ICEORE_DESC:
Ice is a class of materials made up mostly (if not completely) of <link="WATER">Water</link> in a frozen or partially frozen form.

As a material in a frigid solid or semi-solid state, these elements are very useful as a low-cost way to cool the environment around them.

When heated, ice will melt into its original liquified form (ie.<link="BRINEICE">Brine Ice</link> will liquify into <link="BRINE">Brine</link>). Each ice element has a different freezing and melting point based upon its composition and state.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.INSULATOR_DESC: Insulators have low thermal conductivity, and effectively reduce the speed at which <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link> is transferred through them.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.LUBRICATINGOIL_DESC: Gear oils are lubricating fluids useful in the maintenance of complex machinery, protecting gear systems from damage and minimizing friction between moving parts to support optimal performance.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.METAL_DESC:
Metal ore is the raw form of metal, and has a wide variety of practical applications in electronics and general construction.

Metal ore is typically processed into <link="REFINEDMETAL">Refined Metal</link> using the <link="ROCKCRUSHER">Rock Crusher</link> or the <link="METALREFINERY">Metal Refinery</link>.

Some rare metal ores can also be refined in the <link="SUPERMATERIALREFINERY">Molecular Forge</link>.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.ORGANICS_DESC: Organic materials are useful ingredients gathered from the environment, harvested from <link=\"PLANTS\">plants</link> or derived from <link=\"CREATURES\">critters</link>.\n\nSome, not all, require additional processing before they can be used.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.PLASTIC_DESC: Plastics are synthetic <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solids</link> that are pliable and minimize the transfer of <link=\"HEAT\">Heat</link>. They typically have a low melting point, although more advanced plastics have been developed to circumvent this issue.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.PLASTIFIABLELIQUID_DES: Plastic monomers are organic compounds that can be processed into <link=\"PLASTIC\">Plastics</link> that have valuable applications as advanced building materials.\n\nPlastics derived from these monomers can also be used as packaging materials for <link=\"FOOD\">Food</link> preservation.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.PRECIOUSROCK_DESC: Precious rocks are raw minerals. Their extreme hardness produces durable <link=\"DECOR\">Decor</link>.\n\nSome precious rocks are inherently attractive even in their natural, unfinished form.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.REFINEDMETAL_DESC: Refined metals are purified forms of metal often used in higher-tier electronics due to their tendency to be able to withstand higher temperatures when they are made into wires. Other benefits include the increased decor value for some metals which can greatly improve the well-being of a colony.\n\nMetal ore can be refined in either the <link=\"ROCKCRUSHER\">Rock Crusher</link> or the <link=\"METALREFINERY\">Metal Refinery</link>.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.REMOTEOPERABLE_DESC: These buildings can be operated from a distance by a <link=\"REMOTEWORKTERMINAL\">Remote Controller</link> so long as they are built within range of a <link=\"REMOTEWORKERDOCK\">Remote Worker Dock</link>.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.SLIPPERY_DESC: Some <link=\"ELEMENTSLIQUID\">liquids</link> and <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">solids</link> have a remarkably low coefficient of friction. These present a safety hazard if left on the ground, as Duplicants may slip and fall when traveling across them.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.SUBLIMATING_DESC: Sublimators are a class of <link=\"ELEMENTSSOLID\">Solid</link> elements that passively convert to a <link=\"ELEMENTSGAS\">Gaseous</link> state. When off-gassing is complete, no trace of the original solid remains.\n\nThis passive conversion persists when the element is left in storage.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.TRANSPARENT_DESC: Transparent materials allow <link=\"LIGHT\">Light</link> to pass through. Illumination boosts Duplicant productivity during working hours, but undermines sleep quality.\n\nTransparency is also important for buildings that require a clear line of sight in order to function correctly, such as the <link=\"COMETDETECTOR\">Space Scanner</link>.
STRINGS.MISC.TAGS.UNREFINEDOIL_DESC: Oils in their raw, minimally processed forms. They can be used as industrial lubricants or refined for other applications at designated buildings.

STRINGS.ROOMS.TYPES.CREATUREPEN.DESCRIPT:
Critters don't mind it here, as long as things don't get too crowded.

Stabled critters can be tended to in order to improve their happiness, hasten their domestication and increase their production.

Enables the use of Grooming Stations, Shearing Stations, Critter Condos, Critter Fountains and Milking Stations.
STRINGS.ROOMS.TYPES.CREATUREPEN.NAME: Stable
STRINGS.ROOMS.TYPES.CREATUREPEN.TOOLTIP: A stable enables Grooming Station, Critter Condo, Critter Fountain, Shearing Station and Milking Station use

STRINGS.ROOMS.TYPES.GREATHALL.DESCRIPTIO: A great place to eat, with great decor. Great!\n\nEating in a Great Hall will improve Duplicants' Morale.
